for them and young people.

590753171
01:12:52.837 --> 01:12:53.487
>> Minister.

102201148
01:12:53.489 --> 01:12:54.644
>> Can I thank my hon.

1362749020
01:12:54.645 --> 01:12:58.299
Friend, not just for her
question, but for the work that

807449725
01:12:58.300 --> 01:13:00.707
the Select Committee has
done on their inquiry.

1135431589
01:13:00.708 --> 01:13:03.418
And indeed, I know that she
had Alan Milburn along to

2484838148
01:13:03.419 --> 01:13:06.530
the committee recently to speak
to the work that he is doing.

2290332429
01:13:06.531 --> 01:13:10.495
She is absolutely right to call for
a focus on disabled people, too,

2162603176
01:13:10.496 --> 01:13:13.407
and the work that we are doing
around the Connect to Work

2557936974
01:13:13.408 --> 01:13:16.045
agenda does provide significant
support to people.

2419117765
01:13:16.045 --> 01:13:18.800
There is, of course, more
that we can always do,

1574139938
01:13:18.801 --> 01:13:22.801
but on this, as with
those not in employment,

2599288014
01:13:22.802 --> 01:13:27.504
education or training aged 16 to
84, we are determined to act.

2149467548
01:13:27.505 --> 01:13:30.917
We have a programme to do so,
and we take this extremely seriously.

2444952433
01:13:30.918 --> 01:13:33.994
>> Steve Darling Liberal
Democrat spokesperson.

489404704
01:13:33.995 --> 01:13:34.898
>> Thank you, Mr.

3517960981
01:13:34.899 --> 01:13:36.855
Speaker, and it's a pleasure to follow

1428841325
01:13:36.856 --> 01:13:39.293
the Member for Oldham
East and Saddleworth,

1637793615
01:13:39.294 --> 01:13:44.395
who always has something of
value to bring to the chamber.

3473632347
01:13:44.396 --> 01:13:48.551
With a million youngsters, not
an employment, education or training,

1152056349
01:13:48.552 --> 01:13:53.649
this is something that has
been brewing for many years,

1326244533
01:13:53.650 --> 01:13:57.197
but sadly it has been exacerbated
by the new Labour government.

343886000
01:13:57.197 --> 01:14:01.411
We've seen the sad decline of our
high streets over the last 20 years.

1544151322
01:14:01.411 --> 01:14:04.295
A quarter of a million jobs
lost in retail in the last

979946264
01:14:04.295 --> 01:14:09.496
five years and in the last
well since the last Budget,

3954691107
01:14:09.496 --> 01:14:13.494
a 100 000 jobs being lost in hospitality.

3813443192
01:14:13.495 --> 01:14:15.450
The dual impact of National Insurance,

3391857247
01:14:17.848 --> 01:14:20.156
job tax and also business
rates has hit hard.

1028586359
01:14:23.435 --> 01:14:25.692
3800 jobs Whitbread have
cut three 3800 jobs

3719746611
01:14:25.693 --> 01:14:29.093
across the United Kingdom with the closure

3749270368
01:14:29.094 --> 01:14:31.049
of two restaurants in my constituency,

3022861469
01:14:31.050 --> 01:14:32.856
one in Torquay and one in Paignton.

1389555478
01:14:34.844 --> 01:14:37.052
I'd like to welcome
most of the findings of

3424711306
01:14:37.053 --> 01:14:39.610
the Alan Milburn Review for
the Liberal Democrats.

1154420832
01:14:39.844 --> 01:14:44.244
We welcome the sense of direction
that this goes within,

3303948831
01:14:44.245 --> 01:14:47.054
but I'd like to ask some key
questions to the Minister.

399959895
01:14:47.056 --> 01:14:48.260
What plans do you have?

1156641241
01:14:48.261 --> 01:14:51.101
What plans does the Minister
have to bring forward some

1002030787
01:14:51.102 --> 01:14:55.155
clear economic plans to
grow jobs for young people,

1236315808
01:14:55.156 --> 01:14:59.152
but also, how can we grow
our greater connections

1328984624
01:15:01.802 --> 01:15:04.008
with European partners
to grow our economy?

3709879588
01:15:04.009 --> 01:15:05.362
>> Minister thank you, Mr.

286709279
01:15:05.364 --> 01:15:05.813
Speaker.

1211930324
01:15:05.815 --> 01:15:06.266
The hon.

939093695
01:15:06.267 --> 01:15:08.974
Gentleman will have heard
the Prime Minister's recent

1943102983
01:15:08.975 --> 01:15:11.081
intent to work more closely with European

2368451270
01:15:11.844 --> 01:15:13.697
colleagues in partnership because of

762094842
01:15:13.699 --> 01:15:17.348
the economic benefits that that can yield.

2524933487
01:15:17.349 --> 01:15:19.496
He is right to recognise that this is

401300796
01:15:19.496 --> 01:15:21.303
a problem many years in the making.

4034539370
01:15:21.844 --> 01:15:26.350
And can I welcome the broad support
from the Liberal Democrat,

4251998191
01:15:26.351 --> 01:15:29.208
from Liberal Democrat colleagues
for the interim review,

389603393
01:15:29.209 --> 01:15:32.005
and I hope that that will
be the same when the final

2833442382
01:15:32.007 --> 01:15:34.161
review comes forward with recommendations.

1573535336
01:15:34.161 --> 01:15:37.072
In terms of plans to bring
forward jobs for young people,

124870940
01:15:37.072 --> 01:15:39.780
I would point him to recently
announced interventions

2760104489
01:15:39.781 --> 01:15:42.005
by the Secretary of
State to provide £3,000

2711621135
01:15:42.007 --> 01:15:48.188
to small and medium sized enterprises
hiring apprenticeships and £2,000

506193965
01:15:48.190 --> 01:15:51.295
to any employer who hires
a young person who has been

1920382284
01:15:51.295 --> 01:15:53.603
on Universal Credit for
more than six months.

1173155893
01:15:53.603 --> 01:15:58.146
This will make a significant difference
and is the right thing to do.

4098069277
01:15:58.147 --> 01:16:01.258
>> Johanna Baxter thank you, Mr.

3996186885
01:16:01.259 --> 01:16:01.709
Speaker.

3551819483
01:16:01.710 --> 01:16:05.499
Too often young people are
written off as lacking ambition,

2086401728
01:16:05.500 --> 01:16:07.607
when the reality is that they are lacking

2946609573
01:16:07.608 --> 01:16:10.144
the opportunities of good work.

3277166700
01:16:10.145 --> 01:16:12.553
More than 40% of young
people not in education,

2441837848
01:16:12.843 --> 01:16:14.898
employment or training said that finding

2142635634
01:16:16.844 --> 01:16:18.850
fulfilling work was their top priority.

2425190631
01:16:18.851 --> 01:16:21.801
Despite that, in my area under
the SNP run Renfrewshire

4224769341
01:16:23.847 --> 01:16:25.902
Council and SNP run Holyrood government,

3301554369
01:16:25.903 --> 01:16:29.203
employability services are being cut 30%

3315357207
01:16:29.204 --> 01:16:32.706
failing too many of our young people.

1405796023
01:16:32.707 --> 01:16:33.460
So can my hon.

3499122865
01:16:33.461 --> 01:16:37.051
Friend set out what steps
the government is taking to work with

205430881
01:16:37.052 --> 01:16:41.349
the Scottish Government to protect
vital employability services,

524350856
01:16:41.350 --> 01:16:47.297
to ensure apprenticeship opportunities
for young people in my area.

3356546583
01:16:47.298 --> 01:16:48.201
>> Thank you, Mr.

2932048524
01:16:48.202 --> 01:16:48.652
Speaker.

3321286900
01:16:48.653 --> 01:16:49.657
Can I thank my hon.

453148912
01:16:49.658 --> 01:16:50.911
Friend for her question?

3016901511
01:16:50.911 --> 01:16:53.922
She knows that I met with
an employment support provider in

1234980786
01:16:53.923 --> 01:16:56.952
her constituency recently,
and I was grateful for her.

1101448353
01:16:56.953 --> 01:16:57.554
Welcome to.

3743067517
01:16:57.554 --> 01:17:00.008
She is absolutely right to say that young

202343784
01:17:00.009 --> 01:17:03.998
people do not lack ambition to find work.

2232548400
01:17:03.999 --> 01:17:09.205
This is a failure of the state's
making, not a failure of young people.

29858401
01:17:09.206 --> 01:17:11.499
And if she has specific
concerns about cuts

3622575002
01:17:11.500 --> 01:17:13.255
to employment support in her area,

1544014654
01:17:13.255 --> 01:17:15.263
I would very much welcome a letter from

112177225
01:17:15.264 --> 01:17:16.968
her setting out those challenges,

3073893022
01:17:16.969 --> 01:17:19.227
and I will raise those
issues on her behalf.

1041598814
01:17:19.228 --> 01:17:20.833
>> Peter Bedford thank you, Mr.

3798708581
01:17:20.834 --> 01:17:21.284
Speaker.

710479274
01:17:21.285 --> 01:17:24.748
As the report highlights, the number
of NEETs is set to rise to 1.25

4266948582
01:17:24.749 --> 01:17:27.759
million over the next five
years, and if something is done,

286192019
01:17:27.760 --> 01:17:30.669
the government need to listen
to the wealth creators that

947692868
01:17:30.670 --> 01:17:33.429
create the jobs that so many
of our young people need.

3290719515
01:17:33.431 --> 01:17:36.440
Indeed, Alan Milburn's report
says that 84% of young people

801678952
01:17:36.441 --> 01:17:39.352
really do want to get a job
to get education or training.

1810367147
01:17:39.353 --> 01:17:42.914
But because the policies of his
government is making that even harder.

3526886276
01:17:42.915 --> 01:17:45.925
So given that the government
is looking for a reset moment,

2453136155
01:17:45.926 --> 01:17:47.179
perhaps over the summer,

1942924888
01:17:47.179 --> 01:17:50.190
could I ask the Minister to
speak to his Cabinet colleagues

43403720
01:17:50.191 --> 01:17:52.849
to look again at the increase
in national insurance,

1124832149
01:17:52.850 --> 01:17:55.358
to look again at
the increases in business rates,

3832119684
01:17:55.359 --> 01:17:58.218
and to look again at repealing
the most damaging aspects

2801436978
01:17:58.219 --> 01:18:00.778
of the Employment Rights
Act that is doing so much

1589265060
01:18:00.779 --> 01:18:03.858
damage to the life prospects
of our young people?

1539040787
01:18:03.859 --> 01:18:04.109
Yes.

3533853019
01:18:04.110 --> 01:18:05.013
>> Thank you, Mr.

3877710546
01:18:06.848 --> 01:18:07.298
Speaker.

442270772
01:18:07.299 --> 01:18:07.901
My the hon.

515562102
01:18:07.902 --> 01:18:10.750
Gentleman has elevated
me to Cabinet level,

3297961682
01:18:10.751 --> 01:18:13.399
something that is at least premature,

1980216835
01:18:13.400 --> 01:18:15.356
if unlikely to ever happen, I suspect.

3607002176
01:18:15.357 --> 01:18:18.664
But may I just refer him to the report?

3539702558
01:18:18.665 --> 01:18:24.248
Because from the sound of it, he
has not read Milburn's report.

214833486
01:18:24.249 --> 01:18:27.562
He says, and I quote, the UK's
Neet crisis is much more long term

1083750378
01:18:27.563 --> 01:18:31.762
and deep seated than any decisions
taken in the last few years,

2467677802
01:18:31.763 --> 01:18:36.054
with particular reference
to National Insurance.

4260952950
01:18:36.056 --> 01:18:38.615
He says, and I quote, it
is worth remembering that

2769176175
01:18:38.616 --> 01:18:41.072
those under 21 remain
exempt from employer NICs.

2079264609
01:18:41.074 --> 01:18:43.230
And as the review has already highlighted,

1727928547
01:18:43.231 --> 01:18:46.097
the increase in youth inactivity long

3927428954
01:18:46.098 --> 01:18:49.696
precedes any recent changes to NICs.

813965344
01:18:49.697 --> 01:18:50.399
>> Thank you.

2924662170
01:18:50.400 --> 01:18:51.303
>> Thank you, Mr.

2389734491
01:18:51.848 --> 01:18:52.298
Speaker.

3187475438
01:18:52.299 --> 01:18:54.255
I'd like to welcome the interim report

698211962
01:18:54.255 --> 01:18:56.362
and ask a question about work experience.

4042611712
01:18:56.362 --> 01:19:00.709
When I was at school, this was typically
organised by teachers and gave

899574250
01:19:00.710 --> 01:19:04.019
children a peek into worlds that
otherwise would be unimaginable.

2815618864
01:19:04.020 --> 01:19:06.376
But today, children in
my Bristol constituency

3252216312
01:19:06.377 --> 01:19:09.201
are being asked to find
their own placements,

51555637
01:19:09.202 --> 01:19:11.406
which obviously
disadvantages children from

4229605526
01:19:11.407 --> 01:19:13.649
families that are less well connected.

657078095
01:19:13.650 --> 01:19:16.197
So I'd like to ask, will we be likely

4271497195
01:19:16.199 --> 01:19:18.103
to see more organised work experience

2124480527
01:19:18.105 --> 01:19:23.260
placements for school children
as a result of this review?

1657827805
01:19:23.261 --> 01:19:24.416
>> Can I thank my hon.

2629645998
01:19:24.417 --> 01:19:25.670
Friend for his question?

745437984
01:19:26.848 --> 01:19:29.457
He is entirely right to
highlight the value of work

3619075997
01:19:29.458 --> 01:19:31.914
experiences and in particular
from children from

3174677544
01:19:31.915 --> 01:19:34.420
disadvantaged backgrounds
who perhaps do not have

580921116
01:19:34.422 --> 01:19:36.527
the connections that others benefit from.

3896434973
01:19:36.528 --> 01:19:38.886
He will be pleased to
know that the government

911264980
01:19:38.887 --> 01:19:41.042
is committed to reforming work experience,

425312244
01:19:41.043 --> 01:19:42.998
to break down barriers to opportunity,

3685214175
01:19:42.999 --> 01:19:46.461
so that every pupil will have access
to two weeks worth of multiple,

4087965007
01:19:46.462 --> 01:19:48.666
meaningful and varied
workplace experiences

4111013545
01:19:48.848 --> 01:19:50.753
throughout key stages three and four,

386198327
01:19:50.754 --> 01:19:53.451
progressively increasing
their work readiness

592487037
01:19:53.452 --> 01:19:55.899
as they move through secondary education.

1906309112
01:19:55.900 --> 01:19:57.355
>> John Milne thank you, Mr.

3542731826
01:19:57.848 --> 01:19:58.298
Speaker.

2620689329
01:19:58.299 --> 01:20:01.507
I welcome the government's Youth
Guarantee Scheme and something

3548691693
01:20:01.508 --> 01:20:05.054
similar similar operates in
a number of European countries.

4186293945
01:20:05.054 --> 01:20:09.248
However, under the proposals, it
does not kick in for 18 months.

1996472964
01:20:09.249 --> 01:20:12.660
If someone is unemployed for 18
months, the damage is already done.

575296930
01:20:12.661 --> 01:20:19.236
Will the government I can
understand consider acting earlier?

4234240020
01:20:19.237 --> 01:20:20.692
>> I can understand the hon.

3035286792
01:20:20.693 --> 01:20:22.648
Gentleman's trepidation, but I fear he

3614776300
01:20:22.649 --> 01:20:25.478
has not been made aware of the full

3144208639
01:20:25.478 --> 01:20:28.846
range of activity that happens before

1480078100
01:20:28.847 --> 01:20:30.652
the 18 month intervention kicks in.

1975133295
01:20:30.653 --> 01:20:34.255
The addition of a reframed employment
and skills review at two weeks,

1820802639
01:20:34.257 --> 01:20:37.855
the maintenance of weekly
appointments from weeks 3 to 12,

1854142004
01:20:37.856 --> 01:20:41.366
with increased focus on personal
support to address barriers to work.

798100682
01:20:41.367 --> 01:20:44.826
After three months, the Specialist
Youth Guarantee Gateway kicks in,

2641141865
01:20:44.827 --> 01:20:48.388
where young people are referred to
one of six options including swaps,

1909943054
01:20:48.389 --> 01:20:51.445
training, work experience,
apprenticeships at six months.

1000947237
01:20:51.446 --> 01:20:53.552
The £3,000 Youth Jobs grant for employers

1471402564
01:20:53.553 --> 01:20:55.257
recruiting young people kicks in.

3975812056
01:20:55.258 --> 01:20:58.218
This is one part of a range of
holistic interventions, Mr.

1940633894
01:20:58.219 --> 01:21:00.776
Speaker, which we consider
will make a significant

3843541332
01:21:00.777 --> 01:21:02.632
difference to the challenge we face.

4068402739
01:21:02.633 --> 01:21:06.505
>> Jim McMahon.

285097357
01:21:06.506 --> 01:21:07.358
Isn't the truth.

463829750
01:21:07.359 --> 01:21:10.252
>> The government's just
do not respect working

2254239388
01:21:10.253 --> 01:21:11.906
class jobs like apprenticeships.

369966756
01:21:11.907 --> 01:21:14.715
You know, since the apprenticeship
levy was brought in,

797285347
01:21:14.716 --> 01:21:17.404
the number of starts
has dropped by 35% and

3509741247
01:21:17.405 --> 01:21:21.656
the number of level two
starts has dropped by 68%.

1589344340
01:21:21.657 --> 01:21:25.507
And even those that did take place,
only 16% of them were advertised

795702710
01:21:25.508 --> 01:21:28.718
in the two months that young
people were finishing their exams,

167470438
01:21:28.809 --> 01:21:31.316
creating that gap that
young people fall through.

4043065980
01:21:31.317 --> 01:21:34.803
And so the Milburn Review is
welcome and absolutely needed.

771737957
01:21:34.804 --> 01:21:39.756
And I'm appreciative of
the government for starting this process.

1627460502
01:21:39.757 --> 01:21:41.062
But can I ask two things?

287947133
01:21:41.063 --> 01:21:43.472
First of all, why can't
we close that gap today

2975710097
01:21:43.473 --> 01:21:45.629
and say that every public sector employer,

3100779068
01:21:45.854 --> 01:21:47.658
whether it's the government itself,

4294882409
01:21:47.659 --> 01:21:50.207
a council, the police service or the NHS,

1562438729
01:21:50.208 --> 01:21:53.518
must advertise at the point that
young people are leaving school,

4097310312
01:21:53.519 --> 01:21:55.977
and secondly, that devolution
has got to be part

616604792
01:21:55.978 --> 01:21:58.084
of this problem because we cannot command

3990620152
01:21:58.085 --> 01:22:00.142
and control from the centre when so much

2819038947
01:22:00.143 --> 01:22:02.861
of this is about localised economies.

3373453393
01:22:02.862 --> 01:22:04.017
>> Can I thank my hon.

2180624658
01:22:04.018 --> 01:22:05.553
Friend for his question?

1838960998
01:22:05.554 --> 01:22:08.463
I certainly agree with him
about the power of devolution,

2497972432
01:22:08.464 --> 01:22:11.709
something that he and I know
only too well from our roles as

2627898183
01:22:11.710 --> 01:22:16.006
leaders within the Greater
Manchester Combined Authority.

3883082600
01:22:16.007 --> 01:22:19.904
But what I hope that he will recognise
is that this government is taking

2965855218
01:22:19.905 --> 01:22:23.413
a very different approach on
apprenticeships and technical education,

1098476195
01:22:23.414 --> 01:22:26.623
and that is underpinned by
the Prime Minister's revised target,

3491349933
01:22:26.624 --> 01:22:29.032
not of 50% of young people
going to university,

203693056
01:22:29.809 --> 01:22:31.866
but two thirds of young people in either

1858174502
01:22:31.867 --> 01:22:33.821
an apprenticeship or higher education.

4079954187
01:22:33.822 --> 01:22:35.427
>> So, Oliver Dowden thank you.

160950519
01:22:35.428 --> 01:22:35.779
>> Mr.

2780418037
01:22:35.780 --> 01:22:36.230
Speaker.

2263458691
01:22:36.231 --> 01:22:39.409
Many young people take
time to adapt to new jobs

4121966939
01:22:39.410 --> 01:22:43.657
and simply haven't proved
themselves after six months.

2734242370
01:22:43.658 --> 01:22:45.364
But with the coming into force of

3055870959
01:22:45.365 --> 01:22:49.454
the Government's Employment Rights Act,

709135503
01:22:49.455 --> 01:22:53.456
they're going to increase
the reduce the period for dismissal

316201047
01:22:53.457 --> 01:22:55.906
without fault from two
years to six months.

2066776813
01:22:55.907 --> 01:22:58.756
Now, many employers have told me this will

2412182553
01:22:58.757 --> 01:23:02.162
make them much less likely to employ

3880381386
01:23:02.163 --> 01:23:04.269
young people because they fear they won't

4080330262
01:23:04.270 --> 01:23:06.175
prove themselves in that time period,

3846015045
01:23:06.176 --> 01:23:08.635
and indeed, after six
months to get rid of them,

815664592
01:23:08.636 --> 01:23:11.894
unless they really prove themselves
because they fear otherwise,

4281969829
01:23:11.895 --> 01:23:13.300
it would be so much harder.

203412231
01:23:13.301 --> 01:23:15.961
Now, this provision is not
due to come into force at

3518038816
01:23:15.962 --> 01:23:18.675
the beginning of next year,
at this very late stage.

4091921262
01:23:18.676 --> 01:23:20.935
Can I urge the Minister
to look at it again?

2209324403
01:23:20.936 --> 01:23:24.398
Because it will make a bad situation
so much worse for young people.

2477890845
01:23:24.853 --> 01:23:27.161
>> I understand the point
that the right hon.

1716896023
01:23:28.811 --> 01:23:31.722
Gentleman is making, but
I have to say I have rather more

2897930180
01:23:31.723 --> 01:23:36.257
faith in young people in
the workforce than he seems to.

1294131852
01:23:36.258 --> 01:23:40.210
It is the case that the Employment
Rights Act is an important and once

147350031
01:23:40.211 --> 01:23:43.471
in a generation opportunity to
level up rights in the workplace.

3637082765
01:23:43.472 --> 01:23:45.527
This government remains committed to it.

2878838726
01:23:45.853 --> 01:23:46.304
>> They.

1756865147
01:23:46.305 --> 01:23:47.258
>> Meg Hillier Mr.

2903165282
01:23:47.259 --> 01:23:50.958
Speaker, I very much welcome
this report by Alan Milburn,

1682758321
01:23:50.959 --> 01:23:53.616
and he highlights the need
to work cross-sectionally

2431231353
01:23:53.617 --> 01:23:54.955
to support young people.

4290731773
01:23:54.956 --> 01:23:57.013
I wonder if the Minister could take away

4279940446
01:23:57.014 --> 01:23:58.669
the thought that he could pilot,

207586080
01:23:58.670 --> 01:24:01.781
test and, and learn by doing
a pilot in Hackney with choices,

3234074405
01:24:01.782 --> 01:24:04.390
which works with disabled
people and my local mind,

2379988553
01:24:04.391 --> 01:24:06.446
which have very good employment training

1460890359
01:24:06.447 --> 01:24:08.152
schemes to help people into work.

1701377527
01:24:08.153 --> 01:24:11.462
Their success rate is phenomenally
higher than DWP success rates,

2431458969
01:24:11.463 --> 01:24:14.424
and we'd be very keen to work
with the government on this.

4129854043
01:24:14.425 --> 01:24:15.881
>> Can I thank my right hon.

2221759375
01:24:15.882 --> 01:24:17.751
Friend for her question?

2924319054
01:24:17.752 --> 01:24:20.904
She makes an important
observation that for

491072484
01:24:20.905 --> 01:24:23.457
us to make successful
change in this space,

3661251909
01:24:23.458 --> 01:24:26.604
we need to work with a range
of partners and providers.

3576144371
01:24:26.605 --> 01:24:29.809
I am very happy to propose
on the terms that she has,

3921815960
01:24:29.810 --> 01:24:32.858
that Hackney be put forward to
test some of the initiatives

1518726303
01:24:32.859 --> 01:24:35.411
that we look to take
forward in this space.

1025717510
01:24:35.412 --> 01:24:37.317
It's not just working with charities,

1604532040
01:24:37.318 --> 01:24:40.929
employment support providers that we
need to look at in moving forward,

135080294
01:24:40.930 --> 01:24:43.636
but also working more
holistically across government,

4234586272
01:24:43.637 --> 01:24:46.193
with health, with education
and other departments.

2179070135
01:24:46.194 --> 01:24:47.950
We are determined to do that work.

2368025944
01:24:47.951 --> 01:24:48.854
>> Very much, Mr.

1598231397
01:24:48.860 --> 01:24:49.310
Speaker.

677133621
01:24:49.311 --> 01:24:52.857
Alan Milburn, in his excellent
but devastating report,

3016127466
01:24:52.858 --> 01:24:57.760
makes clear that young people most at
risk of ending up out of education

2549081536
01:24:57.761 --> 01:25:01.825
or employment are likely to go
to a further education college,

960252485
01:25:01.852 --> 01:25:07.409
and he identifies that 32,000 of
those places are currently unfunded.

2855132165
01:25:07.410 --> 01:25:08.664
Now, just last year, Mr.

1067634979
01:25:09.852 --> 01:25:13.361
Speaker, in her Skills White Paper,
the Education Secretary promised,

2568564098
01:25:13.362 --> 01:25:14.014
and I quote,

2002647443
01:25:14.015 --> 01:25:16.206
increased real terms per pupil funding in

3927587987
01:25:16.207 --> 01:25:19.060
the next academic year
for 16 to 19 providers.

3778543465
01:25:19.061 --> 01:25:22.022
Yet I know from talking to my
local college that per head,

1707803553
01:25:22.023 --> 01:25:26.211
funding this year is
only going up by 0.55%.

1794363008
01:25:26.212 --> 01:25:30.119
That is a real terms cut
and a broken promise,

1134263527
01:25:30.120 --> 01:25:33.964
coupled with the lag in funding
of up to a year for new students.

331747088
01:25:33.965 --> 01:25:39.558
This is actually disincentivising
colleges to take on these pupils.

3825590845
01:25:39.559 --> 01:25:41.364
How does the Minister explain that?

2445151192
01:25:41.857 --> 01:25:43.866
>> I mean, what I would say to the hon.

795410714
01:25:43.867 --> 01:25:49.919
Lady is that the 0.55% increase
in 16 to 19 funding rates is only

3502879871
01:25:49.920 --> 01:25:54.358
one aspect of 16 to 19 funding
in the academic year 2026 to 27,

1730061441
01:25:54.359 --> 01:25:57.412
we will provide nearly
£9 billion in 16 to 19.

2280823737
01:25:57.413 --> 01:26:02.820
Funding and overall funding per
student will rise by 1.66%.

3344375649
01:26:02.821 --> 01:26:06.364
Meeting the White Paper commitment
by reflecting inflation

3277680216
01:26:06.365 --> 01:26:08.622
at the time the spending
review was settled.

2084649819
01:26:08.855 --> 01:26:10.310
>> Anna Dixon thank you, Mr.

1887047787
01:26:10.311 --> 01:26:10.761
Speaker.

1524586404
01:26:10.762 --> 01:26:13.864
This excellent report
makes clear that exams

3838907513
01:26:13.865 --> 01:26:16.254
can lead to early school disengagement,

123327341
01:26:16.255 --> 01:26:18.958
particularly for children
who are neurodiverse.

3522447640
01:26:18.959 --> 01:26:24.114
My constituent Danielle's son,
repeatedly failed his GCSEs,

3370201802
01:26:24.115 --> 01:26:27.157
leaving him stressed
and undermining his self-confidence.

4225134634
01:26:27.856 --> 01:26:30.062
She felt his opportunities
would be limited

3427018561
01:26:30.063 --> 01:26:32.370
and doors would be closed for him,

2238142225
01:26:32.371 --> 01:26:36.058
but thankfully he was encouraged to
take functional skills and has now

1426440952
01:26:36.059 --> 01:26:39.419
secured a place at Leeds College
of Building to learn bricklaying.

683192049
01:26:39.420 --> 01:26:43.711
So does the Minister agree that
early information and awareness

2588021398
01:26:43.712 --> 01:26:46.116
around alternative
qualifications and pathways,

3816456731
01:26:46.117 --> 01:26:51.402
such as functional skills, can help
young people fulfil their potential?

2675794871
01:26:51.403 --> 01:26:52.103
Commissioner.

3118412156
01:26:52.104 --> 01:26:54.412
>> I would just absolutely
agree with my hon.

4170347775
01:26:54.413 --> 01:26:55.014
Friend, Mr.

3116566956
01:26:55.015 --> 01:26:58.277
speaker, and if she has any ideas
of how we can extend knowledge

346477229
01:26:58.278 --> 01:27:01.538
and availability of such information,
I'd be happy to hear them.

1364031664
01:27:01.539 --> 01:27:02.692
>> Bob Blackman thank.

616723299
01:27:02.693 --> 01:27:03.295
>> You, Mr.

1013240462
01:27:03.296 --> 01:27:03.746
Speaker.

3334926328
01:27:03.747 --> 01:27:05.852
Clearly, the Minister needs to understand

4245478925
01:27:05.853 --> 01:27:07.760
that to create the jobs that we need,

4175539502
01:27:07.761 --> 01:27:10.319
we need to encourage
the private sector to invest.

4197457243
01:27:10.320 --> 01:27:13.077
And in my constituency, every
single hospitality venue

42381395
01:27:13.078 --> 01:27:15.285
has halved the number
of staff they employ.

4060755926
01:27:15.286 --> 01:27:20.407
And when I've asked the question why
they question National Insurance,

2151522264
01:27:20.408 --> 01:27:24.662
obviously non-domestic rates
and also the new Employment Rights Act,

2814706916
01:27:24.663 --> 01:27:30.262
the key key here is that if National
Insurance is extended, the holiday,

1243268363
01:27:30.263 --> 01:27:32.323
if you like, from from 28 to 20 1 to 24,

2238133300
01:27:32.856 --> 01:27:36.508
that will enable people that leave
school to get a job and also

3724853748
01:27:36.509 --> 01:27:40.655
those that leave university
to get a job and de-risk

223170426
01:27:40.656 --> 01:27:46.059
the employment of employers
taking on young people.

4076826268
01:27:46.060 --> 01:27:46.662
>> The hon.

715164972
01:27:46.663 --> 01:27:50.911
Gentleman is correct to
highlight that incentives are

2057792688
01:27:50.912 --> 01:27:53.966
needed to encourage employers
to hire young people.

4222657885
01:27:53.967 --> 01:27:55.272
That is why my right hon.

4148257047
01:27:55.273 --> 01:27:57.729
Friend the Secretary of
State recently announced

1032660909
01:27:57.730 --> 01:27:59.736
the incentives that I have already laid

1347116665
01:27:59.737 --> 01:28:01.943
out around supporting
young people who have

1215819857
01:28:01.944 --> 01:28:04.000
been on Universal Credit for six months,

2138931150
01:28:04.001 --> 01:28:08.411
incentivising employers in
financial terms to hire them,

2208436896
01:28:08.412 --> 01:28:12.210
and also in apprentices under the age
of 25 earning less than £50,000,

1827885566
01:28:12.211 --> 01:28:17.508
where there is also an incentive for
small and medium sized enterprises.

461516481
01:28:17.509 --> 01:28:18.864
>> Jo White thank you, Mr.

2222472039
01:28:18.865 --> 01:28:19.315
Speaker.

1804083318
01:28:19.316 --> 01:28:20.018
>> I've just.

576615569
01:28:20.019 --> 01:28:22.203
>> Had a group of year eight pupils visit.

634824576
01:28:22.204 --> 01:28:23.508
>> Me in Parliament, and.

1924372099
01:28:23.509 --> 01:28:27.070
>> Many of their questions were about
the increasing numbers of young.

3791612858
01:28:27.071 --> 01:28:27.773
>> People on.

3894067346
01:28:27.774 --> 01:28:30.682
>> Benefits, AI sweeping away
jobs and new opportunities,

1202909206
01:28:30.683 --> 01:28:32.237
and training for young people.

4037885748
01:28:32.238 --> 01:28:34.946
>> The Red wall MPs recognise
that issues surrounding

2532483193
01:28:34.947 --> 01:28:36.501
youth unemployment is not new,

134049254
01:28:36.502 --> 01:28:38.658
but I'm hugely concerned that young people

1334903443
01:28:38.861 --> 01:28:40.717
are now seeing this as their future.

3126156641
01:28:40.718 --> 01:28:43.561
I very much welcome
the government initiative

258429845
01:28:43.562 --> 01:28:45.454
to have a youth hub in Worksop,

317395254
01:28:45.455 --> 01:28:48.757
and I'm already working
with partners on this.

1238307184
01:28:48.758 --> 01:28:53.261
But does the Minister agree with me
that it's working beyond the DWP

3646542666
01:28:53.262 --> 01:28:55.269
and with other partners that we need to

3844271907
01:28:55.270 --> 01:28:59.268
work do to to resolve this problem?

4157409350
01:28:59.269 --> 01:29:00.223
>> I do agree, Mr.

848457650
01:29:00.224 --> 01:29:01.629
Speaker, and I hope my hon.

2731258571
01:29:01.630 --> 01:29:04.558
Friend heard what I said in
response to my right hon.

558613316
01:29:04.559 --> 01:29:07.818
Friend from Hackney earlier about
the need to work holistically,

3453882070
01:29:07.819 --> 01:29:10.325
both across government
and outside of government,

622402761
01:29:10.326 --> 01:29:12.331
with partners in the charitable sector,

2659815625
01:29:12.332 --> 01:29:14.085
with employment support companies,

2735175777
01:29:14.086 --> 01:29:15.087
etcetera, etcetera,

720482539
01:29:15.088 --> 01:29:18.700
to make sure that we have that range
of interventions available so that

3602778739
01:29:18.862 --> 01:29:22.764
young people do not do exactly what
she outlines and see a career,

3783019498
01:29:22.765 --> 01:29:26.012
a life not in education,
employment or training

3065593853
01:29:26.013 --> 01:29:30.118
as their future, that we must stop.

1459493382
01:29:30.119 --> 01:29:32.024
>> Suella Braverman 70% of graduates.

3692721314
01:29:32.025 --> 01:29:34.282
>> Say that university
just wasn't worth it.

3924934272
01:29:34.283 --> 01:29:38.323
And is it any wonder when we've seen
an increase in low quality degrees,

3613926935
01:29:38.324 --> 01:29:41.612
people coming out with crippling debt

2724324640
01:29:41.613 --> 01:29:43.568
and lower job prospects for graduates?

189666655
01:29:43.569 --> 01:29:46.277
Whilst I welcome many elements
in The Milburn Review,

3697003387
01:29:46.278 --> 01:29:49.891
isn't it right that if we are to fix
this crisis of youth unemployment,

4030370650
01:29:49.892 --> 01:29:52.261
what's needed is not tweaks,

702702552
01:29:52.262 --> 01:29:54.418
but an overhaul of vocational and training

2233044159
01:29:56.862 --> 01:29:59.018
and a correction to the Blairite obsession

3904992298
01:29:59.019 --> 01:30:01.725
with university so that fewer young people

2951484538
01:30:01.726 --> 01:30:06.114
get scammed by the great university.

2094713314
01:30:06.115 --> 01:30:06.365
Con.

1998670498
01:30:06.366 --> 01:30:06.566
No.

3350150192
01:30:06.567 --> 01:30:08.316
>> I have to say, Mr.

1225872951
01:30:08.317 --> 01:30:10.374
Speaker, that I wouldn't put it quite in

2362980995
01:30:12.856 --> 01:30:14.712
the terms utilised by the right hon.

2331483133
01:30:14.713 --> 01:30:16.869
Lady, but jingoistic rhetoric is a feature

488792658
01:30:16.870 --> 01:30:19.914
of her new place in this House.

2344606493
01:30:19.915 --> 01:30:23.061
What I would say on that, Mr.

2620933997
01:30:23.062 --> 01:30:25.371
Speaker, is, as I said
in response to my hon.

920081623
01:30:25.856 --> 01:30:27.109
Friend from Oldham West,

2155037931
01:30:27.110 --> 01:30:30.624
this government recognises
that it should no longer

97613051
01:30:30.625 --> 01:30:32.809
be a target for any government to send

2744704379
01:30:32.810 --> 01:30:34.565
50% of young people to university.

4117110413
01:30:34.566 --> 01:30:37.814
That is why we have revised
the target in such a way that

915165905
01:30:37.815 --> 01:30:41.061
it now is the case that this
government's aspiration

2358291864
01:30:41.062 --> 01:30:44.266
is that 66% of young people
are either in higher

1767003008
01:30:44.267 --> 01:30:46.471
education or undertaking
an apprenticeship.

1391298045
01:30:46.472 --> 01:30:47.424
>> Rachel, Boston.

1273405918
01:30:47.425 --> 01:30:48.328
>> Thank you, Mr.

3350119022
01:30:48.329 --> 01:30:48.779
Speaker.

2072814898
01:30:48.780 --> 01:30:52.769
In York, 410 young people are not in
education, training or employment.

805218365
01:30:52.770 --> 01:30:58.171
And of course, we know from Alan
Milburn's report the causation of that.

4287053768
01:30:58.172 --> 01:31:01.629
And particularly, I want to focus
on mental health and the fact

786971196
01:31:01.630 --> 01:31:04.841
that we don't have the right
support in place for young people,

1110046402
01:31:04.857 --> 01:31:07.414
much earlier than the point
of seeking employment.

2056916368
01:31:07.415 --> 01:31:09.723
Will he work with
the Department of Health to

3108567164
01:31:09.858 --> 01:31:12.015
ensure that we have those systems in place

943712630
01:31:12.016 --> 01:31:16.015
to identify young people who
experience mental health challenges,

4017702739
01:31:16.016 --> 01:31:16.968
and in particular,

58892358
01:31:16.969 --> 01:31:19.223
children with adverse
childhood experiences,

728470799
01:31:19.224 --> 01:31:21.383
so that they can be set on a stronger path

4059986342
01:31:21.384 --> 01:31:24.040
and build more resilience
throughout their childhood

1961910782
01:31:24.041 --> 01:31:26.812
to enable them to be prepared for work.

3569504126
01:31:26.813 --> 01:31:27.365
>> My hon.

3416066748
01:31:27.366 --> 01:31:30.024
Friend is absolutely right
to recognise that many of

646268702
01:31:30.025 --> 01:31:32.831
the challenges faced by young
people not in education,

485444502
01:31:32.832 --> 01:31:36.267
employment or training start
at school or even pre-school,

153663741
01:31:36.861 --> 01:31:40.473
and that we need to ensure that there
is early intervention in schools,

2324131381
01:31:40.474 --> 01:31:44.261
more mental health practitioners
available to children and young people,

3140976807
01:31:44.262 --> 01:31:45.968
and that they are able to receive

1755987356
01:31:45.969 --> 01:31:48.714
the support needed at the first possible

1185329119
01:31:48.715 --> 01:31:51.723
opportunity because it does
blight and affect their future,

1466642744
01:31:51.724 --> 01:31:53.680
not just in academic terms with exams,

834198252
01:31:53.681 --> 01:31:55.587
but often for many years beyond that.

303412922
01:31:55.588 --> 01:31:57.365
So I absolutely agree with her.

1566129679
01:31:57.366 --> 01:31:59.422
This underpins many of the proposals put

1055914511
01:31:59.821 --> 01:32:01.876
forward by the Department for Education.

1863861512
01:32:01.877 --> 01:32:04.182
With their special
educational needs reforms.

2044625837
01:32:04.183 --> 01:32:06.540
We need early intervention
and we need greater

2792083839
01:32:06.541 --> 01:32:08.345
mental health support for children.

3117469453
01:32:08.346 --> 01:32:08.797
>> Nice.

1419326504
01:32:08.798 --> 01:32:10.203
>> Thank you very much, Mr.

1561098559
01:32:10.204 --> 01:32:10.654
Speaker.

1105195640
01:32:10.655 --> 01:32:13.364
This is an important piece
of work from Alan Milburn,

2805193469
01:32:13.365 --> 01:32:15.974
but I want to ask
the Minister about the principles

2929614289
01:32:15.975 --> 01:32:18.280
that will underpin
the government's approach.

3144663468
01:32:18.281 --> 01:32:20.538
Does he think that other
things being equal,

2509175002
01:32:20.539 --> 01:32:23.918
if you increase the cost
of employing people,

242837679
01:32:23.919 --> 01:32:27.161
that will come at the cost of jobs,

3463118415
01:32:27.162 --> 01:32:30.221
and that if there is slack
in the labour market,

2864592385
01:32:30.222 --> 01:32:34.669
then if you do things like reducing
probation periods at the same time,

3491796498
01:32:34.670 --> 01:32:38.719
at a time when the cost of
employing younger people

3400791879
01:32:38.720 --> 01:32:41.466
without experience is any way going up,

3226810677
01:32:41.467 --> 01:32:44.921
that that will mean those young
people are less likely to be

1768763790
01:32:44.922 --> 01:32:47.780
given the opportunities
and the vacancies that do exist.

1179452627
01:32:47.781 --> 01:32:48.081
Yeah.

1932828946
01:32:48.865 --> 01:32:50.873
>> Well, I do agree with the right hon.

3250415074
01:32:51.873 --> 01:32:53.979
Gentleman is that in the current climate,

2927902661
01:32:53.980 --> 01:32:58.268
incentives are required to encourage
employers to hire young people.

661030468
01:32:58.269 --> 01:33:01.724
I have set out the measures
that we have taken to do that,

1910824674
01:33:01.725 --> 01:33:04.336
but he is one of a number
of members from the party

748638583
01:33:04.337 --> 01:33:06.867
opposite today to raise
the Workers Rights Act.

2913932916
01:33:06.868 --> 01:33:10.028
This is the biggest upgrade to
workers rights in a generation.

178730867
01:33:10.029 --> 01:33:13.170
This government is steadfast in
continuing to support working

243787060
01:33:13.861 --> 01:33:16.870
people and making sure that
that bill is fully implemented.

3265429253
01:33:16.871 --> 01:33:17.573
>> I Bedford.

1747266192
01:33:17.574 --> 01:33:17.925
>> Mr.

1308128338
01:33:17.926 --> 01:33:21.265
Speaker, this generation of NEETs grew up

1339836327
01:33:21.266 --> 01:33:25.117
under the Tory austerity they suffered.

3761313718
01:33:25.118 --> 01:33:27.815
They suffered closure
of Surestart centres.

121163990
01:33:27.816 --> 01:33:32.472
They finished their education with funding

3746817626
01:33:32.473 --> 01:33:34.330
per pupil lower than it was in 2010.

1584600410
01:33:34.331 --> 01:33:36.439
And then many of them grew up in poverty.

923390976
01:33:36.440 --> 01:33:38.412
Does my right hon.

3444660280
01:33:38.413 --> 01:33:38.813
Friend.

3232928428
01:33:38.814 --> 01:33:39.215
My hon.

2753274964
01:33:39.216 --> 01:33:41.775
Friend agree that we need
a root and branch change

26640539
01:33:41.776 --> 01:33:43.882
from what we had under the Conservatives?

2405342260
