03:35:40.593 --> 03:35:41.495
>> My honourable.

3861858143
03:35:41.496 --> 03:35:42.800
>> Friend for giving way.

3268908585
03:35:42.801 --> 03:35:46.412
He's talking about the support that
this Labour government is giving to

349553520
03:35:46.413 --> 03:35:49.972
veterans and improving their housing
situation in my own constituency,

2754188807
03:35:49.973 --> 03:35:51.477
the East Sussex Veterans Hub,

3445424109
03:35:51.478 --> 03:35:54.084
provide really valuable
support for local veterans,

1297734352
03:35:54.085 --> 03:35:57.146
and they have just received
a half £1 million grant to scale

3277710969
03:35:57.147 --> 03:35:59.805
up the work they're doing
and convert disused office

2380923184
03:35:59.806 --> 03:36:02.906
block accommodation in Hastings
town centre into supported

1321399079
03:36:03.992 --> 03:36:06.699
accommodation for over 14
veterans, which is amazing.

145465755
03:36:06.700 --> 03:36:08.853
So will he join me in paying tribute to

3299651485
03:36:08.854 --> 03:36:10.610
the work that the Veterans Hub do,

2668367703
03:36:10.611 --> 03:36:12.014
led by Bernard Stonestreet,

3695903803
03:36:12.015 --> 03:36:14.022
and could I extend an invitation to him

3632556448
03:36:14.023 --> 03:36:15.728
to visit the Sussex Veterans Hub,

3544181297
03:36:15.729 --> 03:36:20.099
where he will be pleased to know
they've built a full scale flight

3828094551
03:36:20.100 --> 03:36:23.594
simulator where you can come
and simulate Operation Black Buck,

943380960
03:36:23.595 --> 03:36:28.245
which I know they'd be delighted
to welcome him to Minister.

834007909
03:36:28.246 --> 03:36:31.407
>> As an ex-Marine, I've never
been known for flying, but the.

971561848
03:36:31.408 --> 03:36:34.921
I would love to come and visit East
Sussex Veterans Hub and it always

693942456
03:36:34.922 --> 03:36:38.233
amazes me when you go around
the country, whether it be Scotland,

1778196590
03:36:38.234 --> 03:36:41.894
Northern Ireland, Wales or England,
where you find these little examples

1326968286
03:36:41.895 --> 03:36:44.804
of just pure community spirit
that help our veterans out.

3248525411
03:36:44.805 --> 03:36:47.864
And importantly, the flight
simulator, whilst it may be fun,

24655176
03:36:47.865 --> 03:36:51.326
also helps people learn critical
skills and get them back into work.

3155462346
03:36:51.327 --> 03:36:54.840
And I'd like to thank Bernard in
particular for all of his hard work.

848384131
03:36:54.841 --> 03:36:57.501
And if I can come and visit,
I most definitely will.

4264608515
03:36:57.502 --> 03:36:59.107
I'll make way ever so slightly.

2776047163
03:36:59.108 --> 03:37:01.464
Amendment 48 means
the Defence Housing Service

2968358421
03:37:01.465 --> 03:37:03.721
provisions comes into
force on Royal assent,

1627249314
03:37:03.722 --> 03:37:06.029
ensuring no delays in
standing up the Defence

3480772716
03:37:06.030 --> 03:37:08.036
Housing Service as early as April 2027,

2516893720
03:37:08.037 --> 03:37:10.495
I will remind the House
that the Defence Housing

1864970522
03:37:10.496 --> 03:37:12.402
Strategy plans 9 in 10 defence houses

3746717335
03:37:12.403 --> 03:37:15.543
will be modernised
or upgraded for our family

3049333692
03:37:15.544 --> 03:37:17.599
personnel 4000 across the entire estate.

2342625319
03:37:17.600 --> 03:37:20.497
This is a once in a generation
opportunity with over

503058397
03:37:20.498 --> 03:37:24.396
10,000 refurbished
or replaced over that period.

752756036
03:37:24.397 --> 03:37:25.651
I will give way, giving.

1678683567
03:37:25.652 --> 03:37:29.105
>> Way and I'm sure he would
also like to pay tribute to

2650587553
03:37:29.106 --> 03:37:31.764
the work of Aylesbury in
and around my constituency,

3218455058
03:37:31.765 --> 03:37:33.971
which does great work
for service veterans.

4009847092
03:37:33.972 --> 03:37:37.596
However, will he ensure that we
don't give the false impression?

2688471636
03:37:37.597 --> 03:37:40.106
And that is to say that
veterans are all homeless

3696609581
03:37:40.107 --> 03:37:41.761
and have mental health problems,

2454128430
03:37:41.762 --> 03:37:44.219
because nothing could be
further from the truth,

1505261073
03:37:44.220 --> 03:37:47.747
and the great majority of people
leaving our armed forces happily

1142430150
03:37:47.748 --> 03:37:51.250
are well sorted in their lives
and are in robust mental health,

2647419178
03:37:51.251 --> 03:37:54.301
which is important since
we need to attract people

1349945764
03:37:54.302 --> 03:37:56.760
to join our armed forces
and our reserve forces,

2936159151
03:37:56.761 --> 03:38:00.452
not deter them or put them off.

1365514469
03:38:00.453 --> 03:38:01.104
>> Minister.

2266494047
03:38:01.105 --> 03:38:05.250
>> I'd like to thank
what was a really useful

3616852629
03:38:05.251 --> 03:38:07.694
point and observation, first of all,

3878921976
03:38:07.695 --> 03:38:10.303
to support the work going
on with his constituency,

2306904082
03:38:10.304 --> 03:38:12.461
with an elaborate of doing an amazing job,

3132427774
03:38:12.462 --> 03:38:15.923
and I think they might have recently
received some funding for that,

3495210049
03:38:15.924 --> 03:38:19.486
which is a part of a programme really
trying to change the initiative,

1402138615
03:38:19.487 --> 03:38:20.891
how we look after veterans.

1622254042
03:38:20.892 --> 03:38:24.354
And then to your second point, I'm
a firm believer that veterans do,

3980645547
03:38:24.355 --> 03:38:25.809
when they join the military,

302839834
03:38:25.810 --> 03:38:29.018
they contribute to their most
important function of government,

3830565542
03:38:29.019 --> 03:38:31.377
which is to protect our
people and our nation.

4145020848
03:38:31.378 --> 03:38:34.740
And then when they leave, they go
on to contribute to the economy,

2253337745
03:38:34.741 --> 03:38:37.197
because actually a large
percentage of veterans,

1136723992
03:38:37.198 --> 03:38:40.459
when they leave the military, go
on to thrive across all sectors

3358553299
03:38:40.460 --> 03:38:42.967
of civilian society
and deliver above and beyond.

3827485067
03:38:42.968 --> 03:38:45.977
There are that need help
and there are smaller percentages,

1142909695
03:38:45.978 --> 03:38:46.931
need lots of help.

1364229400
03:38:46.932 --> 03:38:48.889
And that's what we've got to focus on.

2377619238
03:38:48.890 --> 03:38:50.997
That's what valour is really there to do.

567808439
03:38:50.998 --> 03:38:53.206
And I'm sure over
the next couple of years,

2562277510
03:38:53.207 --> 03:38:55.964
it will absolutely deliver
and readjust our mechanisms

3799795758
03:38:55.965 --> 03:38:58.120
for looking after veterans across society.

804284456
03:38:58.121 --> 03:39:01.030
So the service justice system
looks at amendments 57, 59,

1992703818
03:39:01.031 --> 03:39:03.691
66 and 67 relate to the point
raised by the Director

913195888
03:39:03.692 --> 03:39:06.148
of Service Prosecutions
at the Select Committee.

3247306592
03:39:06.149 --> 03:39:08.807
They ensure service protection
orders can be made by

2862237052
03:39:08.808 --> 03:39:11.316
a service court in relation
to a service offence,

2393322044
03:39:11.317 --> 03:39:13.575
even if the person has
left the Armed Forces

2933280761
03:39:13.576 --> 03:39:15.582
amendments 80 and 84 make provision for

1137879980
03:39:15.583 --> 03:39:17.988
the Post-service management
of Service stalking

1904427648
03:39:17.989 --> 03:39:19.943
protection orders in Northern Ireland.

2355055602
03:39:19.944 --> 03:39:22.952
They ensure that such orders
can be effectively recognised,

2990708180
03:39:22.953 --> 03:39:25.158
enforced once
an individual leaves service.

2628959778
03:39:25.159 --> 03:39:28.718
Amendment 30 provides for service
restraining orders to be enforceable

1833457030
03:39:28.719 --> 03:39:31.476
as equivalent orders in
Scotland and Northern Ireland.

3540646431
03:39:31.477 --> 03:39:32.779
In certain circumstances.

3001882328
03:39:32.780 --> 03:39:35.338
New clause four introduces
a new power for service

3568391491
03:39:35.339 --> 03:39:37.696
courts to make a service
image deletion order.

3532009606
03:39:37.697 --> 03:39:40.957
The new deletion order will enable
the service courts to require

2858744064
03:39:40.958 --> 03:39:43.717
offenders to delete and destroy
any images or films in

84769551
03:39:43.718 --> 03:39:47.277
their possession or control that are
connected with specific offences,

2415495445
03:39:47.278 --> 03:39:49.686
and which depict a person
in an intimate state.

7206603
03:39:49.687 --> 03:39:52.747
Amendment 31 removes
the limitation of the powers to search

2194647183
03:39:52.748 --> 03:39:55.103
and seize electronically
tracked stolen goods,

756906297
03:39:55.104 --> 03:39:57.401
without a warrant being applicable to

221419304
03:39:57.402 --> 03:39:59.205
relevant residential premises only,

927782550
03:39:59.206 --> 03:40:02.910
and instead applies the broader
concept of relevant premises.

4090943849
03:40:02.911 --> 03:40:04.415
This is any premise premises,

226120467
03:40:04.995 --> 03:40:07.201
premises occupied
or controlled by a person

1467794173
03:40:07.202 --> 03:40:10.612
subject to service law or a civilian
subject to service discipline,

2003537681
03:40:10.613 --> 03:40:13.070
but are not necessarily
occupied as a residence.

392513579
03:40:13.071 --> 03:40:16.853
It is worth noting that across both
sides of the House, since 2021,

2725375686
03:40:16.854 --> 03:40:20.151
we have created the Defence
Serious Crime Command.

3408708607
03:40:20.152 --> 03:40:23.053
We've created a witness care
unit when we move forward

1395842482
03:40:23.054 --> 03:40:25.811
with Tri-service complaint
system and putting in place

4155038771
03:40:25.996 --> 03:40:28.604
the Violence Against Women
Task Girls Task Force to

3031708464
03:40:28.956 --> 03:40:31.462
improve the standards
and culture within defence.

122931346
03:40:32.000 --> 03:40:33.655
Turning to amendments 33 and 34,

3750679800
03:40:33.656 --> 03:40:38.358
which make small but very
important changes to clause 25.

1479414477
03:40:38.359 --> 03:40:41.569
Clause 25 will require the Secretary
of State to issue guidance

1955386768
03:40:41.570 --> 03:40:44.730
to help a victim reach a view on
their preferred jurisdiction.

2729821145
03:40:44.731 --> 03:40:47.136
The Select Committee
highlighted the importance

498054581
03:40:47.137 --> 03:40:48.790
of victims receiving information

1996638155
03:40:48.791 --> 03:40:52.400
in an objective and impartial way
to help them give an informed view.

655302158
03:40:52.401 --> 03:40:56.106
The government recognises that need
and amendment 33 reflects that.

3481737712
03:40:56.107 --> 03:40:58.263
This amendment also ensures that the needs

1185109029
03:40:58.264 --> 03:41:00.460
of the victims and the circumstances

3332025101
03:41:00.461 --> 03:41:03.921
of the events are taken into account
and providing that information,

231951720
03:41:03.922 --> 03:41:06.981
and that the appropriate record
is kept of that information.

2536731125
03:41:06.982 --> 03:41:08.938
Amendment 34 adds the Lord advocate to

3320603422
03:41:08.939 --> 03:41:11.045
the list of consultees which ensures that

3750583125
03:41:11.046 --> 03:41:13.303
she is consulted when
the Secretary of State

1122428307
03:41:13.304 --> 03:41:16.305
issues or revises the new guidance.

3535132578
03:41:16.306 --> 03:41:19.207
Amendment 37 extends
the provision in clause 29,

1852558534
03:41:19.208 --> 03:41:21.514
which requires a disclosure
of spent cautions

2116447614
03:41:21.515 --> 03:41:24.152
for the purpose of administrative action.

2255883374
03:41:24.153 --> 03:41:27.213
Cautions are not issued in
Scotland as in England and Wales.

663914636
03:41:27.214 --> 03:41:30.875
This amendment means that clause 29
will now apply to spent alternatives

898953423
03:41:30.876 --> 03:41:37.397
to prosecution issued under
the Scottish justice system.

2523595411
03:41:37.398 --> 03:41:39.605
Moving on to reserves
amendments 38 and 39.

921679719
03:41:40.000 --> 03:41:43.350
Remove the 18 year recall
liability for other ranks.

4115512715
03:41:43.351 --> 03:41:47.505
This is simplifying
and unifying the liability

1705466685
03:41:47.506 --> 03:41:48.961
for all service to 65 years.

1397172404
03:41:48.962 --> 03:41:50.802
This change is significant.

1544995349
03:41:50.803 --> 03:41:52.508
It aligns with our NATO partners.

2973739261
03:41:52.509 --> 03:41:55.065
Germany and Finland both
have similar liabilities,

2883323629
03:41:55.284 --> 03:41:58.960
while France has also just announced
a similar increase to age 70.

501875205
03:41:58.961 --> 03:42:02.960
Aligning policy with NATO partners
ensures effective cooperation.

2732399807
03:42:02.961 --> 03:42:05.217
It strengthens our
collective defence and it

1710096288
03:42:05.218 --> 03:42:08.705
improves joint response to shared threats.

679932850
03:42:08.706 --> 03:42:11.612
Further simplifying the reserve
liability is fundamental.

4085832428
03:42:11.613 --> 03:42:14.272
It enables us to create
a clear and modern framework

4014471060
03:42:14.273 --> 03:42:17.202
that is easier to administer,
easier to explain,

1088560441
03:42:17.203 --> 03:42:20.204
and will enable the MoD to
plan more effectively for

506426697
03:42:21.000 --> 03:42:23.304
workforce requirements
and defence readiness.

3011960526
03:42:23.305 --> 03:42:25.860
These amendments also ensure
greater compatibility

2479137835
03:42:25.861 --> 03:42:28.186
with a new workforce
model or zigzag careers,

3949544363
03:42:28.187 --> 03:42:31.258
as we're calling it, provided
for by clause 31 of this bill.

3451681541
03:42:31.259 --> 03:42:34.400
We want to encourage
a much more flexible working

1510178652
03:42:34.401 --> 03:42:36.405
approach that mirrors civilian society,

2693160994
03:42:37.000 --> 03:42:39.256
allows people's careers
to be more flexible,

1470981201
03:42:39.257 --> 03:42:41.714
but it is difficult
and complicated to calculate

2632565075
03:42:41.715 --> 03:42:44.172
exactly when the 18 year
liability should start.

65399185
03:42:44.173 --> 03:42:47.182
For people who might move between
the regulars and reserves

550938243
03:42:47.183 --> 03:42:49.389
and potentially back
again, we need assist.

828506599
03:42:51.003 --> 03:42:51.454
We will.

131840898
03:42:51.455 --> 03:42:53.762
>> I thank the Minister
for his intervention.

3481270223
03:42:53.763 --> 03:42:56.824
I just wanted to bring up
the topic of the strategic reserve

4041304948
03:42:56.825 --> 03:42:59.181
and welcome the introduction
within this bill,

3383475991
03:42:59.182 --> 03:43:02.745
but I just want to clarify how
the strategic reserve will be paid for.

4248960247
03:43:02.746 --> 03:43:04.904
Will it be paid for by a separate funding,

1475314048
03:43:04.905 --> 03:43:06.461
or will it come from the money

2866049720
03:43:06.462 --> 03:43:09.823
already allocated to pay for
the active reserve in the MoD Budget?

2101830882
03:43:09.824 --> 03:43:10.175
>> Mr.

47086048
03:43:10.176 --> 03:43:10.677
>> Thank.

2994555719
03:43:11.000 --> 03:43:11.954
>> So, as the hon.

11231153
03:43:11.955 --> 03:43:13.911
Member will know, there is a multitude

1423280372
03:43:13.912 --> 03:43:15.767
of different reserves in the system,

3725226828
03:43:15.768 --> 03:43:18.673
different liabilities, different
pay, different pensions.

2940742550
03:43:18.674 --> 03:43:19.074
Indeed.

2092643562
03:43:19.075 --> 03:43:22.536
I've often described it as a sort
of spaghetti junction of different

2372549720
03:43:22.537 --> 03:43:25.648
policies layered on top of each
other over the last 60 years.

865631238
03:43:25.649 --> 03:43:28.459
This is the first move to
simplify that and to simplify

2856096012
03:43:28.460 --> 03:43:31.067
the funding mechanisms
and recall processes for it.

2788724654
03:43:31.068 --> 03:43:34.580
So by removing the 18 year liability,
we simplify it around 65 years,

3465486292
03:43:34.581 --> 03:43:36.988
which creates our ability
to zigzag those roles

1037318445
03:43:36.989 --> 03:43:39.045
within the military where you can leave,

3710759818
03:43:39.046 --> 03:43:42.304
rejoin and leave again, depending
on your personal circumstances

3793886587
03:43:42.305 --> 03:43:44.962
and the liability available
within the armed forces.

677138760
03:43:44.963 --> 03:43:46.519
>> On that point, will my hon.

3061587948
03:43:46.520 --> 03:43:46.920
Friend.

3262870424
03:43:46.921 --> 03:43:47.473
>> I will.

1885016461
03:43:47.474 --> 03:43:50.702
>> Thank my hon.

690458366
03:43:50.703 --> 03:43:52.508
Friend for giving way this weekend.

3550488339
03:43:55.499 --> 03:43:57.906
just over two I received
my recall notification

3349685751
03:43:57.907 --> 03:44:01.664
just over two years after
leaving the military,

3872521561
03:44:01.665 --> 03:44:06.408
and I managed to update
the details that were kept within it.

3747082673
03:44:06.409 --> 03:44:10.103
At the same time as I've
been presented with

549869331
03:44:14.150 --> 03:44:16.357
nearly 60 pages worth
of forms to complete,

2520012454
03:44:16.358 --> 03:44:24.006
just to move into reserve or to take
on a reserve service commitment.

2570175610
03:44:24.007 --> 03:44:24.860
So would my hon.

3367461450
03:44:24.861 --> 03:44:27.659
Friend agree with me that
there is some way to go,

235773789
03:44:27.660 --> 03:44:30.761
and that this amendment
perhaps should speak

1230877476
03:44:30.762 --> 03:44:34.160
of reserve movement between reserve
forces and regular forces,

2301919536
03:44:34.161 --> 03:44:38.309
rather than the other way round.

4085542066
03:44:38.310 --> 03:44:39.112
>> Exactly one.

1944460831
03:44:39.113 --> 03:44:41.810
One of the reasons why
creating this amendment

797272898
03:44:41.811 --> 03:44:44.704
and other provisions within the bill.

1791623773
03:44:44.705 --> 03:44:47.811
In the past, you had to leave
the regular forces to join

2409196864
03:44:47.812 --> 03:44:51.022
the reserves and leave the reserves
to join the regular forces.

1454925541
03:44:51.023 --> 03:44:53.581
We want to create a seamless
transition which will

1631028453
03:44:53.582 --> 03:44:56.251
reduce the 60 pages of
administrative burden that

3918081010
03:44:56.252 --> 03:44:59.112
you've had to fill in to
a much more seamless transition

822947225
03:44:59.113 --> 03:45:00.967
between regular and reserve service,

1057229081
03:45:00.968 --> 03:45:03.224
actually mirroring some
of the other nations

3265266410
03:45:03.225 --> 03:45:05.332
across the world that do that quite well.

3727438061
03:45:05.333 --> 03:45:08.746
We the reality is we need a system
that is fair, that is equitable,

3328679614
03:45:08.747 --> 03:45:10.802
and does not discriminate against anyone

8460708
03:45:10.803 --> 03:45:12.808
who wishes to exercise the flexibility.

1899465236
03:45:12.809 --> 03:45:15.717
It is also worth noting in
this geostrategic environment,

968456025
03:45:15.718 --> 03:45:17.273
what this will provide the UK.

348646413
03:45:17.274 --> 03:45:19.030
It will likely take us from 95000,

3773382545
03:45:19.031 --> 03:45:21.500
the strategic reserve
that could be mobilised

238302321
03:45:21.501 --> 03:45:23.459
up to 150 000 over the next ten years,

1577424383
03:45:25.004 --> 03:45:26.859
which is a significant step forward.

1406707957
03:45:26.860 --> 03:45:30.120
All other government amendments
that have been tabled in my name

3280231320
03:45:30.121 --> 03:45:33.330
are either consequential to
the amendments I have just covered,

3082209170
03:45:33.331 --> 03:45:34.735
or are minor and technical,

2172133974
03:45:34.736 --> 03:45:37.043
that simply improve
the drafting of the bill.

497315853
03:45:37.044 --> 03:45:39.150
I will now turn to opposition amendments.

2215798253
03:45:39.151 --> 03:45:42.412
I will now address the amendments
in groups two, three and four.

4027450881
03:45:42.413 --> 03:45:44.771
Now, I am aware that
the Minister for veterans

945556462
03:45:44.772 --> 03:45:46.979
and people recently met
with the right hon.

4220535971
03:45:46.980 --> 03:45:49.287
Member for Rayleigh
and Wickford and the hon.

4150357490
03:45:49.288 --> 03:45:51.695
Member for Solihull West
and Shirley to discuss

2051351746
03:45:51.696 --> 03:45:54.002
the concerns behind some
of these amendments.

358554757
03:45:54.003 --> 03:45:56.059
We continue to work across government on

14696249
03:45:56.060 --> 03:45:57.966
the best way to address these issues.

3204996326
03:45:57.967 --> 03:46:00.977
In practice, the better route
is not a rigid statutory fix,

2230521783
03:46:00.978 --> 03:46:03.633
but practical improvements
through existing systems.

646678923
03:46:03.634 --> 03:46:06.190
The Covenant Legal Duty
statutory guidance already

2905406293
03:46:06.191 --> 03:46:08.246
gives public bodies a flexible framework

3343034644
03:46:08.247 --> 03:46:10.553
to take account for
the particular challenges

3678972296
03:46:10.554 --> 03:46:12.560
service families face when on the move.

42743072
03:46:12.561 --> 03:46:15.168
Let me be clear considering
the statutory guidance,

3652578937
03:46:15.169 --> 03:46:17.024
supporting the duty is not optional.

2160685781
03:46:17.025 --> 03:46:20.036
Once it is in force, public
bodies subject to the duty must

2256042745
03:46:20.037 --> 03:46:22.807
have regard to it in their
decision making, policy.

2709320481
03:46:22.808 --> 03:46:26.006
Sorry decision making
and their policy development.

1065867087
03:46:26.007 --> 03:46:28.710
Special education needs
adopting and fostering

2105474160
03:46:28.711 --> 03:46:30.365
an NHS continuity are important,

3554488637
03:46:30.366 --> 03:46:32.822
exceptionally important
issues, but they are not

1786315634
03:46:32.823 --> 03:46:34.927
well addressed through rigid legislation.

1700471665
03:46:34.928 --> 03:46:38.036
The systems are different,
the legal frameworks are different

1642701400
03:46:38.037 --> 03:46:41.395
and the decisions involved often
depend on professional judgement.

3797952811
03:46:41.396 --> 03:46:44.605
Safeguarding or clinical need
a blanket duty to transfer plans,

1553789192
03:46:44.606 --> 03:46:47.812
arrangements or treatment
automatically could create confusion.

2622362661
03:46:47.813 --> 03:46:50.419
Cut across devolved
responsibilities in some cases.

1676383802
03:46:50.420 --> 03:46:52.074
DeLay the support families need.

2433821865
03:46:52.075 --> 03:46:56.167
Our focus instead is on proving
continuity and delivery so service

1659342779
03:46:56.168 --> 03:47:00.215
families get better support
without unintended consequences.

680720494
03:47:00.216 --> 03:47:02.472
Turning to amendment 88,
which would require

2446145650
03:47:02.473 --> 03:47:05.030
the Secretary of State to
review current practices

1965364392
03:47:05.031 --> 03:47:07.906
for communicating with
former service personnel

727075480
03:47:07.907 --> 03:47:10.262
about their armed forces
pension entitlements.

3732075988
03:47:10.263 --> 03:47:13.121
The MoD maintains a comprehensive
and on going programme

2591145295
03:47:13.122 --> 03:47:15.979
of communication with both
serving and former personnel,

466753275
03:47:15.980 --> 03:47:17.833
supported by established governance,

3702391165
03:47:17.834 --> 03:47:20.640
regular data analysis
and targeted engagement activity.

1684918648
03:47:20.641 --> 03:47:23.198
The department already
monitors take up and traces

3825475047
03:47:23.199 --> 03:47:25.153
unclaimed entitlements 60 working days

895754355
03:47:25.154 --> 03:47:28.313
after pension due date where
a positive address is identified,

815055032
03:47:28.314 --> 03:47:29.666
individuals are contacted.

2883188210
03:47:29.667 --> 03:47:31.824
This approach has resulted in over ten 000

1377836336
03:47:32.006 --> 03:47:33.860
pensions being brought into payment.

413901678
03:47:33.861 --> 03:47:36.717
Mandating further statutory
assessment would add process

3342895427
03:47:36.718 --> 03:47:39.222
without delivering meaningful
additional insight.

853568504
03:47:39.223 --> 03:47:41.580
Diverting resource from
the delivery at a time

1977428135
03:47:41.581 --> 03:47:43.486
when focus is rightly on implementing

714400531
03:47:43.487 --> 03:47:47.058
pension remedies and strengthening
frontline pension support,

244346856
03:47:48.008 --> 03:47:50.666
amendment 89 would require
the Secretary of State to

3528317115
03:47:50.667 --> 03:47:53.072
review current practices
regarding the transfer

2461871860
03:47:53.073 --> 03:47:55.278
of armed Forces Personnel's
medical records

4270560513
03:47:55.279 --> 03:47:57.435
upon their transfer to the Reserve Forces.

1551725711
03:47:57.436 --> 03:47:59.443
I would like to reassure the House that

3576702024
03:47:59.444 --> 03:48:01.198
no transfer of military healthcare

2486818643
03:48:01.199 --> 03:48:04.859
records is needed when transferring
from the regular to reserve service,

234763663
03:48:04.860 --> 03:48:07.868
because defence continues to
hold and manage the healthcare

2634869973
03:48:07.869 --> 03:48:10.576
records for reservists in
the same electronic system,

2582992270
03:48:10.577 --> 03:48:13.486
which will also be simplified
with some of the amendments

121697219
03:48:13.487 --> 03:48:15.643
I mentioned earlier to the reserve forces.

650587822
03:48:15.644 --> 03:48:17.852
It is worth noting that
we send out 425,000

1605818226
03:48:18.008 --> 03:48:21.605
quarterly digests to those receiving
pensions across the system.

1317754899
03:48:21.606 --> 03:48:24.414
Amendment 90 seeks to make
sure that all investigations

3869935262
03:48:24.415 --> 03:48:26.408
and prosecutions of service persons

1491698439
03:48:26.409 --> 03:48:29.114
for sexual offences and domestic abuse in

4060533100
03:48:29.115 --> 03:48:31.523
the UK take place in
a criminal justice system.

2869869082
03:48:31.524 --> 03:48:34.460
Since the prosecutor's protocols
were published in 2023,

283356617
03:48:34.461 --> 03:48:36.819
there have been no cases
where a victim wanted

2521800722
03:48:36.820 --> 03:48:38.725
trial in the criminal justice system,

1923637430
03:48:38.726 --> 03:48:42.810
but the case was instead prosecuted
in the service justice system.

3433846667
03:48:42.811 --> 03:48:46.713
The amendment would, however,
override the victim's preference.

3808842894
03:48:46.714 --> 03:48:47.767
I'll say that again.

4217170284
03:48:48.005 --> 03:48:49.508
The amendment would, however,

647178011
03:48:49.509 --> 03:48:52.863
override the victim's
preference in case in cases

3865771115
03:48:52.864 --> 03:48:55.170
where they prefer
the service justice system.

3434527823
03:48:55.171 --> 03:48:57.658
This risks increasing
the victim withdrawal

2457620660
03:48:57.659 --> 03:48:59.663
rate in civilian police investigations,

633181479
03:48:59.664 --> 03:49:02.666
which for adult rape flag
cases in 2024 was 59%.

92941932
03:49:02.667 --> 03:49:06.562
The withdrawal rate for the Defence
Serious Crime Command was 24%.

2302783419
03:49:06.563 --> 03:49:09.311
The amendment could furthermore lead to

49892865
03:49:09.312 --> 03:49:11.659
the loss of erosion of the golden hour,

1185725960
03:49:11.660 --> 03:49:13.564
evidence and safeguarding of victims,

1813238059
03:49:13.565 --> 03:49:16.526
as there is no duty on civilian
police to accept the case,

1243093597
03:49:16.527 --> 03:49:18.935
a case by case approach
that takes into account

2922345469
03:49:18.936 --> 03:49:20.692
the views of the victim is better.

2913334528
03:49:20.693 --> 03:49:24.608
Clause 25 therefore strengthens
the provision of information

2193813650
03:49:24.609 --> 03:49:27.416
to victims when asked for
their preferred jurisdiction.

19665840
03:49:27.417 --> 03:49:30.325
This will help prosecutors
take into account the victim's

1343829107
03:49:30.326 --> 03:49:33.859
view when making
a decision on jurisdiction.

2077828815
03:49:33.860 --> 03:49:36.960
Amendment five would
extend eligibility to sit

2160323686
03:49:36.961 --> 03:49:39.268
on a court martial board
to retired officers.

2902190784
03:49:39.269 --> 03:49:42.627
However, the government does not
consider the amendment necessary,

1126206680
03:49:42.628 --> 03:49:44.984
nor would it improve
the current arrangements.

2547094246
03:49:44.985 --> 03:49:47.743
First, there is no shortage
of eligible board members.

3756529629
03:49:47.744 --> 03:49:50.001
The court martial already
draws from a broad

1759855838
03:49:50.002 --> 03:49:52.157
and sufficient pool of eligible personnel.

3202069038
03:49:52.158 --> 03:49:56.214
In 2025, for example, 447 service
personnel were sworn for 263 trials

2287988793
03:49:56.215 --> 03:49:59.073
and there has been no difficulty
in constituting boards.

4125792339
03:49:59.074 --> 03:50:01.631
Secondly, it is important
that board members bring

2752666705
03:50:01.632 --> 03:50:03.786
current knowledge and practical experience

243165396
03:50:03.787 --> 03:50:07.446
of the latest single service policies,
procedures, values and standards.

3988443264
03:50:07.447 --> 03:50:10.725
An individual has left service
even relatively recently,

3126918539
03:50:10.726 --> 03:50:12.882
may no longer be sufficiently connected to

398137299
03:50:12.883 --> 03:50:14.839
the pace of change across the service.

875725175
03:50:14.840 --> 03:50:16.995
Now, I recognise the valuable contribution

320193575
03:50:16.996 --> 03:50:18.600
that veterans continue to make,

1215526854
03:50:18.601 --> 03:50:21.410
but service in a court martial
board is not appropriate

388984812
03:50:21.411 --> 03:50:23.467
and means of drawing on that experience.

691831045
03:50:23.468 --> 03:50:26.829
It is also worth noting when we are
court Martialling higher rank.

46885091
03:50:26.830 --> 03:50:30.191
There are over 331 fun stars in
the British military and therefore

430617863
03:50:30.192 --> 03:50:32.699
ample opportunity to sit
on court martial boards.

51375627
03:50:32.700 --> 03:50:34.607
I will now turn to amendment one one,

1967116295
03:50:34.608 --> 03:50:37.465
which would ensure that persons
undertake vital civilian

4259992078
03:50:37.466 --> 03:50:39.674
work to be exempt from
a recall order under

3321198162
03:50:39.675 --> 03:50:41.782
new section 69 of the Reserve Forces Act,

681965908
03:50:41.783 --> 03:50:43.940
1996, section 73 of the Reserve Forces Act

1232537792
03:50:45.005 --> 03:50:46.909
already provides powers of exemption.

275256827
03:50:46.910 --> 03:50:49.015
To recall, this existing provision allows

954980262
03:50:49.016 --> 03:50:51.021
the Defence Council to, by regulations,

534199311
03:50:51.022 --> 03:50:54.210
exempt individuals from
or relax recall liability.

3097014368
03:50:54.211 --> 03:50:57.570
In total, amendment six aims to
increase the readiness requirement

3199901277
03:50:57.571 --> 03:51:01.065
for reservists in Army Reserve
Group A from 180 days to 90 days.

3684807343
03:51:01.066 --> 03:51:03.525
I would like to reassure
the House that all Army

1634979587
03:51:03.526 --> 03:51:05.882
readiness levels are
subject to annual review.

2406271930
03:51:05.883 --> 03:51:08.891
To effectively fulfil its
obligations, the Army must review

272475074
03:51:08.892 --> 03:51:12.001
and adjust readiness levels
across all elements of its force,

2475527964
03:51:12.002 --> 03:51:14.960
responding to evolving demands
of the nation is essential.

652679267
03:51:14.961 --> 03:51:17.918
The defence maintains
the necessary flexibility to respond

2050468018
03:51:17.919 --> 03:51:20.575
swiftly and appropriately
to changing threat levels.

728392160
03:51:20.576 --> 03:51:23.031
Embedding such provisions
in primary legislation

3536831068
03:51:23.032 --> 03:51:24.635
would impose rigid constraints,

3134602642
03:51:24.636 --> 03:51:27.343
creating an obstacle rather
than a suitable mechanism

3836707304
03:51:27.344 --> 03:51:29.549
for setting and reviewing
readiness levels.

1520983011
03:51:29.550 --> 03:51:35.849
Hopefully, I have given the necessary
assurances and would >> Mr.

2754523314
03:51:35.850 --> 03:51:38.005
Martin, ask these amendments be withdrawn.

3936850236
03:51:38.006 --> 03:51:38.357
>> Mr.

1004843667
03:51:38.358 --> 03:51:40.564
Martin, are you hoping
to contribute today?

1950420425
03:51:40.565 --> 03:51:42.873
Do we just have
the pleasure of your company?

50166984
03:51:42.874 --> 03:51:43.474
Marvellous.

610060144
03:51:44.005 --> 03:51:45.559
I'll call the shadow Minister.

287689818
03:51:45.560 --> 03:51:46.311
Mark Francois.

885233891
03:51:46.312 --> 03:51:50.863
>> Thank you very much, Madam Chairman.

3498098851
03:51:50.864 --> 03:51:51.617
I beg to move.

1527848414
03:51:53.008 --> 03:51:53.608
Amendments.

3680775766
03:51:53.609 --> 03:51:57.265
One, two, three, four, five
and six and new clauses one,

954493472
03:51:57.266 --> 03:52:01.224
two, three and six in my
name and that of my hon.

845667605
03:52:01.225 --> 03:52:01.675
Friends.

1448509249
03:52:01.676 --> 03:52:03.885
I should like to say
a little about each of

3676048309
03:52:03.886 --> 03:52:07.062
these amendments and new clauses in turn,

1027867908
03:52:07.063 --> 03:52:11.422
but also to refer to new clause five
in the name of my right and my hon.

3123438591
03:52:11.423 --> 03:52:15.159
Friend from Huntingdon, and say at
least a little about the multiplicity

1520370503
03:52:15.160 --> 03:52:19.342
of government amendments that have
just been tabled and in particular,

3045774077
03:52:21.010 --> 03:52:23.767
Government amendment 54 on
the proposed Crown immunity

2090452865
03:52:24.008 --> 03:52:26.014
for the Defence Housing Service by Ali.

3011570544
03:52:26.015 --> 03:52:29.721
Madam chairman, I propose to speak
to the amendments first and then

3104040469
03:52:29.722 --> 03:52:33.413
to refer to the new clauses
a little bit later on in the debate,

1647096599
03:52:33.414 --> 03:52:37.115
so as not to try the patience of the House

3749665735
03:52:37.116 --> 03:52:39.405
with an inordinately long speech.

2900736758
03:52:39.406 --> 03:52:44.113
Turning to the Bill itself,
I hope that we have collectively

1101380767
03:52:44.114 --> 03:52:46.321
done the House
and indeed the Armed Forces,

2557913992
03:52:46.322 --> 03:52:49.614
a service in our scrutiny
of the Bill so far

3072436645
03:52:49.615 --> 03:52:53.562
is the Armed Forces Bill Select Committee,

3500651032
03:52:53.563 --> 03:52:54.918
most of whom are here now.

1151938242
03:52:54.919 --> 03:52:57.978
We held seven oral evidence
sessions on the Bill's contests,

278765393
03:52:57.979 --> 03:53:01.369
as well as a fact finding
visit to the Defence Serious

3621859551
03:53:01.370 --> 03:53:05.361
Crime Command in Fareham and to
defence housing sites at Emsworth,

2303619332
03:53:05.362 --> 03:53:07.913
near His Majesty's Naval Base, Portsmouth.

3000595824
03:53:07.914 --> 03:53:11.085
As a committee, we also
received 47 pieces of written

698836265
03:53:11.086 --> 03:53:15.297
evidence and heard in
total from 42 witnesses.

454184361
03:53:15.298 --> 03:53:19.018
Having held these evidence
sessions, we then went through

1438276313
03:53:19.019 --> 03:53:21.418
a detailed process of
line by line scrutiny of

3399289465
03:53:21.419 --> 03:53:24.679
the Bill itself and produced our
subsequent report to the House,

776212748
03:53:24.680 --> 03:53:28.815
which was published on the 29th of April.

721343331
03:53:28.816 --> 03:53:34.508
So the bill has already had quite
a detailed amount of scrutiny,

1861070670
03:53:34.509 --> 03:53:38.212
but it's quite right that a measure
of this importance is now being

3898228273
03:53:38.213 --> 03:53:42.718
debated in its Committee stage,
on the floor of the House.

3492654584
03:53:42.719 --> 03:53:48.016
And again, I reiterate my
disappointment that reform

4072354570
03:53:48.017 --> 03:53:50.615
don't regard these
proceedings as important.

4033848849
03:53:50.616 --> 03:53:55.770
I'm sure the rest of us do.

589930890
03:53:55.771 --> 03:53:56.924
That's why we're here.

2298321236
03:53:56.925 --> 03:53:57.475
Certainly.

4254140329
03:53:58.972 --> 03:53:59.775
>> The the hon.

3162864487
03:53:59.776 --> 03:54:00.377
Member for.

1273697393
03:54:00.378 --> 03:54:05.215
Rayleigh and Wickford
for for for giving way.

1310708173
03:54:05.216 --> 03:54:09.469
I would also like to reiterate
the fact that there aren't any members

3090725070
03:54:11.013 --> 03:54:17.165
here from the the party led by
the Member for Clacton in particular,

3095335743
03:54:17.166 --> 03:54:19.614
because so many of the local authorities

611377884
03:54:19.615 --> 03:54:21.519
that are responsible for implementing

4194346715
03:54:22.012 --> 03:54:28.909
the Armed Forces Covenant are
led by that particular party.

3080770390
03:54:28.910 --> 03:54:32.220
So it is even more
grossly incompetent that

1974019586
03:54:32.221 --> 03:54:34.329
they are not here to listen and to learn.

2272692967
03:54:34.330 --> 03:54:36.337
>> Can I reiterate the comments made by

2135755972
03:54:36.338 --> 03:54:38.819
the Chairman of Ways and Means earlier,

1158728645
03:54:38.820 --> 03:54:42.613
that it is not in scope
of this Bill, that there.

217233057
03:54:42.614 --> 03:54:43.617
Point that the hon.

1241802364
03:54:43.618 --> 03:54:45.674
Lady has raised, and indeed others have.

408606622
03:54:45.675 --> 03:54:48.070
So perhaps it would be
best if we moved on.

3222704418
03:54:48.071 --> 03:54:51.816
>> Mark Francois thank
you, Madam Chairman.

3506488111
03:54:51.817 --> 03:54:54.116
I won't cut across your ruling, but I do

156014830
03:54:54.117 --> 03:54:59.971
nevertheless wholly agree with the hon.

2403930392
03:54:59.972 --> 03:55:00.272
Lady.

2345687746
03:55:00.273 --> 03:55:02.567
Can I then say, during the process of

2271031590
03:55:02.568 --> 03:55:04.516
the Bill so far we and His Majesty's

4176252307
03:55:04.517 --> 03:55:08.064
opposition have sought to act as
critical friends to the Bill,

2548574852
03:55:08.065 --> 03:55:10.320
agreeing the government
with the government,

3063128520
03:55:10.321 --> 03:55:13.431
where we think they've done
the right thing and probing them,

3868244295
03:55:13.432 --> 03:55:16.291
where we think that perhaps
they could have done better.

703283588
03:55:16.292 --> 03:55:18.764
The government has now tabled some 81

3228046424
03:55:18.765 --> 03:55:21.308
new clauses and amendments in toto.

4125729431
03:55:21.309 --> 03:55:23.165
Many of these, as the Minister said,

3136602242
03:55:23.166 --> 03:55:26.671
are relatively minor or technical
drafting improvements,

897044041
03:55:26.672 --> 03:55:28.820
but some of them are quite substantial,

972230505
03:55:28.821 --> 03:55:32.378
in particular relating to
the proposed new defence

3235036423
03:55:32.379 --> 03:55:34.785
Housing service and
the service justice system.

395491157
03:55:34.786 --> 03:55:37.244
I'd like to ask the Minister
a specific question

7737105
03:55:37.245 --> 03:55:40.815
about the government's
proposed amendment 54,

2802690449
03:55:40.816 --> 03:55:45.416
the essence of which is that where
property held by the Defence Housing

1014002821
03:55:45.417 --> 03:55:49.065
Service is to be treated as property
held on behalf of the Crown,

677718707
03:55:49.066 --> 03:55:52.666
the Defence Housing Service
should have the same immunities,

645909477
03:55:52.667 --> 03:55:57.334
privileges and exemptions in respect
of holding that property as would

102025949
03:55:57.335 --> 03:56:00.397
apply if it were property held
by or on behalf of the Crown.

1783163290
03:56:00.398 --> 03:56:03.168
It would be helpful if
the Minister could explain

3660790858
03:56:03.169 --> 03:56:06.968
to the House exactly what
that means in practice,

3137464244
03:56:06.969 --> 03:56:11.420
specifically if this
amendment is to grant Crown

4031954088
03:56:11.421 --> 03:56:13.476
immunity to the Defence Housing Service,

3600629460
03:56:13.477 --> 03:56:15.232
which is what the wording implies,

1240351991
03:56:15.233 --> 03:56:18.324
how would that affect
the ability of armed forces

2516410162
03:56:19.018 --> 03:56:23.067
families to raise complaints about
the standards of their accommodation?

3350686184
03:56:23.068 --> 03:56:27.118
The Minister will recall we spent
a lot of time in committee debating

2321352501
03:56:27.119 --> 03:56:30.473
