which I hope the House would accept.

3272937766
04:07:44.454 --> 04:07:47.215
It is a very important matter,
but he's hoping to join

2900353295
04:07:47.216 --> 04:07:50.182
us later in the debate when
he's attended to that,

2966602233
04:07:50.183 --> 04:07:51.636
given his medical expertise.

2424817238
04:07:51.637 --> 04:07:54.626
He pressed this point with
the Minister for veterans at

3952529081
04:07:54.627 --> 04:07:58.089
People at the same meeting
I've already referred to.

4216862393
04:07:58.090 --> 04:08:02.439
And sadly, again, we received an equally

3335323818
04:08:02.440 --> 04:08:04.144
uninspiring reply for the record,

2900613954
04:08:04.145 --> 04:08:06.891
given that The King's Speech also presaged

1721189553
04:08:06.892 --> 04:08:10.683
new legislation on NHS organisation,

4020542166
04:08:10.684 --> 04:08:14.238
we sought to suggest that one way
to proceed might be to include

2239739931
04:08:14.239 --> 04:08:17.452
an amendment in that bill
rather than in this one.

785919877
04:08:17.453 --> 04:08:22.351
So, in other words, to put that medical
issue in a bill being introduced

3563840753
04:08:22.352 --> 04:08:26.934
by Ministers from the Department
of Health and Social Care.

3276914062
04:08:26.935 --> 04:08:31.192
So I can only reiterate again
this afternoon our request,

686817860
04:08:31.193 --> 04:08:33.632
perhaps to the government more broadly,

1670224421
04:08:33.633 --> 04:08:42.532
to consider what we still regard
to be a very sensible proposal.

2603282073
04:08:42.533 --> 04:08:46.281
Turning now to amendment five
and chairman on court martial boards,

1555703304
04:08:46.282 --> 04:08:48.980
one of the issues that
was highlighted during

2726598272
04:08:48.981 --> 04:08:51.428
our visit to see the service justice

1451661729
04:08:51.429 --> 04:08:53.785
system was the challenge
of finding sufficient

3240087888
04:08:53.786 --> 04:08:55.942
officers to serve on court martial boards,

4274615244
04:08:56.028 --> 04:08:58.436
who are in no way connected
with the defendant.

4284613061
04:08:58.436 --> 04:09:03.030
This can become more of a challenge
as defendants become more senior,

1129712798
04:09:03.031 --> 04:09:05.740
and therefore the pool of
officers from which to draw

407378892
04:09:05.740 --> 04:09:08.181
narrows as one moves up
the promotion pyramid.

3933906946
04:09:08.182 --> 04:09:10.589
Now, the essence of this
amendment is therefore

3049593068
04:09:10.590 --> 04:09:12.043
to allow retired officers to

2862544056
04:09:12.044 --> 04:09:14.579
be drawn upon to help
comprise the membership

3172579516
04:09:14.579 --> 04:09:16.034
of boards for court martial,

758894519
04:09:16.035 --> 04:09:18.141
and therefore to widen the potential pool

3380585510
04:09:18.142 --> 04:09:20.628
of those who might be unavailable

3869721636
04:09:20.629 --> 04:09:23.980
to undertake this important
military and indeed civic duty.

1141628968
04:09:23.981 --> 04:09:24.883
>> At that point.

3226371581
04:09:24.885 --> 04:09:25.286
>> Yes.

1910812737
04:09:25.287 --> 04:09:26.993
>> I'm very grateful to my right.

2364831142
04:09:26.994 --> 04:09:29.789
I've been very indulgent.

4176013572
04:09:29.790 --> 04:09:32.953
I have to say that I agree with
him and not with with respect,

4007628324
04:09:32.954 --> 04:09:33.906
with the Minister,

1952077834
04:09:33.907 --> 04:09:38.284
because my recollection from being
the relevant Minister at the time was

2976694752
04:09:38.285 --> 04:09:43.184
there was a shortage of officers
to populate court martial boards.

1699408678
04:09:43.185 --> 04:09:45.790
One of the things we did in office was to

211760969
04:09:45.791 --> 04:09:47.646
ensure that it was service agnostic,

1571640158
04:09:47.647 --> 04:09:50.780
which gave a bigger pool
from which to draw,

2768026312
04:09:50.781 --> 04:09:55.130
but would perhaps compromise
be that retired officers

1958853525
04:09:55.131 --> 04:09:59.890
of a certain seniority might be allowed,

2896410944
04:09:59.891 --> 04:10:02.500
or a length of time after
service could be allowed,

1069023723
04:10:02.501 --> 04:10:04.526
since that would maintain the currency.

3104362245
04:10:04.528 --> 04:10:06.533
That clearly is troubling the Minister.

118245448
04:10:06.534 --> 04:10:09.040
And does he agree with
me that the Minister

4014584730
04:10:09.041 --> 04:10:12.081
is right to require or OR-7s,

3705123031
04:10:12.082 --> 04:10:13.536
as well as warrant officers,

1036314543
04:10:14.029 --> 04:10:15.734
to serve on court martial boards,

2193750611
04:10:15.735 --> 04:10:20.158
since that will expand
the pool of people available?

3532453019
04:10:20.159 --> 04:10:20.459
Well.

819199513
04:10:20.460 --> 04:10:21.363
>> Again, my hon.

1217008848
04:10:21.364 --> 04:10:23.219
Friend makes a very important point.

234324717
04:10:23.220 --> 04:10:26.429
Firstly, by allowing, as it
were, tri service boards,

3852915267
04:10:26.430 --> 04:10:29.237
that that that increases
the potential pool

3892743509
04:10:29.238 --> 04:10:31.194
even of senior officers who can serve.

1094732336
04:10:31.195 --> 04:10:35.776
Now, when we made that visit,
the Minister was not able to be with us.

3029953251
04:10:35.778 --> 04:10:36.931
There is no criticism.

2835147050
04:10:36.932 --> 04:10:38.530
He's an MoD Minister.

1003479218
04:10:38.531 --> 04:10:40.087
He's got a lot to think about.

1644757147
04:10:40.088 --> 04:10:44.186
He's got a great deal to
think about at the moment,

2245899608
04:10:44.188 --> 04:10:47.137
but he wasn't able to
be there on that visit,

4245875120
04:10:47.138 --> 04:10:49.797
so he wouldn't have heard
it from the horse's mouth.

1624915367
04:10:49.798 --> 04:10:53.135
This issue was raised
with us by practitioners

2701830765
04:10:53.136 --> 04:10:55.436
in the service justice system,

1520184166
04:10:55.436 --> 04:10:57.093
and they told us as a committee,

2003060737
04:10:57.094 --> 04:10:59.502
I'm looking around
the House for nods of assent

341463139
04:10:59.503 --> 04:11:01.510
from others who were on the same visit,

1406118963
04:11:01.511 --> 04:11:05.283
and I'm getting them that
this was a problem and this

3041444895
04:11:05.284 --> 04:11:07.740
was crimping the ability
to hold court martials.

1551072895
04:11:07.742 --> 04:11:10.342
So all we were trying to
do was to, if you like,

512387460
04:11:10.343 --> 04:11:13.504
justify the cost of the train
ticket to the taxpayer and prove

1687830001
04:11:13.505 --> 04:11:16.416
that we'd listen to what we
were being told on the visit.

3519631026
04:11:16.417 --> 04:11:17.370
And so that hence.

2968252237
04:11:17.371 --> 04:11:21.482
So I don't take quite
the sanguine approach of the Minister

3203681996
04:11:21.483 --> 04:11:24.374
that there are plenty enough
officers to go round,

169357629
04:11:24.375 --> 04:11:26.382
so I won't handle the name any further.

883793206
04:11:26.382 --> 04:11:30.989
I won't hammer the nail any
further, but I would respectfully,

1382501442
04:11:30.990 --> 04:11:35.083
particularly after
the contributions today,

2792065227
04:11:35.084 --> 04:11:38.186
just ask the Minister to look
at >> This one more time.

3682873359
04:11:38.186 --> 04:11:39.641
Now moving to amendment six.

1028141053
04:11:40.032 --> 04:11:42.490
The essence of this is to
speed up the potential

1042250630
04:11:44.032 --> 04:11:45.686
mobilisation of Group A reserves

2384420641
04:11:45.686 --> 04:11:51.692
from readiness level R nine 180
days to readiness level R 890 days.

2218972084
04:11:52.032 --> 04:11:54.439
Again, we debated this
in the Select Committee,

2356154536
04:11:54.440 --> 04:11:55.946
where I was keen to point out

1531306529
04:11:55.947 --> 04:11:58.131
to the Minister that this suggestion came,

2698730843
04:11:58.132 --> 04:12:00.338
as it were, from the shop floor,

1453614891
04:12:00.339 --> 04:12:04.334
having been put to me by a number
of serving reserve officers,

3023011438
04:12:04.335 --> 04:12:09.490
no names and no pack drill in order
to prevent any any career damage.

2971292234
04:12:09.490 --> 04:12:14.582
But they were very clear that
they would like the government

4292762177
04:12:14.583 --> 04:12:18.246
to accelerate their potential
mobilisation timetable.

3972962116
04:12:18.247 --> 04:12:20.683
And it's because it came
from that quarter that

3817171781
04:12:20.684 --> 04:12:23.785
we gave this request
particular consideration.

3343706691
04:12:23.786 --> 04:12:26.881
Now, I recall from
the Select Committee phase,

656764935
04:12:26.882 --> 04:12:30.544
the Minister did give an undertaking
to the committee that he would

4050841976
04:12:30.546 --> 04:12:33.839
take the suggestion away
and look at it in more detail,

108570885
04:12:33.840 --> 04:12:37.389
in consultation with
officials in his department.

1671719972
04:12:37.390 --> 04:12:40.433
We were therefore cautiously
optimistic that this might

4199378451
04:12:42.028 --> 04:12:44.535
lead to some change in
the government's position.

10142799
04:12:44.536 --> 04:12:46.743
I've heard what
the Minister has just said,

2652547689
04:12:46.744 --> 04:12:49.790
but we retabled this amendment
to give him an opportunity.

2543713645
04:12:50.032 --> 04:12:55.435
We hope to report back to the House
on the fruit of those discussions,

4156068033
04:12:55.436 --> 04:12:58.686
given the strong hint that
he dropped us in committee.

1724295727
04:12:58.688 --> 04:13:04.390
I would again very much urge
the Minister to think again on that,

1728090534
04:13:05.036 --> 04:13:10.036
bearing in mind this wasn't my idea
of that of my honourable, hon.

856706378
04:13:10.037 --> 04:13:10.487
Friends.

1656527411
04:13:10.488 --> 04:13:15.334
It was the idea of serving
reserve officers.

953112739
04:13:15.335 --> 04:13:19.090
So I'm acting here in supporting
their plea to him to mobilise

3501083139
04:13:19.091 --> 04:13:24.340
them more quickly should
the situation require it.

1317591327
04:13:24.341 --> 04:13:25.985
It's as simple as that.

181494786
04:13:25.986 --> 04:13:27.691
So at that point, Madam Chairman,

1206568731
04:13:27.692 --> 04:13:29.748
I'll thank the House for its indulgence.

3378838728
04:13:29.749 --> 04:13:33.202
I'll sit down to facilitate
other contributions,

114602868
04:13:33.203 --> 04:13:35.510
not least on education
and health care plans.

495493876
04:13:36.033 --> 04:13:38.041
And then by your leave, I might want to

2506789387
04:13:38.042 --> 04:13:39.798
speak again a bit towards the end,

1954520786
04:13:39.799 --> 04:13:42.908
when we've heard the debate,
particularly on the new clauses,

3559152331
04:13:42.909 --> 04:13:44.637
for the moment, I'll rest there.

2341294760
04:13:44.638 --> 04:13:48.239
>> Defence Select Committee
Tanmanjeet Singh Dhesi.

2879594846
04:13:48.240 --> 04:13:50.382
>> Thank you very much, Madam Chair.

4040913202
04:13:50.382 --> 04:13:52.440
And may I begin by thanking the Minister

3842378386
04:13:54.032 --> 04:13:56.039
and his team at the Ministry of Defence

3471008888
04:13:56.040 --> 04:14:00.639
for their engagement with the Defence
Committee on this legislation,

3279893132
04:14:00.640 --> 04:14:04.686
including the helpful briefing they
gave us ahead of Second Reading.

3106765888
04:14:04.688 --> 04:14:09.185
I would also like to thank
the Select Committee on the bill,

3384466783
04:14:09.186 --> 04:14:14.436
including my good friend and the hon.

3052816093
04:14:14.438 --> 04:14:19.792
Member from Eltham, who has
done him and his committee

1736513008
04:14:19.793 --> 04:14:23.168
have done incredible work
on the Select Committee,

3785546292
04:14:23.168 --> 04:14:30.093
and I also want to place on record my
thanks to my committee colleagues,

2570014306
04:14:30.094 --> 04:14:33.440
the honourable and gallant members,
the members for North Devon

2640977043
04:14:33.441 --> 04:14:37.837
and for Tunbridge Wells who
served on that committee.

3459496176
04:14:37.838 --> 04:14:41.339
The Defence committee naturally
takes a close interest in

2424034613
04:14:41.340 --> 04:14:44.349
the areas affected by this bill,
beginning with clause two.

2312090955
04:14:46.032 --> 04:14:49.536
We strongly welcome that
the government is extending

1735007553
04:14:49.537 --> 04:14:51.543
the Armed Forces Covenant to new policy

1939227071
04:14:54.033 --> 04:14:56.390
areas and making the duty
binding on Whitehall

175451749
04:14:57.037 --> 04:14:59.341
departments and
the devolved administrations.

1884777897
04:14:59.342 --> 04:15:03.193
This is something we
recommended in our inquiry

4269665396
04:15:05.037 --> 04:15:06.742
report on the covenant last year.

666560764
04:15:06.743 --> 04:15:10.788
At the time, we said that
legislation would be only one

273651136
04:15:10.789 --> 04:15:13.446
part of the solution for
strengthening the covenant,

3248405495
04:15:13.447 --> 04:15:18.040
and that the government needed to make
sure that the covenant legal duty

2960756761
04:15:18.041 --> 04:15:21.689
is more consistently applied by
improving guidance and training.

3115279460
04:15:21.690 --> 04:15:23.939
>> On that point, will he give way?

1576922599
04:15:23.940 --> 04:15:24.492
>> I will.

3940478260
04:15:24.493 --> 04:15:25.447
>> I thank my hon.

53065741
04:15:26.036 --> 04:15:27.189
Friend for giving way.

3935274737
04:15:27.190 --> 04:15:30.400
The Armed Forces Covenant is one
of the most impressive things,

1753805751
04:15:30.400 --> 04:15:36.637
in my opinion, about this bill, not
just UK, but also for the 115,000

2759209641
04:15:36.638 --> 04:15:38.694
veterans in Wales and their families who

2405869351
04:15:38.695 --> 04:15:40.551
will now benefit from the legal duty

2190886377
04:15:40.552 --> 04:15:43.192
of public services to
take into consideration

3810446165
04:15:43.193 --> 04:15:45.237
their specific circumstances.

3911480071
04:15:45.238 --> 04:15:49.740
Will he join with me in wishing
a very happy Armed Forces

1656619056
04:15:49.742 --> 04:15:52.485
Day to Prestatyn Royal
British Legion branch,

3501920266
04:15:52.486 --> 04:15:54.694
as I will when I celebrate
this special day

908967322
04:15:54.695 --> 04:15:58.943
and commemorate with them
and later this month.

3984434610
04:15:58.944 --> 04:15:59.898
>> I thank my hon.

2741868552
04:15:59.899 --> 04:16:04.192
Friend and indeed commend
her intervention and extend

849745509
04:16:04.193 --> 04:16:07.143
her and join her in
extending my best wishes,

376438489
04:16:07.144 --> 04:16:09.442
because it is welcome, Madam Chair,

2006122040
04:16:09.443 --> 04:16:11.939
that the government has now published

3400962792
04:16:11.940 --> 04:16:14.337
its draft guidance on the legal duty.

1544249124
04:16:14.338 --> 04:16:19.791
I'm pleased to see that it
includes an explanation of

2363159930
04:16:19.792 --> 04:16:22.737
what it means to pay due
regard to the covenant,

3760349883
04:16:22.738 --> 04:16:25.540
as witnesses to our
inquiry told us that this

4081876547
04:16:25.541 --> 04:16:27.395
phrase can sometimes seem ambiguous,

3775179132
04:16:28.994 --> 04:16:32.454
and I hope that the Minister will
consult widely with those affected

2031194152
04:16:32.456 --> 04:16:35.692
by the legal duty to make sure
this guidance meets their needs.

809107318
04:16:35.693 --> 04:16:38.540
Our committee will be
watching very closely

135064598
04:16:38.541 --> 04:16:41.263
to see whether the expanded covenant is

1518079149
04:16:41.264 --> 04:16:46.039
being delivered and making
a positive difference

2576234398
04:16:46.040 --> 04:16:47.644
for our armed Forces community.

2445870109
04:16:49.037 --> 04:16:53.239
Madam chair, the creation of a new
Defence Housing Service service

51222207
04:16:53.240 --> 04:16:56.292
in clause three of the Bill
is also very, very welcome.

288614945
04:16:56.293 --> 04:16:59.998
I'm pleased that the government has made

4127515465
04:16:59.999 --> 04:17:02.436
it a priority to modernise the defence

3363320561
04:17:02.438 --> 04:17:07.592
estate and has committed £9 billion
over ten years to support its work.

289582579
04:17:07.593 --> 04:17:10.138
The challenge for the Minister, though,

47183809
04:17:10.139 --> 04:17:14.737
will be to ensure that this
funding is delivered as promised.

1681615662
04:17:14.738 --> 04:17:17.138
In the current geopolitical climate,

3671167877
04:17:17.139 --> 04:17:20.988
it is not hard to imagine
how a government might

1341351677
04:17:20.989 --> 04:17:25.239
come under pressure to
divert scarce resources

1217841160
04:17:25.240 --> 04:17:26.644
in response to some crisis,

4100328683
04:17:26.645 --> 04:17:31.544
and I hope that the government
will uphold its commitment

760890002
04:17:31.546 --> 04:17:33.502
to our service families come what may.

3358745075
04:17:34.036 --> 04:17:36.292
Madam chair, turning
briefly to clause four,

2093073400
04:17:36.293 --> 04:17:41.436
the new powers to counter uncrewed
devices are sorely needed.

3380407943
04:17:41.438 --> 04:17:46.642
My committee's inquiry into defence
in the Grey zone examined the many

1394948025
04:17:46.643 --> 04:17:51.543
kinds of hybrid threat posed by
hostile states, including drones.

3441457403
04:17:52.036 --> 04:17:56.038
The armed forces need to have
the power to deal with these threats,

2049623115
04:17:56.039 --> 04:18:00.647
to show our adversaries that their hybrid

1316188643
04:18:00.648 --> 04:18:02.353
tactics will not work against us.

3454053744
04:18:02.354 --> 04:18:07.889
Now, turning to the measures on
service, just yes, I will give way.

3915958808
04:18:07.890 --> 04:18:10.600
>> I thank the chair of
the committee for giving way.

571483759
04:18:10.601 --> 04:18:13.661
I have the opportunity to meet
with the Ministry of Defence,

1535184592
04:18:13.662 --> 04:18:16.621
Police and the Chief Constable
of the Ministry of Defence,

3000639678
04:18:16.622 --> 04:18:19.331
Police at RAF Wyton in my
constituency the other day,

913726474
04:18:19.332 --> 04:18:21.639
and I was very impressed
by the Counter-drone

1931702276
04:18:21.640 --> 04:18:23.544
capability that they are now equipped

4223920556
04:18:23.546 --> 04:18:27.108
with vastly in excess of what
the Home Office policing teams now have.

4257690118
04:18:27.109 --> 04:18:30.019
I think it's a very simple
solution to the counter- drone

726380717
04:18:30.020 --> 04:18:32.629
capability that we should
have at all of our bases,

3157680534
04:18:32.630 --> 04:18:34.638
and I would urge him to put pressure on

2936040387
04:18:34.639 --> 04:18:36.948
the Minister to try
and roll out the new CPM.

959948171
04:18:38.041 --> 04:18:41.249
Wilson and Watson drone drone
weapons or counter-drone weapons,

3812810731
04:18:41.250 --> 04:18:43.993
rather that they had to all
of our bases to make sure

211227491
04:18:43.994 --> 04:18:48.242
that that capability is as
widespread as possible.

3853720989
04:18:48.243 --> 04:18:49.849
>> Madam chair, I thank my hon.

3935487584
04:18:49.850 --> 04:18:52.056
Friend the Member for
Huntingdon for making

2480627292
04:18:52.057 --> 04:18:53.610
that intervention, and indeed,

4110301188
04:18:53.611 --> 04:18:55.767
the Defence Committee had the good fortune

1768584650
04:18:55.768 --> 04:18:57.737
to view some of these counter-drone

2689521199
04:18:57.738 --> 04:18:59.895
measures during one of our visits as well,

1015898520
04:19:00.996 --> 04:19:02.702
so I fully concur with his views.

3394669914
04:19:02.703 --> 04:19:06.797
Madam chair, turning now to
the measures on service justice,

126559134
04:19:08.040 --> 04:19:12.093
they are focussed on better supporting
victims of serious offences.

3975347680
04:19:12.094 --> 04:19:14.543
As the Minister knows, this is a subject

4155002324
04:19:14.543 --> 04:19:16.200
that comes up again and again in

2789968774
04:19:16.201 --> 04:19:19.943
the Defence Committee's regular
sessions on women in the Armed forces,

2314989016
04:19:19.944 --> 04:19:24.246
and so I am pleased that
this is a focus of the Bill.

892941647
04:19:24.247 --> 04:19:27.243
It is only right that
the Bill brings protections

2403603556
04:19:27.244 --> 04:19:29.799
available in the service justice system,

2260194874
04:19:29.800 --> 04:19:34.643
such as the domestic abuse orders
and stalking protection orders,

2381703118
04:19:34.644 --> 04:19:38.044
into line with those available
in the civilian system.

53852725
04:19:38.046 --> 04:19:41.398
The new reporting requirements and

3664581552
04:19:41.399 --> 04:19:45.142
the victims code are also welcome changes,

3054139565
04:19:45.143 --> 04:19:49.046
but it has been our experience as
a committee and for our predecessors

1658544859
04:19:49.047 --> 04:19:54.843
that new initiatives do not always
have the impact we would hope for,

2133257783
04:19:54.844 --> 04:19:59.895
because they take place in
an environment and culture that doesn't

1773552344
04:19:59.896 --> 04:20:02.767
take the needs of victims
as seriously as it should.

3506075489
04:20:02.768 --> 04:20:06.602
And I know that you cannot
legislate for culture Madam Chair,

2631620600
04:20:07.041 --> 04:20:11.390
but I will make the point
that unless there is proper

3614079812
04:20:11.391 --> 04:20:14.251
training on the measures in
this bill and a message from

1116395027
04:20:14.252 --> 04:20:19.048
leaders throughout defence
that things must change,

2725394120
04:20:19.049 --> 04:20:22.260
it is likely our or our Committee
will continue to hear stories

1324849803
04:20:22.261 --> 04:20:27.498
from victims who feel let down
by the service justice system.

367727484
04:20:28.040 --> 04:20:29.293
Turning now to reserves.

3553183817
04:20:29.293 --> 04:20:32.704
The Bill also aims to update
the way defence uses them,

3594382192
04:20:32.706 --> 04:20:35.591
and I welcome clause 31,

2669836823
04:20:35.592 --> 04:20:37.699
which will make it easier to move between

1313921469
04:20:37.700 --> 04:20:39.304
the regular and reserve forces.

3663970755
04:20:39.305 --> 04:20:41.611
This will support more
flexible career paths,

1159469372
04:20:41.612 --> 04:20:44.018
allowing people with
military expertise to move

3042240027
04:20:44.019 --> 04:20:47.293
into roles in industry and vice versa.

408415869
04:20:47.294 --> 04:20:51.147
The changes to call out and recall
conditions in clauses 32 and 33 of

2301388571
04:20:53.041 --> 04:20:58.344
the bill should also help to strengthen
the capacity of our reserves,

393304335
04:20:58.345 --> 04:21:01.854
because reserves are a key component
of our nation's readiness,

459351898
04:21:01.855 --> 04:21:05.996
showing that we are ready
to respond to aggression,

4141870752
04:21:05.997 --> 04:21:11.049
stirs our enemies and lets us
respond more effectively if needed,

3085371243
04:21:11.050 --> 04:21:12.303
and our hope, therefore,

4239436297
04:21:12.304 --> 04:21:14.746
that these measures will
soon be followed by

3212114070
04:21:14.747 --> 04:21:18.224
further steps to improve our readiness,

2684805577
04:21:18.225 --> 04:21:22.245
including in the promised
Defence Readiness Bill,

630270519
04:21:22.246 --> 04:21:25.644
which is needed sooner rather
than later, Madam chair.

3327462394
04:21:25.645 --> 04:21:28.395
And while the measures in this Bill will

1769760176
04:21:28.396 --> 04:21:31.549
undoubtedly improve our readiness,

2271456078
04:21:31.550 --> 04:21:34.942
they are focussed on
the strategic reserve only now,

1035996567
04:21:34.943 --> 04:21:39.092
the Strategic Defence Review
stated an ambition to increase

191108170
04:21:39.093 --> 04:21:42.293
the active reserves by
20% when funding allows,

3806425355
04:21:42.294 --> 04:21:46.645
and we do not know how
and when this will be achieved.

131941553
04:21:46.646 --> 04:21:50.896
The measures in the Bill are
therefore a good start,

26160024
04:21:50.897 --> 04:21:52.904
but there is obviously more work to do.

1347061433
04:21:52.905 --> 04:21:54.843
In conclusion, Madam Deputy Speaker,

737519125
04:21:54.844 --> 04:21:59.551
I can see the the stare
from your good self.

2740654601
04:21:59.552 --> 04:22:02.746
I believe this bill will make
a positive difference to

4260571334
04:22:02.747 --> 04:22:05.942
the lives of those who
serve in our Armed forces,

783633846
04:22:05.943 --> 04:22:09.997
and I will certainly be
supporting it as it continues

1197183244
04:22:09.998 --> 04:22:14.395
to make progress through the House.

2593617704
04:22:14.396 --> 04:22:15.449
Thank you very much.

3714603897
04:22:15.450 --> 04:22:16.804
>> Thank you, Madam Chair.

3634218851
04:22:16.805 --> 04:22:17.859
>> There is much in.

748584781
04:22:17.860 --> 04:22:18.813
>> This bill that.

865874406
04:22:18.814 --> 04:22:19.865
>> Deserves support.

4146789509
04:22:19.867 --> 04:22:20.569
>> It renews.

1971856966
04:22:20.570 --> 04:22:22.093
>> The statutory basis for.

1111161421
04:22:22.094 --> 04:22:22.796
>> Our armed.

2768472146
04:22:22.797 --> 04:22:23.347
>> Forces.

3468802284
04:22:23.349 --> 04:22:25.505
>> Extends the Armed forces covenant duty,

101222132
04:22:25.506 --> 04:22:27.962
introduces a defence housing
service and reforms

459414636
04:22:27.963 --> 04:22:30.319
certain aspects of
the service justice system.

3244117537
04:22:30.320 --> 04:22:32.275
These are genuine steps forward and we

2816189123
04:22:32.276 --> 04:22:34.082
really do acknowledge them as such.

421495640
04:22:34.083 --> 04:22:36.842
But good intentions are not
the same as good outcomes,

4142255895
04:22:36.843 --> 04:22:38.900
and it is a gap between those two things

1165304861
04:22:38.901 --> 04:22:40.657
that our amendments seek to close.

2467461534
04:22:40.658 --> 04:22:42.765
Let me begin with the question of people,

2922618349
04:22:42.766 --> 04:22:44.470
specifically how we recruit them,

481410966
04:22:44.471 --> 04:22:46.728
retain them, and treat
them when they leave.

127438551
04:22:46.729 --> 04:22:48.883
The government will shortly ask Parliament

2085409602
04:22:48.885 --> 04:22:50.539
to authorise the maximum numbers

2823718893
04:22:50.540 --> 04:22:54.746
of service personnel across each
branch of the armed forces.

2259500199
04:22:54.747 --> 04:22:55.699
That is certainly.

126800540
04:22:55.700 --> 04:22:56.302
>> I think.

1375381940
04:22:56.303 --> 04:22:58.341
>> Thank you for giving way.

649909948
04:22:58.342 --> 04:23:00.047
>> This bill makes great strides.

1957258862
04:23:00.048 --> 04:23:00.399
>> In.

2527376479
04:23:00.400 --> 04:23:01.853
>> Modern housing standards.

1159190142
04:23:01.854 --> 04:23:02.456
>> And the.

563170699
04:23:02.457 --> 04:23:04.915
>> Enshrinement of
the covenant is to be lauded.

143535332
04:23:04.916 --> 04:23:07.024
But I can't help but get the feeling that

1575406693
04:23:07.025 --> 04:23:09.031
there is a sense of strategic lethargy,

1569391190
04:23:09.032 --> 04:23:11.440
with a lack of serious
work through policies to

1376054997
04:23:11.441 --> 04:23:13.847
tackle the crisis in
recruitment and retention.

1624021960
04:23:13.847 --> 04:23:17.210
From what I can see, there is no
mention of incentives or bonuses.

4085110464
04:23:17.211 --> 04:23:18.967
Just to give a couple of examples.

3770615779
04:23:18.968 --> 04:23:21.627
Is this an oversight or
a deliberate decision to put

1678451306
04:23:21.628 --> 04:23:23.935
these issues on the back
burner, back burner?

3180401397
04:23:23.936 --> 04:23:26.796
Or, to put it another way, are
the government now simply

1479049880
04:23:26.797 --> 04:23:30.799
content to sit on their hands
while the crisis deepens?

3186235334
04:23:30.800 --> 04:23:31.703
>> Thank the hon.

3140194988
04:23:31.704 --> 04:23:33.157
Member for her intervention.

406626458
04:23:33.158 --> 04:23:35.114
And of course, those are questions for

3669138645
04:23:35.115 --> 04:23:37.472
the Minister to answer
in his closing remarks.

1072715830
04:23:37.472 --> 04:23:39.880
But clearly, recruitment
and retention is a key

2798551810
04:23:39.881 --> 04:23:41.987
concern in the armed forces and something

4156907348
04:23:41.988 --> 04:23:45.847
that's been a source of crisis in
the armed forces for many years now.

4287511537
04:23:45.849 --> 04:23:48.807
It is reasonable, therefore,
in the context of authorising

793792295
04:23:48.808 --> 04:23:50.996
maximum numbers of service personnel,

2938043368
04:23:50.997 --> 04:23:53.504
that Parliament should be
told how the government

3137639132
04:23:53.505 --> 04:23:55.511
plans to treat those people in service.

2306172944
04:23:55.512 --> 04:23:58.496
New clause nine would require
a retention strategy

1061850473
04:23:58.497 --> 04:24:00.753
to be published alongside
the authorisation.

3891884902
04:24:00.754 --> 04:24:03.965
It is a modest proposal and
the case for it is straightforward,

3544779213
04:24:03.966 --> 04:24:06.070
because recruitment alone solves nothing.

881693810
04:24:06.071 --> 04:24:09.649
If the conditions of service
drive people back out the door.

513990217
04:24:09.650 --> 04:24:12.507
We can invest in advertising
and outreach in processing,

2997644948
04:24:12.508 --> 04:24:15.619
but still find ourselves filling
a vessel that will not hold.

3908477378
04:24:15.620 --> 04:24:18.429
The problems that cause people
to leave are well known.

1326706485
04:24:18.430 --> 04:24:22.347
Inadequate housing, unsupported
families, opaque career structures,

2969448579
04:24:22.347 --> 04:24:25.809
and a sense that the institution
does not value them as individuals.

3925926166
04:24:25.810 --> 04:24:28.049
New clause ten would
require an independent

1394270265
04:24:28.050 --> 04:24:30.657
review to examine precisely those factors,

3638632776
04:24:30.658 --> 04:24:33.146
including diversity, inclusion,

4101208555
04:24:33.147 --> 04:24:36.548
the medical discharge process
and the state of defence housing,

889926931
04:24:36.549 --> 04:24:38.704
not because these are peripheral concerns,

44570063
04:24:38.704 --> 04:24:42.296
but because they are
operational and certain.

4095416874
04:24:42.297 --> 04:24:43.751
>> Concern with his remarks.

2295041088
04:24:43.752 --> 04:24:46.898
Because we have we've got
the Continuous Attitude Survey,

39785478
04:24:46.899 --> 04:24:49.494
which does its work
every year and delivers

3687606304
04:24:49.495 --> 04:24:52.448
to Ministers a clear
account of what's keeping

2892322494
04:24:52.449 --> 04:24:54.454
people in and what's driving them away.

3743117571
04:24:54.456 --> 04:24:57.601
Is he seriously proposing
another set of reviews that

3618191122
04:24:59.004 --> 04:25:01.311
will add very little to
what we already know?

3846897566
04:25:01.313 --> 04:25:04.201
>> DEFRA I thank
the Member for his comments,

1312982125
04:25:04.202 --> 04:25:06.397
and this isn't another review.

2869838992
04:25:06.398 --> 04:25:08.704
The Continuous Attitude
Survey is a survey of

3457187472
04:25:08.706 --> 04:25:11.049
service personnel and that is what it is.

3359193224
04:25:11.050 --> 04:25:12.504
A review is quite different.

2290261067
04:25:12.505 --> 04:25:14.862
I'm sure he would appreciate
and we're talking

2716166995
04:25:14.863 --> 04:25:16.567
about an independent review here.

3188477417
04:25:16.568 --> 04:25:18.474
So they're not really the same thing.

2026276273
04:25:18.475 --> 04:25:20.231
On housing, I want to be specific.

4279699525
04:25:20.232 --> 04:25:22.286
The government's commitment to improving

2007297252
04:25:22.287 --> 04:25:24.341
service family accommodation is welcome,

108671639
04:25:24.342 --> 04:25:26.699
but new clause 13 exists
because single living

113664614
04:25:26.700 --> 04:25:28.505
accommodation has for too long been

2728729514
04:25:28.506 --> 04:25:30.963
treated as a secondary
concern for a significant

2080577290
04:25:30.964 --> 04:25:32.617
proportion of serving personnel.

4131852593
04:25:32.618 --> 04:25:35.376
That accommodation is not
temporary, it is their home.

1728505225
04:25:35.377 --> 04:25:37.533
It is where they recover after deployment,

1613768642
04:25:37.534 --> 04:25:39.288
where they live, between postings,

3615066264
04:25:39.289 --> 04:25:41.446
where they begin and end each working day.

2000338208
04:25:41.447 --> 04:25:43.503
If it falls below a reasonable standard,

2252937132
04:25:43.504 --> 04:25:46.565
that is not merely a welfare
issue, it is a retention issue.

1275568460
04:25:46.566 --> 04:25:49.225
We cannot speak of our people
as our greatest asset,

535442829
04:25:49.226 --> 04:25:52.436
while declining to apply that in
principle to where they sleep,

1909669978
04:25:52.436 --> 04:25:54.293
I will now turn to veterans support.

297137073
04:25:54.293 --> 04:25:56.501
The move from military
to civilian life is,

1136945916
04:25:56.502 --> 04:25:58.056
for some, a difficult passage.

4260493516
04:25:58.057 --> 04:26:00.865
It should not be made harder
by administrative failure.

2789314316
04:26:00.865 --> 04:26:02.922
New clause 11 will ensure that personnel

772077032
04:26:02.923 --> 04:26:04.677
leaving service receive a complete

2581375380
04:26:04.678 --> 04:26:07.737
copy of their medical records
within one month of discharge,

3846058690
04:26:07.738 --> 04:26:11.047
with the option for direct transfer
to civilian health providers.

405251389
04:26:11.048 --> 04:26:12.854
This reflects a basic duty of care,

1515641013
04:26:12.855 --> 04:26:15.212
and it really shouldn't
be complex for someone

468831585
04:26:15.213 --> 04:26:16.816
leaving with physical injuries,

3487292493
04:26:16.817 --> 04:26:20.478
with trauma, or with a history that
civilian doctors need to understand.

2124308730
04:26:20.479 --> 04:26:22.786
A delayed or incomplete
medical record can be

1020701046
04:26:22.787 --> 04:26:25.042
more than just
a bureaucratic inconvenience,

1893728626
04:26:25.043 --> 04:26:26.847
but a genuine barrier to treatment.

566704265
04:26:26.849 --> 04:26:29.607
New clause 12 addresses
something we have discussed in

4271784904
04:26:29.608 --> 04:26:32.265
this House for many years
without sufficient access.

1986543183
04:26:32.266 --> 04:26:33.468
Veterans mental health.

3115480635
04:26:33.469 --> 04:26:33.969
Secondly.

1706587974
04:26:33.970 --> 04:26:34.924
>> I thank my hon.

3111997610
04:26:34.925 --> 04:26:36.078
Friend for giving way.

2817127869
04:26:36.079 --> 04:26:38.133
Veterans mental health challenges can be

2820875387
04:26:38.135 --> 04:26:40.246
significant for obvious reasons trauma,

2263628076
04:26:40.247 --> 04:26:43.555
stress, long time away from
friends and family and so on.

795561144
04:26:43.556 --> 04:26:45.060
And devastatingly, as my hon.

4171441912
04:26:45.061 --> 04:26:46.264
Friend, I'm sure knows,

1229055777
04:26:46.265 --> 04:26:49.060
young veterans under the age
of 24 have a suicide rate

3922627763
04:26:49.061 --> 04:26:50.950
that is 2 to 4 times higher than

2510449795
04:26:50.951 --> 04:26:53.549
the civilian population of the same age.

94891685
04:26:53.550 --> 04:26:57.000
So given that mental health
problems are so significant

727644437
04:26:57.001 --> 04:26:59.960
and less visible than physical
health needs, would my hon.

2919923014
04:26:59.961 --> 04:27:02.368
Friend agree with me that
establishing the role

566775693
04:27:02.369 --> 04:27:04.725
of a Veterans Mental
Health Oversight officer,

299707970
04:27:04.726 --> 04:27:06.030
as outlined in clause 12,

251711190
04:27:06.052 --> 04:27:09.453
would ensure that mental
health support is robust?

3519418396
04:27:09.454 --> 04:27:10.408
>> I thank my hon.

3339142030
04:27:10.409 --> 04:27:12.765
>> Friend for her
intervention and absolutely.

61520622
04:27:12.766 --> 04:27:15.677
And I think the something to
say is that the suicide rate

2597285671
04:27:15.678 --> 04:27:18.336
amongst young men in this
country is already higher,

686655828
04:27:18.337 --> 04:27:21.751
and therefore it is deeply
troubling the numbers relating

4291444296
04:27:21.752 --> 04:27:23.958
to people discharged
from the armed forces.

587303391
04:27:23.959 --> 04:27:27.698
We have passed motions, public
strategies and made commitments.

3772676657
04:27:27.699 --> 04:27:31.059
What we've not done is create
proper, sustained oversight.

101071931
04:27:31.060 --> 04:27:31.612
As my hon.

4010061475
04:27:31.613 --> 04:27:34.620
Friend mentions, a veterans
Mental Health oversight Officer

1435427087
04:27:34.621 --> 04:27:36.877
with a statutory remit
to monitor provision,

2981211302
04:27:36.878 --> 04:27:39.383
assess compliance with
covenant duties and report

3621409146
04:27:39.385 --> 04:27:41.791
annually to Parliament
would begin that change.

1049334531
04:27:41.792 --> 04:27:44.149
The covenant should not
be a postcode lottery.

1252157047
04:27:44.150 --> 04:27:47.307
Its outcomes should be measurable,
consistent and accountable.

3813432091
04:27:47.308 --> 04:27:50.600
I also want to acknowledge
the amendments tabled by my hon.

3366525774
04:27:50.601 --> 04:27:53.860
Friend the Member for Epsom
and Ewell on pension communications.

1777039938
04:27:53.861 --> 04:27:55.715
The transfer of medical assessments,

4111677292
04:27:55.716 --> 04:27:58.073
the Reserve Forces estate
and the treatment of

3861448434
04:27:58.074 --> 04:28:00.079
domestic abuse offences they address in

140171830
04:28:00.079 --> 04:28:02.035
each case the same underlying problem.

163028640
04:28:02.036 --> 04:28:04.141
The service personnel, veterans and their

2785452693
04:28:04.142 --> 04:28:06.301
families are too often disadvantaged,

267479491
04:28:06.302 --> 04:28:09.414
not by malice but by systems
that do not speak to one another

1753008513
04:28:09.415 --> 04:28:12.324
and processes that were never
designed with them in mind.

1530757137
04:28:13.048 --> 04:28:15.054
Which brings me to the covenant itself.

3391461933
04:28:15.055 --> 04:28:18.805
New clause 14 replaced national standards
around extended covenant duty,

1001708295
04:28:18.806 --> 04:28:20.308
requiring statutory guidance,

1247496900
04:28:20.309 --> 04:28:23.165
minimum requirements for public
bodies, proper training,

581203117
04:28:23.166 --> 04:28:25.472
and a framework for
monitoring and reporting.

1976114025
04:28:25.472 --> 04:28:28.505
New clause 15 would then
require the annual covenant

928672995
04:28:28.506 --> 04:28:32.558
report to assess compliance
against those standards,

1923001727
04:28:32.559 --> 04:28:34.713
analyse outcomes and make recommendations.

15605794
04:28:34.714 --> 04:28:37.371
The objection to such measures
is rarely principled.

4229961717
04:28:37.372 --> 04:28:39.177
Almost no one opposes the covenant.

423565988
04:28:39.178 --> 04:28:42.655
The difficulty has always
been consistency of delivery.

20277795
04:28:42.656 --> 04:28:44.802
One local authority may understand its

2614055669
04:28:44.803 --> 04:28:46.900
obligations well, another may not.

2762042140
04:28:46.900 --> 04:28:49.951
One health body may have invested in this.

900061037
04:28:49.952 --> 04:28:51.456
Another has done the minimum.

4121022998
04:28:51.457 --> 04:28:54.203
One veteran may receive
good support, another,

4196133747
04:28:54.204 --> 04:28:57.063
with identical needs in
a different part of the country,

1007834433
04:28:57.064 --> 04:28:59.171
may be left to navigate the system alone.

934969987
04:28:59.172 --> 04:29:01.879
These amendments exist to
make the covenant something

3341504308
04:29:01.880 --> 04:29:03.987
more than just a statement of good faith,

1247729076
04:29:03.988 --> 04:29:06.847
to make it a standard that can
be measured and enforced.

90750863
04:29:06.849 --> 04:29:08.001
Finally, amendment 90.

1230745359
04:29:08.002 --> 04:29:10.809
This amendment would require
that allegations of sexual

2377920236
