The proposal from my ten minute rule
bill to bring Royal Fleet auxiliary

3569837289
05:01:24.085 --> 05:01:27.344
personnel within the remit of
the new Armed Forces Commissioner,

851333777
05:01:27.345 --> 05:01:31.645
has become clause 30 in this bill,
which introduces schedule four.

3257240750
05:01:31.646 --> 05:01:36.140
I hope it's the start of work
on building recognition of

2639249641
05:01:36.141 --> 05:01:39.200
the RFA and on retention
and recruitment within the service,

386268960
05:01:40.088 --> 05:01:41.894
which is so valued and so valuable.

1477737404
05:01:41.895 --> 05:01:44.438
I'd like to speak a bit about housing.

2338270583
05:01:44.439 --> 05:01:46.948
The reason I made my home
in Cornwall was because

2569152951
05:01:46.949 --> 05:01:49.334
my then husband was
posted to RNAs Culdrose,

2399819866
05:01:49.335 --> 05:01:52.488
and I know that it's
the same for many families,

2520173610
05:01:52.489 --> 05:01:55.237
even 20 plus years ago
when I experienced it,

1097326889
05:01:55.238 --> 05:01:58.986
military housing wasn't
in a good condition.

1930724602
05:01:58.987 --> 05:02:01.647
We know that in 2023,
and for two thirds of service,

1309071115
05:02:01.648 --> 05:02:04.188
family accommodation was
in such a poor state,

2191625229
05:02:04.189 --> 05:02:05.543
it wasn't fit for purpose.

147936443
05:02:05.543 --> 05:02:08.050
And that's clearly something
we shouldn't accept.

226223962
05:02:08.084 --> 05:02:11.534
That's why I'm so pleased
this government is creating

3347952492
05:02:11.535 --> 05:02:14.543
the publicly owned defence
housing service with a ten year,

183978051
05:02:14.544 --> 05:02:17.764
£9 billion investment, which will benefit

972144023
05:02:17.765 --> 05:02:19.621
over 12000 houses in the South west,

2464981023
05:02:19.622 --> 05:02:21.177
many of which are in Cornwall,

845967020
05:02:21.178 --> 05:02:23.688
by bringing them back
into public ownership

2589380687
05:02:23.689 --> 05:02:27.191
after that disastrous
mid 90s privatisation

1012993856
05:02:27.192 --> 05:02:29.694
after which they degenerated.

4108694329
05:02:29.695 --> 05:02:32.051
I'm pleased that
the Consumer Charter includes

1650046429
05:02:32.052 --> 05:02:34.106
commitments to improve military housing,

339886393
05:02:34.107 --> 05:02:37.538
such as a better move in standard
and reliable repair repairs.

1503270881
05:02:37.539 --> 05:02:38.942
An unnamed housing officer.

3470481417
05:02:38.943 --> 05:02:43.541
We discussed this in committee,
and the bill committee report

4108299804
05:02:43.542 --> 05:02:46.549
highlighted that as private
contracts for customer service,

1187381555
05:02:46.550 --> 05:02:49.383
maintenance and repairs remain till 2029,

1713798672
05:02:49.385 --> 05:02:50.990
there is a need for that robust

157570703
05:02:50.992 --> 05:02:54.734
mechanism in place to hold contractors
to account for their performance.

2326266574
05:02:54.735 --> 05:02:56.791
Furthermore, I'd like to raise the issue

4269365083
05:02:56.792 --> 05:02:58.544
of modernised accommodation offer,

1620239702
05:02:58.546 --> 05:03:01.355
which has been promised for
many years and which extend

3443120572
05:03:01.356 --> 05:03:04.793
would extend entitlement to
service family accommodation to

3799798225
05:03:04.793 --> 05:03:08.939
those in long term relationships
and with shared response.

927706202
05:03:08.940 --> 05:03:10.291
Parental responsibilities.

298112169
05:03:10.292 --> 05:03:12.802
It is true, I know it,
that a lifetime of service

2239987180
05:03:13.084 --> 05:03:14.839
can put a strain on relationships,

3797738074
05:03:14.840 --> 05:03:19.744
sometimes culminating in divorce
or separation, and last year,

3193089702
05:03:20.088 --> 05:03:22.643
5000 personnel had
responsibility for non-resident

725745041
05:03:22.644 --> 05:03:24.448
children and they should absolutely

2586535268
05:03:24.449 --> 05:03:26.807
have a home where they
can have their children

1157856154
05:03:26.808 --> 05:03:28.766
to stay or live with some of the time.

3075446650
05:03:28.767 --> 05:03:30.874
I know this was identified in the housing

2219272376
05:03:30.875 --> 05:03:32.630
strategy as a long term objective,

4202506706
05:03:32.631 --> 05:03:34.441
but I appreciate the military.

719443601
05:03:34.442 --> 05:03:38.191
Families obviously want clarity on this.

2653632305
05:03:38.192 --> 05:03:42.535
The bill committee did bring that up,

2881566297
05:03:42.536 --> 05:03:47.334
and the MoD did acknowledge
this and say that

1550317978
05:03:47.335 --> 05:03:50.438
this will be a commitment for them within

2046511618
05:03:50.439 --> 05:03:52.093
six months of its establishment.

3197628590
05:03:52.094 --> 05:03:55.339
The DHS should outline a timetable
for widening entitlement

4130742320
05:03:55.340 --> 05:03:58.546
to SFA to include those in
long term relationships.

3853161238
05:03:59.046 --> 05:04:03.488
That was our recommendation
and the MoD did respond

2906412645
05:04:03.489 --> 05:04:05.897
with supporting the call
for the DHS to clarify

1491902522
05:04:06.088 --> 05:04:08.344
and accelerate those
plans to better reflect

2614012298
05:04:11.089 --> 05:04:13.546
the realities of modern
military and other life.

2205863027
05:04:13.547 --> 05:04:16.043
The committee's report also covered single

1109291854
05:04:16.043 --> 05:04:18.645
living accommodation at paragraph 52,

2003462129
05:04:18.646 --> 05:04:23.597
and there was a recommendation
there to urge the MoD to commit to

1479693035
05:04:23.599 --> 05:04:28.090
a costed plan for improving
the condition and maintenance of SLA,

1742404984
05:04:28.091 --> 05:04:30.645
and within 12 months of
the review's completion.

3325582612
05:04:30.646 --> 05:04:35.139
And the MoD did as well agree
with that recommendation,

3152773919
05:04:35.140 --> 05:04:37.999
which was positive to move to
the Armed Forces Covenant.

3867269524
05:04:38.000 --> 05:04:40.943
The Bill extends the covenant
to cover central government

3191268349
05:04:40.944 --> 05:04:43.385
departments and devolved administrations,

673810538
05:04:43.386 --> 05:04:45.141
and hopefully all of the councils,

974012889
05:04:45.142 --> 05:04:48.492
as well as new policy areas such
as employment and social care,

2061422903
05:04:48.493 --> 05:04:50.388
so no one falls through those gaps.

3260062038
05:04:50.389 --> 05:04:53.099
This is very welcome, and
I know the covenant has had

2732667071
05:04:53.100 --> 05:04:56.136
a positive impact in Cornwall,
particularly so far.

3377152987
05:04:56.137 --> 05:04:58.845
Witnesses who gave evidence
to the Bill committee did

4029619639
05:04:58.846 --> 05:05:02.147
raise the need for clearer
guidance and support,

4067411605
05:05:02.148 --> 05:05:04.904
and highlighted lack of
consistency and implementation

1039179395
05:05:04.905 --> 05:05:06.740
of the covenant across the country.

3587840483
05:05:06.742 --> 05:05:12.793
Public bodies are not always clear
what's expected of them and some.

3977090009
05:05:12.793 --> 05:05:13.647
I will give way.

4166678580
05:05:14.088 --> 05:05:15.092
>> I thank the hon.

1045873961
05:05:15.093 --> 05:05:16.246
Member for giving way.

2530498497
05:05:17.088 --> 05:05:21.738
Given Northern Ireland's
disproportionate contribution

1743562803
05:05:21.739 --> 05:05:23.695
to the armed forces over many decades,

2056121730
05:05:23.696 --> 05:05:27.145
the answer that
the Minister gave to my hon.

1127169792
05:05:27.146 --> 05:05:31.302
Friend from North Antrim
doesn't really cut it with

1877481907
05:05:31.303 --> 05:05:33.460
the armed forces with regards to the Armed

2291765451
05:05:33.461 --> 05:05:38.092
Forces covenant covenant
being made compulsory

3545022189
05:05:38.093 --> 05:05:40.140
within councils in Northern Ireland,

3074778235
05:05:40.141 --> 05:05:43.000
would she agree that
the government needs to go further?

2779559086
05:05:43.001 --> 05:05:45.257
Because, sadly, in
Northern Ireland we still

1284651852
05:05:45.257 --> 05:05:47.240
have political parties who completely

2247117667
05:05:47.240 --> 05:05:49.297
oppose the Armed Forces Covenant and its

2793976099
05:05:49.298 --> 05:05:51.101
implementation in Northern Ireland.

1142568563
05:05:51.102 --> 05:05:53.608
So therefore, it's important
that this government

1814893177
05:05:53.609 --> 05:05:57.344
act to protect our veterans
in Northern Ireland.

2749848190
05:05:57.345 --> 05:05:59.993
>> Jayne Kirkham thank you, Madam Chair.

2265151111
05:05:59.994 --> 05:06:02.899
I would agree to support this.

3539997646
05:06:02.900 --> 05:06:06.078
The MoD is updating and strengthening
the statutory guidance,

1823995805
05:06:06.079 --> 05:06:08.788
and I certainly would agree
that, as far as possible,

1813005219
05:06:08.789 --> 05:06:10.896
it covers all parts of the United Kingdom

164932321
05:06:10.897 --> 05:06:12.702
to include that clear and prominent

2409756327
05:06:12.703 --> 05:06:17.024
explanation of what due regard is
regarding to the covenant principles.

2092061693
05:06:17.025 --> 05:06:19.844
That guidance should explain
how service related

479791037
05:06:21.089 --> 05:06:22.893
disadvantage may arise in practice,

2915450357
05:06:22.894 --> 05:06:26.454
and how special provision can be
applied within relevant policy areas.

179063766
05:06:28.092 --> 05:06:30.550
I'd also like to refer
quickly to amendment two.

334987650
05:06:31.048 --> 05:06:32.452
The government I will give.

2014341231
05:06:32.453 --> 05:06:35.162
>> Way apologise for
interrupting the flow of my hon.

3961902544
05:06:35.163 --> 05:06:37.293
Friend's speech, but linked to her point

2383152273
05:06:37.293 --> 05:06:40.592
about the Armed Forces Covenant,

3844574082
05:06:40.593 --> 05:06:43.856
she may be aware that one of
the ways in which the United States

1364735813
05:06:43.857 --> 05:06:46.140
supports their military
personnel is through

206144655
05:06:46.141 --> 05:06:48.246
encouraging membership of a credit union,

2728402086
05:06:48.247 --> 05:06:51.538
the world's biggest credit
union, Navy, federal.

1802994634
05:06:51.539 --> 05:06:54.801
We have military credit unions
here in the UK, as she will know.

2203520992
05:06:54.802 --> 05:06:58.644
But more could be done to raise
awareness amongst military personnel

13434506
05:06:59.047 --> 05:07:03.592
about the benefits of helping
recruits manage their finances,

1659507084
05:07:03.593 --> 05:07:06.388
both during military life
and in civilian life.

923749036
05:07:06.389 --> 05:07:07.190
Afterwards too.

3863054529
05:07:07.191 --> 05:07:09.199
Does she share my view that it would be

2169424250
05:07:09.200 --> 05:07:11.338
good to hear from Ministers what more

992337333
05:07:11.339 --> 05:07:14.584
they're planning to do
to help raise awareness

608337824
05:07:14.585 --> 05:07:16.139
of the military credit unions?

1058701308
05:07:16.140 --> 05:07:16.891
Jayne Kirkham.

2121071449
05:07:16.892 --> 05:07:17.594
>> Thank you.

3630059396
05:07:17.595 --> 05:07:18.999
And thank you, Madam Chair.

2470720216
05:07:19.000 --> 05:07:23.040
Yes, I would agree, as a fellow
co-operative member that credit unions

3728895814
05:07:23.041 --> 05:07:27.001
can do so much in a very important
and I would certainly agree

464883319
05:07:27.002 --> 05:07:29.392
that if members of the armed forces could

3757747771
05:07:29.393 --> 05:07:32.351
be pointed and signposted towards those,

3139401342
05:07:32.352 --> 05:07:36.140
that would be absolutely
beneficial for them.

1384169635
05:07:36.141 --> 05:07:40.793
To go straight to amendment
two very quickly.

2954643094
05:07:40.793 --> 05:07:41.797
Of course, I would.

2205967754
05:07:41.798 --> 05:07:43.388
Thank you very much.

284633803
05:07:43.389 --> 05:07:48.493
Jocelyn was talking about
services and access.

1875262000
05:07:48.494 --> 05:07:50.852
The figures show that
fewer than 31% of female

1392606794
05:07:52.088 --> 05:07:54.192
serving personnel registered as veterans.

3595560502
05:07:54.193 --> 05:07:58.939
So that makes it much more difficult
for them to access services,

1645948608
05:07:58.940 --> 05:08:02.905
particularly if they have
had problems such as

203037925
05:08:02.906 --> 05:08:05.494
violence or bullying in the armed forces.

664724123
05:08:05.495 --> 05:08:09.494
So does she think that
more needs to be done to

3465055558
05:08:09.495 --> 05:08:11.650
encourage female veterans to come forward?

800763304
05:08:12.094 --> 05:08:12.845
Jayne Kirkham.

758907859
05:08:12.846 --> 05:08:13.699
I thank the hon.

2571628378
05:08:13.700 --> 05:08:14.100
Member.

1988607086
05:08:14.101 --> 05:08:15.957
And yes, this was something that was

897591008
05:08:15.958 --> 05:08:17.813
discussed at the committee that some

2583504528
05:08:17.814 --> 05:08:21.372
people simply didn't consider themselves
veterans for certain reasons.

555744774
05:08:21.373 --> 05:08:24.232
But the reasons that she's
given that they hadn't served

2167854594
05:08:24.233 --> 05:08:26.942
for very long and that
the that an awareness campaign

1318584622
05:08:27.093 --> 05:08:30.201
basically would be really important
so that people understand

2042927104
05:08:30.202 --> 05:08:32.790
that they are entitled
to all of these things.

2014970375
05:08:32.791 --> 05:08:35.489
And I think it's something
that a lot of people,

4047511408
05:08:35.490 --> 05:08:36.994
when they leave the military,

2869419658
05:08:36.995 --> 05:08:39.151
they they don't even think about it again.

3700324891
05:08:39.153 --> 05:08:42.647
And they don't have any idea that
those options are open to them.

218338155
05:08:44.093 --> 05:08:45.347
So I do agree with that.

1510749684
05:08:45.349 --> 05:08:48.709
Certainly regarding SED, we have
talked a bit about SED provision.

4183127415
05:08:48.710 --> 05:08:51.749
So there are people here who sit on

588465050
05:08:51.750 --> 05:08:53.808
the APPG and know for much more than me.

2670439553
05:08:53.809 --> 05:08:56.620
I would simply want to point
out that we know our send,

1626079596
05:08:56.621 --> 05:08:59.196
our SEND provision in
this country has been

3271111673
05:08:59.197 --> 05:09:01.154
broken for a very long period of time,

2554775214
05:09:01.155 --> 05:09:03.513
and that there is a White
Paper coming forward

492975802
05:09:03.514 --> 05:09:05.218
which should deal and standardise

1400984312
05:09:05.219 --> 05:09:07.225
some of these provisions so that across

2474343728
05:09:07.226 --> 05:09:09.247
the country you will not miss out.

2122026905
05:09:09.248 --> 05:09:12.007
It will not be the postcode
lottery that is the ideal,

3473713794
05:09:12.008 --> 05:09:14.165
and that our SEND provision should improve

4228307188
05:09:14.166 --> 05:09:16.121
so that whether you're in Basingstoke,

15556161
05:09:16.122 --> 05:09:18.679
Shrewsbury or Cornwall,
the provision you you need

2909857078
05:09:18.680 --> 05:09:21.138
will be there and will be
transferable with you.

3829239020
05:09:21.139 --> 05:09:24.148
Finally, very briefly, I'd like
to attest to the importance

1046466165
05:09:24.149 --> 05:09:26.105
of the veteran question in the census.

2789923571
05:09:26.106 --> 05:09:29.803
This was raised in
the committee and in the report.

2158985080
05:09:29.804 --> 05:09:33.215
Data from that 2021 census has been
vital to the local authorities,

3234954613
05:09:33.216 --> 05:09:35.547
for example, to find
some of those veterans.

3277752632
05:09:35.548 --> 05:09:38.797
And it's enabled them to
understand where veterans are,

4205481689
05:09:38.798 --> 05:09:40.101
the challenges they face,

3209419361
05:09:40.102 --> 05:09:43.392
and how best to deliver and design those

691962379
05:09:43.393 --> 05:09:45.349
services for them to meet their needs.

2001909425
05:09:46.092 --> 05:09:50.093
Retaining the veteran question in
2031 would allow for standardisation

3748244080
05:09:50.094 --> 05:09:52.944
and the ability to track
changes in those trends.

1815999908
05:09:52.945 --> 05:09:55.451
It's also been absolutely
essential for veterans,

787907175
05:09:55.452 --> 05:09:58.593
charities and organisations that rely

3943363432
05:09:58.594 --> 05:10:00.450
on that evidence to bid for funding,

799267773
05:10:00.451 --> 05:10:05.497
and I very much support its
inclusion in the next census.

1913382273
05:10:05.498 --> 05:10:07.503
Cornwall has a proud military heritage.

3553443855
05:10:07.504 --> 05:10:10.463
Many families have someone who
served or is still serving,

333004613
05:10:10.464 --> 05:10:13.522
who make extraordinary sacrifices
to keep this country safe,

4039938120
05:10:13.523 --> 05:10:16.079
and they obviously deserve
fair homes, safe homes,

2128772245
05:10:16.081 --> 05:10:18.945
fair treatment and
a system that understands

652795853
05:10:18.946 --> 05:10:20.801
the unique demands of military life.

611069541
05:10:22.088 --> 05:10:24.244
I'm pleased that the Royal Fleet Auxiliary

2182704240
05:10:24.245 --> 05:10:25.800
is also included in this bill,

786995762
05:10:25.801 --> 05:10:28.601
and that I've played a very
tiny part in shaping it.

811022806
05:10:28.602 --> 05:10:31.512
And I'm also pleased that those
who keep our armed forces

449005310
05:10:31.513 --> 05:10:34.601
moving around will be properly
recognised and protected.

3778856893
05:10:35.093 --> 05:10:36.949
As a government, we promise to renew

3554272912
05:10:36.950 --> 05:10:39.156
the nation's contract
with those who serve,

2652814533
05:10:39.157 --> 05:10:42.548
and we are starting to deliver on that.

1253108810
05:10:42.549 --> 05:10:43.901
>> Doctor Andrew Murrison.

3094714350
05:10:44.092 --> 05:10:45.446
>> Thank you, Madam Chair.

3600298751
05:10:45.447 --> 05:10:49.304
I'm very privileged to be called
in this debate this afternoon.

2279201132
05:10:49.305 --> 05:10:54.204
And can I start by declaring my
interests as a reservist and also

429721883
05:10:54.204 --> 05:10:57.699
the author of a book called
The Military Covenant, which sadly,

1971066271
05:10:57.700 --> 05:10:59.954
is no longer in print but is available,

2893367269
05:10:59.956 --> 05:11:06.446
I'm told, from good charity shops,

2181481561
05:11:06.447 --> 05:11:08.704
bad ones, the the covenant,
as my right hon.

4052573138
05:11:09.092 --> 05:11:13.248
Friend who speaks for the opposition
said, is isn't about advantage.

4204281942
05:11:13.249 --> 05:11:15.103
It's not about advantage advantaging

3365914741
05:11:15.104 --> 05:11:17.061
the men and women of our armed forces.

543377238
05:11:17.061 --> 05:11:18.717
But it is about no disadvantage.

2093243659
05:11:18.718 --> 05:11:21.496
And it's just important to make that very

1100260521
05:11:21.497 --> 05:11:23.751
clear that servicemen and servicewomen

3919964527
05:11:23.752 --> 05:11:30.036
don't expect to be given anything,
The greatest particularly.

1094480789
05:11:30.037 --> 05:11:37.997
They usually the
the greatest pragmatist going.

2691832450
05:11:37.998 --> 05:11:41.593
And they don't expect But they do expect

3114672135
05:11:41.594 --> 05:11:43.502
not to be messed around if it can be.

3983948862
05:11:44.233 --> 05:11:46.641
Armed Forces Bill is
trying to mitigate some of

2839875788
05:11:46.642 --> 05:11:48.897
the disadvantages that
they necessarily have

466231688
05:11:48.898 --> 05:11:52.403
to put up with by virtue of
the unique circumstances

3010353975
05:11:52.404 --> 05:11:55.551
that they find themselves in now.

4130080215
05:11:55.552 --> 05:11:58.900
Clause 30 deals with
the armed Forces commissioner.

674844119
05:11:58.900 --> 05:12:01.809
It's just worthwhile remembering
what this was all about.

3523185513
05:12:01.810 --> 05:12:07.102
It was because there was
pressure to have some

1946263930
05:12:07.103 --> 05:12:09.208
sort of representation of serving people,

1984999484
05:12:09.209 --> 05:12:11.701
and that was resisted
by the government was,

2405250921
05:12:11.702 --> 05:12:14.398
in my view, and the armed
Forces commissioner

3308448879
05:12:14.399 --> 05:12:16.692
was a sort of a compromise.

3420741919
05:12:16.693 --> 05:12:19.755
But it is there to recognise
the fact that the men and women

3564303379
05:12:19.756 --> 05:12:24.757
of our armed forces do not have
trade union representation.

2632714318
05:12:24.758 --> 05:12:26.297
That's the purpose of it.

4252586524
05:12:26.298 --> 05:12:30.257
And whilst the Royal Fleet Auxiliary
is very close to my heart,

1402840286
05:12:30.258 --> 05:12:34.600
since my grandfather served
beginning of the last century

665107144
05:12:34.601 --> 05:12:37.008
in the early days of
the Royal Fleet Auxiliary.

3394092080
05:12:37.010 --> 05:12:39.469
So I'm very sympathetic
to it, and members of my

2036807343
05:12:39.470 --> 05:12:42.050
family have continued
to serve in that way.

1189839882
05:12:42.051 --> 05:12:45.548
Nevertheless, it is
a civilian merchant operation,

762539989
05:12:45.549 --> 05:12:49.097
and I am slightly concerned
that we may confuse

3892922435
05:12:49.097 --> 05:12:53.850
the Armed Forces Commissioner
and the trade unions.

541692613
05:12:53.851 --> 05:12:58.100
Notwithstanding the attempts
made sub para for A

3173337717
05:12:58.101 --> 05:13:02.657
and to C to cover off that
ambiguity, that grey area.

3393502285
05:13:02.658 --> 05:13:05.747
I have to ask the Minister to.

4128227524
05:13:05.748 --> 05:13:10.247
What about other organisations,
civilian organisations

4143777696
05:13:10.248 --> 05:13:12.597
that work very closely with our armed

1920377469
05:13:12.597 --> 05:13:17.499
forces and can deploy
with our armed forces,

4166183297
05:13:17.500 --> 05:13:20.646
such as the Navy, Army
and Air Force Institute?

4282441569
05:13:20.647 --> 05:13:24.945
An argument could be made for
them to be covered as well.

1102327821
05:13:24.946 --> 05:13:27.547
It'd be interesting to hear, perhaps,

3076712978
05:13:27.548 --> 05:13:29.806
whether the Minister has
any plans to do so,

1021980209
05:13:30.055 --> 05:13:32.363
maybe not in this measure,
but in the future,

323558399
05:13:34.096 --> 05:13:40.151
because that is really the logic
of this particular extension

3797275848
05:13:40.153 --> 05:13:47.797
of the role of the armed
Forces Commissioner.

489760423
05:13:47.798 --> 05:13:49.151
I thoroughly approve of a.

78771565
05:13:49.153 --> 05:13:52.813
Removal of the artificial barrier
between the reserves and the regulars,

1904024470
05:13:52.814 --> 05:13:56.299
and I speak as a as a reservist
and somebody who perhaps in

2606548140
05:13:56.300 --> 05:14:01.065
the past might have had a greater
interest in this than I do now.

2733868656
05:14:01.066 --> 05:14:06.998
Rick Haythornthwaite study the Rafi study.

2137923027
05:14:06.999 --> 05:14:08.799
This is made flesh by the.

2957825125
05:14:08.800 --> 05:14:12.701
Some of the measures in this
particular bill, in particular,

4157204874
05:14:12.702 --> 05:14:16.367
zigzag careers and
the ability to move from one

1171418374
05:14:16.368 --> 05:14:19.300
part of defence to another and back again.

869046496
05:14:19.301 --> 05:14:23.647
And it is complete madness for people

1838277220
05:14:23.648 --> 05:14:25.555
to having to leave and go through all

1295513642
05:14:25.556 --> 05:14:29.118
the rigmarole of filling out the forms
that were mentioned by the hon.

3232759147
05:14:29.119 --> 05:14:30.975
Gentleman is no longer in his place,

1631362765
05:14:30.976 --> 05:14:33.536
and go through the medical
and all the rest of it.

3517086136
05:14:33.537 --> 05:14:34.490
It makes no sense.

2832860416
05:14:34.490 --> 05:14:36.701
It's hugely wasteful
and it puts people off

1443993402
05:14:36.702 --> 05:14:41.201
and it encourages them simply to leave.

598598319
05:14:41.202 --> 05:14:45.102
However, in the bill there
is a clear distinction

3777094692
05:14:45.103 --> 05:14:47.997
between commissioned and non commissioned,

3494529748
05:14:47.998 --> 05:14:51.456
and I sometimes think we get
too wrapped up in all of this.

1167975647
05:14:51.457 --> 05:14:54.878
And simplicity is usually
the best course of action.

2233808001
05:14:54.879 --> 05:14:57.238
And it would be good to
hear from the Minister

3812448563
05:14:57.239 --> 05:14:58.996
why it is that he feels that there

4005997535
05:14:58.997 --> 05:15:01.403
needs to be separate
arrangements for officers,

1107203354
05:15:01.404 --> 05:15:02.757
which, as I understand it,

2904331141
05:15:02.758 --> 05:15:05.852
will not be included
in the initial tranche

3186916234
05:15:05.853 --> 05:15:08.395
of people going through this system

2917220640
05:15:08.396 --> 05:15:12.103
but will be dealt with at some future date

275164591
05:15:12.104 --> 05:15:14.011
if my reading of the bill is correct.

2149703454
05:15:14.012 --> 05:15:16.573
If I'm if it's not, then
I'm sure he will tell me.

2096378330
05:15:16.574 --> 05:15:19.802
In terms of recall for
service, my only concern about

3701322099
05:15:19.803 --> 05:15:22.352
this is certainly not a philosophical one.

3640294287
05:15:22.353 --> 05:15:22.954
Not at all.

3913139731
05:15:22.956 --> 05:15:24.912
But it is making service more onerous.

2842232042
05:15:24.913 --> 05:15:26.669
And at a time when we want people,

1227944420
05:15:27.101 --> 05:15:29.659
volunteers in our system
to join the armed forces,

1392131651
05:15:30.059 --> 05:15:32.065
either in the regulars or the reserves,

155010402
05:15:32.066 --> 05:15:37.203
extending their recall
liability from 6 to 18 years

3915163840
05:15:37.204 --> 05:15:41.809
and from 55 to 65 might not
necessarily be a particularly

2563012564
05:15:41.810 --> 05:15:44.400
attractive proposition for
many of them that don't

3921603827
05:15:44.400 --> 05:15:46.909
necessarily want to commit
to that kind of thing,

1310756639
05:15:46.910 --> 05:15:49.016
notwithstanding the fact that many of our

2728284804
05:15:50.100 --> 05:15:52.004
allies have something rather similar.

1841146656
05:15:52.005 --> 05:15:55.257
And on the subject of our allies,

2648798230
05:15:55.257 --> 05:15:58.754
it would be useful in encouraging
a strategic reserve,

179638353
05:15:58.755 --> 05:16:05.314
which I'm afraid is more
hypothetical than actual to emulate.

2360324052
05:16:06.101 --> 05:16:08.257
Perhaps the Nordics, who insist that their

1592390813
05:16:08.257 --> 05:16:10.456
reserve has come back for a day or two

1942042917
05:16:10.457 --> 05:16:16.059
a year in order to have a kit muster,

169908989
05:16:16.060 --> 05:16:18.018
a bit of a briefing, a bit of bonding.

981898351
05:16:18.100 --> 05:16:20.158
And in that way they seem to hold people

2982927968
05:16:20.159 --> 05:16:23.734
in in a way that we simply do not.

518658057
05:16:23.735 --> 05:16:26.092
Still, in this country,
we have the assumption

4076466709
05:16:26.093 --> 05:16:28.304
that you'll do your time as a regular,

1809079437
05:16:28.305 --> 05:16:30.910
and then you'll leave
and you won't look back.

428494763
05:16:30.911 --> 05:16:33.650
I'm sure the Minister would agree that

2734990627
05:16:33.651 --> 05:16:35.407
is something that needs to change,

2083003183
05:16:35.408 --> 05:16:38.357
and that is a cultural issue
rather than a management

570942219
05:16:40.101 --> 05:16:42.257
issue or a structural issue at the moment.

662379702
05:16:42.258 --> 05:16:47.458
And until we get into
the mindset that service is,

341941264
05:16:47.459 --> 05:16:50.307
if not for life, then for
a working life, ideally,

1979580798
05:16:50.308 --> 05:16:53.258
I fear we're not going
to be able to provide

1626734937
05:16:53.260 --> 05:16:58.156
the government with
the sort of person power

3985845704
05:16:58.157 --> 05:17:04.014
that is necessary in order
to sustain a future

4155845058
05:17:04.015 --> 05:17:07.151
operations in a pre war environment.

2249235531
05:17:07.153 --> 05:17:07.905
Now, many hon.

314200279
05:17:07.906 --> 05:17:08.256
Right.

421523964
05:17:08.257 --> 05:17:08.507
Hon.

1012853250
05:17:08.507 --> 05:17:12.506
Members today have talked about
the service justice parts of this bill,

3846116029
05:17:12.507 --> 05:17:16.156
and in many ways, those are among
the most important elements of it.

141145116
05:17:16.157 --> 05:17:20.852
It is worthwhile saying that certainly
during my time as a Minister,

2847470904
05:17:20.853 --> 05:17:23.559
there was difficulty populating
court martial boards.

126315826
05:17:23.560 --> 05:17:26.066
The Minister gave a slightly
different impression

2637981698
05:17:26.067 --> 05:17:27.571
of the position has improved.

4278871217
05:17:27.572 --> 05:17:30.631
Well, that's a good thing,
but certainly broadening the base

857639011
05:17:30.632 --> 05:17:33.388
makes it much more administratively
straightforward to

312694290
05:17:33.389 --> 05:17:36.197
ensure that people are available
on the days concerned,

3491472408
05:17:36.198 --> 05:17:39.107
and that the court martials
don't have to be interrupted.

1504526519
05:17:39.108 --> 05:17:41.765
There's nothing worse for
victims than finding that,

3954193599
05:17:41.766 --> 05:17:44.254
for whatever reason,
a court martial board,

779904696
05:17:44.255 --> 05:17:47.316
which they thought was going to
be held on a particular day,

284413823
05:17:47.317 --> 05:17:49.750
can't be constituted.

243619771
05:17:49.751 --> 05:17:52.551
And to that to that point,
I very much welcome,

811239141
05:17:52.552 --> 05:17:54.357
as I said, an intervention earlier,

2162505418
05:17:54.358 --> 05:17:58.556
the extension of eligibility
to OR-7 Staff Sergeant,

3797356527
05:17:59.059 --> 05:18:00.111
Chief Petty Officer,

2972390178
05:18:00.112 --> 05:18:04.206
which seems to me to make complete
sense and I hope would encourage

3054909730
05:18:04.207 --> 05:18:07.267
the sense of confidence that
people will have in the system.

4000522376
05:18:10.101 --> 05:18:12.611
In any event, I do have
problems with the I think

3340211754
05:18:13.100 --> 05:18:15.105
it's the Liberal Democrat Amendment 90,

2412658687
05:18:15.106 --> 05:18:17.908
which sort of implied
that civilian structures

1088351048
05:18:17.909 --> 05:18:20.052
are better than than service.

276520940
05:18:20.053 --> 05:18:24.304
That is just not the case,
simply is not the case.

4156792079
05:18:24.305 --> 05:18:27.909
The service justice system is
much quicker and there's nothing

2063569374
05:18:27.910 --> 05:18:31.669
worse for victims and have
to hang on for months,

2299758105
05:18:31.671 --> 05:18:36.308
potentially years, in order
to have their day in court.

1797068322
05:18:36.309 --> 05:18:38.453
Justice delayed is justice denied,

1280590461
05:18:38.454 --> 05:18:41.401
which is why I think it's
perfectly reasonable

1274133537
05:18:41.403 --> 05:18:46.008
to have the court martial option
open for particularly victims.

789358711
05:18:46.010 --> 05:18:49.957
But in any event,
a matter to be determined

2821850630
05:18:49.958 --> 05:18:52.251
under the prosecutor's protocol,

1366379231
05:18:52.252 --> 05:18:56.005
which seems to me to operate
perfectly well at the moment.

3975472787
05:18:56.006 --> 05:19:01.561
And I would be very
reluctant to see change.

70029168
05:19:01.561 --> 05:19:06.459
Clause 3839 is a sort
of hark back to 1688,

1866428310
05:19:06.460 --> 05:19:11.404
and the Parliament's desire to control
the size of the British army.

3538339910
05:19:11.405 --> 05:19:14.667
Of course, in those days there
really wasn't a navy to speak of,

1557557953
05:19:14.668 --> 05:19:17.358
certainly not in the way we
would think of it today.

1354091320
05:19:17.359 --> 05:19:19.466
And I most certainly wasn't an Air Force.

616903316
05:19:19.467 --> 05:19:23.756
So having to split numbers down
by service wasn't an issue then.

1784914526
05:19:23.757 --> 05:19:28.362
It was simply the number
of men you had under arms.

2946807910
05:19:28.363 --> 05:19:31.318
Whilst I understand
the purpose of the changes that

2417936229
05:19:31.319 --> 05:19:34.457
the Minister is proposing
under clauses 38 and 39,

3971776572
05:19:35.105 --> 05:19:36.910
that is to say, aggregating numbers

536159309
05:19:36.911 --> 05:19:39.016
and simply presenting that to Parliament.

109663179
05:19:39.017 --> 05:19:42.256
It does, of course, reduce the granularity

2726990140
05:19:42.257 --> 05:19:45.704
of data available to Parliament.

1351491600
05:19:45.704 --> 05:19:48.806
And I'm not clear that there
will be much cost involved

2921017101
05:19:48.807 --> 05:19:53.106
in providing us the data
that we have at the moment,

3194072469
05:19:53.107 --> 05:19:57.758
which is to be much more
granular in the data on numbers,

1506691365
05:19:57.760 --> 05:20:01.817
reservists, regulars, members
of the three armed forces.

2653963232
05:20:01.818 --> 05:20:06.463
And I would want to preserve
that, whilst at the same time

1242272397
05:20:06.464 --> 05:20:09.656
understanding that what really
matters overall are total,

1464321532
05:20:09.657 --> 05:20:11.463
the total size of our armed forces,

2560037107
05:20:13.105 --> 05:20:15.665
which we all want to ensure
is brought up to spec.

1474109675
05:20:17.118 --> 05:20:20.631
So, madam, Madam Chair, that's all
I really have to say on the issue.

370889772
05:20:20.632 --> 05:20:21.685
I commend this bill.

1928374132
05:20:21.686 --> 05:20:25.115
I think overall it does things
that we would all want to see,

2111044564
05:20:25.115 --> 05:20:27.650
and this is a tradition
with bills of this sort.

2315996016
05:20:27.651 --> 05:20:33.263
There is no great
controversy between the two

3577689931
05:20:33.264 --> 05:20:35.272
sides of the aisle, and I wish it well.

78225546
05:20:35.273 --> 05:20:35.523
Yes.

1585353515
05:20:36.111 --> 05:20:38.217
>> Johanna Baxter thank you, Madam Chair.

2221124715
05:20:38.218 --> 05:20:42.365
May I begin by offering my deepest
thoughts and prayers to the family,

1270839485
05:20:42.365 --> 05:20:44.905
friends and colleagues
of the British soldier

2781764401
05:20:44.906 --> 05:20:48.505
who tragically died in Iraq on Sunday.

986013749
05:20:48.506 --> 05:20:49.157
Madam Chair.

2708954566
05:20:49.158 --> 05:20:52.864
The world we live in
today is more perilous,

2301463964
05:20:52.865 --> 05:20:56.712
volatile and unpredictable than at
any point in our living memory.

3641935931
05:20:56.713 --> 05:21:00.767
We saw that last night
when Russia fired more

3169118341
05:21:00.768 --> 05:21:05.608
than 650 drones and 73
missiles into Ukraine,

4285971031
05:21:05.609 --> 05:21:09.308
killing 13 people, injuring more than 100,

613615002
05:21:09.309 --> 05:21:13.807
including a little girl aged only 11.

2897232103
05:21:13.808 --> 05:21:16.505
In this fragmented
world, a strong, modern,

2632700053
05:21:16.506 --> 05:21:18.561
highly capable military is not a luxury.

1640400200
05:21:18.563 --> 05:21:20.907
It is a necessity.

1938536211
05:21:20.908 --> 05:21:22.814
If we are to secure Britain's future,

2937011609
05:21:24.105 --> 05:21:27.605
national security must
always come above all else.

3998428323
05:21:27.606 --> 05:21:30.013
Which is why I strongly
welcome the continuous,

841326968
05:21:30.014 --> 05:21:34.658
decisive steps this Labour government
is taking to rebuild our defence.

867554392
05:21:34.659 --> 05:21:37.460
After it was hollowed out
by the party opposite.

2857598082
05:21:37.461 --> 05:21:39.806
That is why I support this Bill and

1764719643
05:21:39.807 --> 05:21:41.712
the government amendments laid in it.

4261661412
05:21:43.108 --> 05:21:46.167
Today, week after week, we are
seeing this Labour Government

296258774
05:21:46.168 --> 05:21:49.407
getting on with the job of
investing in our defence.

1188313630
05:21:49.408 --> 05:21:52.065
Just yesterday, the government
announced a vital new

3200668310
05:21:52.066 --> 05:21:54.422
munitions deal supporting
700 jobs in Belfast.

2242677189
05:21:54.423 --> 05:21:56.505
Last week, the government signed a joint

2946537634
05:21:56.506 --> 05:21:58.210
missile programme with Poland and

1853634277
05:21:58.211 --> 05:22:02.219
a new Swedish fighter
jet deal to strengthen

577727775
05:22:02.220 --> 05:22:05.304
Ukraine and boost British jobs.

3562083241
05:22:05.305 --> 05:22:09.856
We do this not simply because
it is a security argument.

544458387
05:22:09.857 --> 05:22:15.709
Agreement deals, but because it is
the moral duty of this government.

471346481
05:22:15.710 --> 05:22:19.169
It also creates highly skilled jobs
right across the United Kingdom,

1537765984
05:22:19.171 --> 05:22:21.377
including for the people
of my constituency

2456680105
05:22:21.378 --> 05:22:24.106
in Paisley and Renfrewshire South.

2534571259
05:22:24.107 --> 05:22:26.454
The substance of this
bill begins the urgent

2458539021
05:22:26.456 --> 05:22:28.561
work of undoing years of systemic damage.

3363218499
05:22:28.563 --> 05:22:32.321
I want to focus my comments
today on two areas

2071205202
05:22:32.322 --> 05:22:36.012
where the legislation
delivers the deepest,

1270342055
05:22:36.013 --> 05:22:38.512
most vital changes that is in defence,

2966188008
05:22:38.513 --> 05:22:43.207
housing and justice for victims of abuse.

2117966566
05:22:43.208 --> 05:22:46.016
So firstly, I warmly welcome
the Armed Forces Covenant,

1035176984
05:22:46.017 --> 05:22:49.428
something the British Legion has
been calling for for over a decade

2314870899
05:22:49.429 --> 05:22:53.214
and is finally being delivered in
full by this Labour government.

832781398
05:22:53.215 --> 05:22:55.858
In the words of the Royal
British Legion itself,

3298320490
05:22:55.859 --> 05:22:59.169
our Armed Forces Covenant will
ensure that the needs of the Armed

143105158
05:22:59.171 --> 05:23:01.927
Forces community are considered
when making decisions.

897112070
05:23:01.928 --> 05:23:04.915
Where further, they go on
to say that they welcome

1187406755
05:23:04.916 --> 05:23:07.614
our decision to fully implement it in law.

2787065285
05:23:07.615 --> 05:23:12.558
This matters immensely, Madam
Chair, because it delivers directly

1693229818
05:23:12.559 --> 05:23:15.636
on our manifesto commitments
to our Armed services,

907120858
05:23:15.637 --> 05:23:19.207
because the brave men and women who
dedicate their lives to defend

995444890
05:23:19.208 --> 05:23:22.357
our country deserve far more
than just our gratitude.

2845762356
05:23:22.358 --> 05:23:25.664
They deserve the peace
of mind that whilst they

2602981199
05:23:25.665 --> 05:23:27.771
are serving our country around the world,

1044690607
05:23:27.772 --> 05:23:31.469
their families are safe
and secure, high quality homes.

3988332254
05:23:31.470 --> 05:23:37.110
Instead, the shocking legacy we inherited

2088695514
05:23:37.111 --> 05:23:41.408
between April 2022 and December 2023,

4237633837
05:23:41.409 --> 05:23:45.658
service family accommodation
fell into disrepair.

2797853674
05:23:45.659 --> 05:23:50.511
Over 20,000 heating failures
were reported in military homes.

3302688527
05:23:50.512 --> 05:23:54.909
Nearly 7000 properties completely lost

626572263
05:23:54.910 --> 05:23:58.554
hot water and more than 1100 families

1675471343
05:23:58.555 --> 05:24:00.561
were forced out of their homes entirely

916888057
05:24:00.561 --> 05:24:02.417
due to severe maintenance issues.

4028905761
05:24:02.418 --> 05:24:04.525
Is it any wonder, then, that the previous

3395109454
05:24:04.525 --> 05:24:07.558
government missed its military

2637229632
05:24:07.559 --> 05:24:10.659
recruitment targets every single
year they were in office?

2450549411
05:24:10.660 --> 05:24:15.413
If you cannot guarantee a soldier
that their child will not

3329308062
05:24:15.414 --> 05:24:18.412
grow up in a house without
a working heating system,

1897640310
05:24:18.413 --> 05:24:22.321
how can you expect them
to stay in the ranks?

3885782756
05:24:22.322 --> 05:24:26.221
That is why I welcome this
government's commitment to £9 billion

1186159968
05:24:27.108 --> 05:24:29.665
investment in defence housing
and the measures set

1603857444
05:24:29.666 --> 05:24:33.507
out in this bill to to establish
the Defence Housing Service

121362839
05:24:33.508 --> 05:24:36.559
and the generational renewal
of military housing,

1147537200
05:24:36.560 --> 05:24:40.210
which will see 9 in 10 military
homes modernised or graded.

1321788907
05:24:40.211 --> 05:24:42.960
The Royal British Legion
has rightly welcomed

1406011326
05:24:42.961 --> 05:24:44.414
the Defence Housing Service,

3941400363
05:24:44.415 --> 05:24:48.111
calling it crucial to ensuring that
armed forces personnel and their

3671593616
05:24:48.112 --> 05:24:51.421
families are provided with
the high quality housing they deserve.

284427462
05:24:51.422 --> 05:24:53.828
This strategy will directly
benefit our forces,

579161905
05:24:53.829 --> 05:24:58.113
including those living in
the 43 service accommodations

3568133687
05:24:58.114 --> 05:25:00.669
in my Paisley and Renfrewshire
South constituency,

1864355873
05:25:00.671 --> 05:25:05.005
something that is no less than our
personnel and their families deserve.

3020785212
05:25:05.006 --> 05:25:08.515
Secondly, Madam Chair, I strongly
welcome the protections for victims

1614749610
05:25:08.516 --> 05:25:13.415
of sexual harm and domestic abuse
contained within the bill.

1676643162
05:25:13.416 --> 05:25:16.073
Every single victim of sexual
harm deserves justice.

2728905957
05:25:16.108 --> 05:25:20.461
Yet for too long, the experiences of
too many victims have been ignored.

4294454602
05:25:20.462 --> 05:25:23.483
And this bill changes that.

2526469979
05:25:23.484 --> 05:25:26.894
By introducing a strict legal duty
on commanding officers to report

2725058731
05:25:26.895 --> 05:25:30.363
serious offences to civilian
authorities and the service police,

36528498
05:25:30.364 --> 05:25:32.522
we are ensuring that there can be no scope

2100079552
05:25:32.523 --> 05:25:35.113
for anyone to look the other way.

144246989
05:25:35.114 --> 05:25:36.970
We are ensuring that nobody can say,

264182746
05:25:36.971 --> 05:25:41.161
I did not know when those heinous
crimes have been committed.

3286689966
05:25:41.162 --> 05:25:44.361
This bill will give
the service police increased

3240691914
05:25:44.362 --> 05:25:47.110
powers for investigations,
the service courts,

3834031040
05:25:47.111 --> 05:25:49.758
more powers to deal with perpetrators

1977547547
05:25:49.760 --> 05:25:51.715
and improve the experience of victims.

2177613062
05:25:52.105 --> 05:25:56.161
Furthermore, by bringing our system
in line with the civilian sector,

3246410684
05:25:56.162 --> 05:25:59.360
introducing service, domestic
abuse protection orders,

51606336
05:25:59.361 --> 05:26:02.018
service stalking, protection orders,

3249667239
05:26:02.019 --> 05:26:05.662
strengthening sexual harm prevention
orders and sexual risk orders.

3893107736
05:26:05.663 --> 05:26:09.361
We are ensuring that we protect victims,

1192727386
05:26:09.362 --> 05:26:11.508
target predatory behaviour head on

1802571372
05:26:11.510 --> 05:26:14.662
and ensure that survivors
get the unwavering

550184090
05:26:14.663 --> 05:26:16.618
support and justice that they deserve.

2049042562
05:26:16.619 --> 05:26:20.261
Madam chair, this bill proves that
this Labour Government is cleaning

387925585
05:26:20.262 --> 05:26:23.111
up the legacy of neglect
left by the party opposite.

540613909
05:26:23.112 --> 05:26:25.715
We are getting on with
the task of building

3381654435
05:26:25.716 --> 05:26:27.221
a military fit for the future

3519320245
05:26:27.222 --> 05:26:31.026
and restoring dignity to our armed forces,

1119034490
05:26:31.028 --> 05:26:32.814
and I commend it to the House.

670934506
05:26:32.815 --> 05:26:34.269
>> Josh Babarinde thank you.

629656723
05:26:34.270 --> 05:26:36.764
>> Madam Chair.

2376182101
05:26:36.765 --> 05:26:42.015
I speak in support of amendment
88, tabled by my hon.

3958455512
05:26:42.016 --> 05:26:45.916
Friend the Member for Epsom
and Ewell, and that amendment amendment

2524359378
05:26:45.917 --> 05:26:48.475
would require the Secretary
of State to review how

3208959467
05:26:48.476 --> 05:26:52.858
former service personnel are communicated

4188358617
05:26:52.859 --> 05:26:54.813
with about their pension entitlements,

3299250840
05:26:54.814 --> 05:26:56.918
and I support that wholeheartedly,

162682991
05:26:56.918 --> 05:26:59.128
and I want to use my
remarks in relation to

4118141480
05:27:00.070 --> 05:27:02.176
this amendment as an opportunity to raise

588610132
05:27:02.177 --> 05:27:06.913
again in this chamber
an injustice that goes

1648065952
05:27:06.914 --> 05:27:09.711
far deeper than just communication,

1341241681
05:27:09.712 --> 05:27:13.967
but to the heart of what this
country owes its veterans.

1642197570
05:27:13.968 --> 05:27:18.363
And I want to share with the House
for the sixth or seventh time now,

88571177
05:27:18.364 --> 05:27:24.814
the story of legendary
Eastbourne and Pauline Cole.

4744905
05:27:24.815 --> 05:27:29.113
Pauline served as a staff
sergeant and served this country

1727278027
05:27:29.114 --> 05:27:33.970
with distinction during
the conflict in Aden.

968265503
05:27:33.971 --> 05:27:37.764
In the 60s, she suffered
solar skin damage,

3949910311
05:27:37.765 --> 05:27:42.714
resulting in cancer
and post-traumatic stress disorder.

2164754172
05:27:42.715 --> 05:27:47.018
As a direct result of her service
and after years of tribunals,

437454524
05:27:47.019 --> 05:27:53.563
the government recognised her
sacrifice and awarded her military

45456862
05:27:53.564 --> 05:27:58.161
compensation in the form of
a war disablement pension.

276968039
05:27:58.162 --> 05:28:00.216
Now, before receiving that compensation,

3632835596
05:28:03.066 --> 05:28:09.322
Pauline had been in receipt of
£76.96 a week in Pension Credit.

1184185037
05:28:09.323 --> 05:28:14.628
After receiving that
compensation, her Pension

1697152371
05:28:14.629 --> 05:28:18.361
Credit collapsed to just £ 9.23

239814279
05:28:18.362 --> 05:28:22.464
a week and that is because military
compensation is considered

3845952403
05:28:22.465 --> 05:28:25.515
as income for the purposes of
calculating Pension Credit,

2980263518
05:28:25.516 --> 05:28:30.218
even though it is the case that
compensation awarded in a civil

2351134510
05:28:32.069 --> 05:28:36.512
context is disregarded from
such calculations and indeed,

2089683304
05:28:36.513 --> 05:28:40.664
military compensation is disregarded
from Universal Credit calculations.

1198071138
05:28:40.665 --> 05:28:42.665
But Pension Credit it is not.

1385117290
05:28:42.666 --> 05:28:46.814
And so in this case,
the government gave with one

4194819939
05:28:46.815 --> 05:28:50.613
hand and took with
another, and as a result,

934859999
05:28:50.614 --> 05:28:56.063
Pauline was forced to seek
lower cost accommodation

2109848655
05:28:56.064 --> 05:28:58.362
and moved out of her Eastbourne home

474411495
05:28:58.363 --> 05:29:03.567
and to somewhere else in
the County of Sussex in

1858749336
05:29:03.568 --> 05:29:05.825
order to sustain herself
on that new income.

1206647095
05:29:07.112 --> 05:29:09.218
I raised this with the Pensions Minister.

468631688
05:29:09.219 --> 05:29:13.367
Pauline came with me to the DWP.

2068633566
05:29:13.368 --> 05:29:17.589
I have raised this in this chamber
at Prime Minister's questions,

1352184376
05:29:17.590 --> 05:29:23.412
and Pauline sat in the gallery
during the course of this,

3578135479
05:29:23.413 --> 05:29:25.069
and sadly she passed away a few.

2072356615
05:29:25.070 --> 05:29:29.418
A few months after having
to move in November 2025,

1298147052
05:29:29.419 --> 05:29:32.772
never having seen this issue corrected.

1869683969
05:29:32.773 --> 05:29:37.472
And so I've pledged to continue
this fight around pension,

2776665519
05:29:39.109 --> 05:29:41.865
communications and pensions
entitlement in her honour.

2046509698
05:29:44.113 --> 05:29:47.363
Together with her sons Simon
and Les Haffenden, now,

3464538884
05:29:47.364 --> 05:29:49.621
the Royal British Legion
has been very clear

1736181112
05:29:50.112 --> 05:29:52.018
that the current state of affairs is,

549955131
05:29:52.019 --> 05:29:57.524
in its view, a violation of
the Armed Forces Covenant.

3445291780
05:29:57.525 --> 05:30:02.764
Now, when I raised this injustice
with the government via the DWP,

2742306132
05:30:02.765 --> 05:30:07.566
they said that the government has
no plans to change this policy.

3490887120
05:30:07.567 --> 05:30:09.676
When I asked a w PQ on this matter around

3384780700
05:30:09.677 --> 05:30:12.913
what it would cost to exempt military

2724490320
05:30:12.914 --> 05:30:16.774
compensation from Pension Credit
entitlements, the answer was no.

1991111895
05:30:16.775 --> 05:30:18.860
Formal assessment has been made.

3714557697
05:30:18.861 --> 05:30:23.119
So the government says it
cannot afford to fix this,

1795316826
05:30:23.120 --> 05:30:28.173
but it has not undertaken to find
out what fixing it would even cost.

993852888
05:30:28.174 --> 05:30:32.272
The government cannot
hide behind affordability

2807311002
05:30:32.273 --> 05:30:35.877
when it has never looked at the price tag.

2106882048
05:30:35.878 --> 05:30:41.362
Now the government knows that it can
act differently because it has.

3699605934
05:30:41.363 --> 05:30:44.021
In relation to the Atherton
Review on LGBT veterans,

1455890629
05:30:44.022 --> 05:30:48.224
where the Minister confirmed
that compensation payments

770825725
05:30:48.225 --> 05:30:52.168
would be exempt from tax
and would not affect benefits.

3193117131
05:30:52.168 --> 05:30:53.122
And that is right.

1623217568
05:30:53.123 --> 05:30:56.074
So the government has
accepted the principle.

3572050040
05:30:56.075 --> 05:31:00.324
It just was not applied to Pauline
or thousands of veterans like her.

311797174
05:31:00.325 --> 05:31:05.570
It must be applied and it must
be communicated to all of them.

1221898264
05:31:05.571 --> 05:31:09.118
And so I conclude by
saying and urging, indeed,

1663933908
05:31:09.119 --> 05:31:13.913
the Minister to begin correcting this

405104257
05:31:13.914 --> 05:31:15.768
injustice by undertaking a financial

3513003393
05:31:17.117 --> 05:31:21.266
assessment of this change
and communicating that to

2323954870
05:31:21.267 --> 05:31:25.566
veterans in receipt of
the war Disablement pension.

2554106716
05:31:25.567 --> 05:31:29.118
And I urge him to meet with
me and with Pauline's son,

2855173972
05:31:29.119 --> 05:31:30.372
Simon and Les Haffenden,

3408583140
05:31:30.373 --> 05:31:34.379
who are continuing
the campaign to discuss provisions

3258382592
05:31:34.380 --> 05:31:38.275
to correct this injustice
before Report stage

2727773989
05:31:39.115 --> 05:31:41.625
occurs so that we can
ensure that no veteran ever

275127716
05:31:44.113 --> 05:31:46.319
again is penalised for
serving our country.

1116113100
05:31:46.320 --> 05:31:50.770
>> Luke Akehurst thank you, Madam Chair.

3173627598
05:31:50.771 --> 05:31:53.480
It's been a pleasure to serve
on the Select Committee

3025662463
05:31:53.481 --> 05:31:56.216
set up to scrutinise this
important legislation,

425980376
05:31:56.217 --> 05:32:00.375
which members will know renews
our mandate for a standing army,

2974429590
05:32:00.376 --> 05:32:05.013
as well as delivering important
strides on the covenant service,

3176455425
05:32:05.014 --> 05:32:06.467
housing and service justice.

544707645
05:32:06.468 --> 05:32:10.031
The thrust of my speech today will
be to speak against new clause two,

1607982418
05:32:10.032 --> 05:32:12.415
which I think was
an attempt by the opposition

2833359860
05:32:12.416 --> 05:32:14.615
to play a bit of a political

3451281950
05:32:14.617 --> 05:32:18.964
game over the timing of
the crucial defence investment plan.

2325251087
05:32:18.965 --> 05:32:22.371
Before that, may I first pay,
pay, pay tribute to the armed

2341229960
05:32:22.372 --> 05:32:25.078
forces community across my
North Durham constituency.

3571125103
05:32:25.079 --> 05:32:28.421
As I mentioned in my speech on
the Second Reading of this bill,

2731151638
05:32:28.422 --> 05:32:30.981
North Durham is home to
a large number of veterans

3387124369
05:32:32.075 --> 05:32:34.230
and families of current serving personnel.

4012122818
05:32:34.231 --> 05:32:35.785
As their member of Parliament.

511382597
05:32:35.786 --> 05:32:38.924
I want to use my voice to stand
up for those people in our

2297843606
05:32:38.925 --> 05:32:41.632
community who are serving
or have served our country,

418952202
05:32:41.633 --> 05:32:45.200
which is why I was so keen to play
a role in the passage of this bill.

3617451560
05:32:45.201 --> 05:32:48.311
The Select Committee also allowed
me to highlight the work of

2053203518
05:32:48.311 --> 05:32:51.820
the Combined Cadet Force at
Parkview School in Chapel Street.

2887564576
05:32:51.821 --> 05:32:56.572
I welcome the provisions of the bill
to better integrate cadets into our

2146326910
05:32:56.573 --> 05:33:00.629
armed forces by transforming
the reserve Forces and Cadets Association,

3786600994
05:33:00.630 --> 05:33:08.966
Reserve Reserve Forces and Cadets
Association into a non-departmental

3903723772
05:33:08.967 --> 05:33:11.073
public body moving to nuclear clause two.

1775980638
05:33:11.074 --> 05:33:12.780
I'd like to think there's no one.

662796449
05:33:12.781 --> 05:33:14.737
With the possible exception of my hon.

695018215
05:33:14.738 --> 05:33:18.021
Friends, the Ministers at MoD,
who wants the Defence Investment

1300972169
05:33:18.022 --> 05:33:20.632
plan known as the dip, to
be tabled more than I do.

1107406697
05:33:20.633 --> 05:33:23.226
As I said in the defence
estimates debate held

3719212676
05:33:23.227 --> 05:33:25.978
in this place on the 4th
of March to my hon.

2531243541
05:33:25.979 --> 05:33:29.823
Friend the Minister of State for
Defence Readiness and Industry.

340734635
05:33:30.076 --> 05:33:33.370
My message to the Minister
is to take back into

1058259398
05:33:33.371 --> 05:33:35.477
the Whitehall system the supports on both

974657828
05:33:35.478 --> 05:33:37.635
sides of this House for seeing the Defence

3474502662
05:33:37.636 --> 05:33:40.674
Investment Plan sooner rather than later.

1730062721
05:33:40.675 --> 05:33:44.172
We can't afford more delay
because every month we delay.

3928298034
05:33:44.173 --> 05:33:47.677
Now could be a month in just
a few years time that our

2041346496
05:33:47.678 --> 05:33:50.086
troops don't have
the right kit in their hands.

111917949
05:33:52.120 --> 05:33:54.579
In the event of a war with
a dangerous opponent.

1643013205
05:33:54.579 --> 05:33:58.484
As as a North East MP, I am also
aware the strong industrial case for

2872118634
05:33:58.485 --> 05:34:01.933
providing certainty in the footprint
of our defence spending so

2241027968
05:34:01.934 --> 05:34:04.390
that we can drive investment
towards communities

2522705076
05:34:04.391 --> 05:34:05.695
like the one I represent,

945404945
05:34:05.696 --> 05:34:08.656
where many of my constituents
are proud to travel to work,

1772671909
05:34:08.657 --> 05:34:11.173
making munitions for
the British armed forces

2209031591
05:34:11.174 --> 05:34:13.572
and our gallant allies in Ukraine,

326812377
05:34:13.573 --> 05:34:15.077
at Bay Systems in Washington,

4152841915
05:34:15.078 --> 05:34:18.637
or making essential components for
armoured vehicle programmes such as

3137448645
05:34:18.638 --> 05:34:22.147
the turrets for challenger three at
Pearson Engineering in Newcastle.

2779982746
05:34:22.148 --> 05:34:26.235
And my constituents also hope that
future MoD contracts will lead to

957985816
05:34:26.236 --> 05:34:27.990
the north east of England becoming

944843875
05:34:27.992 --> 05:34:29.948
a major centre for the space industry.

1132411648
05:34:29.949 --> 05:34:31.505
But we need to get this right.

3551139756
05:34:31.506 --> 05:34:32.359
We can only get.

2647358534
05:34:32.360 --> 05:34:35.179
We only have one shot at dealing with

1534418090
05:34:35.180 --> 05:34:37.572
the equipment implications of the SDR.

3593431586
05:34:37.573 --> 05:34:39.631
We do not have an infinite pot of money.

1116484962
05:34:39.632 --> 05:34:42.918
In fact, all of us know that
the state of the public finances

1371649429
05:34:42.918 --> 05:34:46.074
that this government
inherited in 2024 means that

3290067470
05:34:46.075 --> 05:34:49.423
the pot of money we have for
many pressing priorities,

2065391326
05:34:49.424 --> 05:34:53.524
including defence, is
decidedly and sadly finite.

2301877691
05:34:53.525 --> 05:34:56.936
So we must make the right decisions
on where to allocate resources.

2892620
05:34:56.936 --> 05:34:59.497
As I think I've now said
three times to the House,

3822284571
05:34:59.498 --> 05:35:02.433
the political commitment
of this Labour government

2181611470
05:35:02.434 --> 05:35:04.690
to finding the funding
for defence equipment

3152527164
05:35:04.691 --> 05:35:06.875
and procurement should not be doubted,

1806937326
05:35:06.876 --> 05:35:09.032
given the evidence that the early decision

959371790
05:35:09.033 --> 05:35:10.716
to cut the overseas development

3700568748
05:35:10.717 --> 05:35:14.017
Budget by half in order to
increase defence spending,

1731545955
05:35:14.018 --> 05:35:15.872
this was something extremely painful

2439700049
05:35:16.115 --> 05:35:18.221
and politically contentious given the aid

2624495393
05:35:18.222 --> 05:35:20.626
Budget is something close to the hearts

2729032971
05:35:20.627 --> 05:35:22.383
of many on this side of the House.

2502436920
05:35:22.385 --> 05:35:25.222
But it was the right thing
for the Labour government

1567265945
05:35:25.224 --> 05:35:27.380
to do and represents a historic commitment

1141287127
05:35:27.381 --> 05:35:29.587
to the largest increase
in defence spending

2295699716
05:35:29.588 --> 05:35:31.144
since the end of the Cold War.

3265911123
05:35:31.145 --> 05:35:34.256
Given this, no one should be in
any doubt of the preparedness

1326218454
05:35:34.257 --> 05:35:36.213
of this government to make the further

3214205326
05:35:36.214 --> 05:35:38.471
tough political decisions
to be to ensure we

3979258634
05:35:38.472 --> 05:35:40.528
properly fund the defence of the nation.

3253841124
05:35:40.529 --> 05:35:42.635
Indeed, I am hopeful that the publication

357189995
05:35:42.636 --> 05:35:45.725
of the DIP will actually come sooner

2791306855
05:35:45.726 --> 05:35:47.632
than the plan that new clause two was

2921362739
05:35:48.121 --> 05:35:50.025
trying to bounce the government into.

2428752049
05:35:50.026 --> 05:35:53.275
The Defence Secretary
confirmed yesterday that

1949651151
05:35:53.275 --> 05:35:56.423
in this House that the PM is determined

1967181123
05:35:56.424 --> 05:36:00.829
to publish the DIP before the NATO
summit, which starts on July the 7th.

3770327217
05:36:01.079 --> 05:36:04.493
The new clause two would leave this
plan until the end of the year,

716256774
05:36:04.494 --> 05:36:07.470
because that's when this bill
will complete its passage.

2017295821
05:36:07.471 --> 05:36:09.827
The Conservatives lost
the political and moral

3717282910
05:36:09.828 --> 05:36:13.224
right to dictate dictate timetables on

2229690107
05:36:13.225 --> 05:36:15.181
how we best prepare for conflict after

3767270721
05:36:15.182 --> 05:36:17.523
the British people
rejected them from office.

1276819862
05:36:17.524 --> 05:36:21.176
Following over a decade of tragic
underfunding of our armed forces.

327799449
05:36:21.177 --> 05:36:23.584
Indeed, in their very
first year of government,

3901298845
05:36:23.585 --> 05:36:26.725
the party opposite cut defence
spending by £2 billion.

4692565
05:36:26.726 --> 05:36:30.678
In stark contrast to this government,
which is spending over 11 billion

212563326
05:36:31.084 --> 05:36:35.374
more on defence now than in the last
year of the previous government.

2616295306
05:36:35.375 --> 05:36:38.329
Rather than tacking
a timetable on this bill,

3054658310
05:36:38.331 --> 05:36:40.438
a bill which will play a hugely important

117708577
05:36:40.439 --> 05:36:44.100
role in improving how the state delivers
for our armed forces community,

2319150145
05:36:44.101 --> 05:36:46.608
I will be supporting
the government in publishing

2582998906
05:36:46.609 --> 05:36:48.767
a well thought out DIP that is not rushed,

1882316742
05:36:48.768 --> 05:36:50.674
but is published as soon as possible,

1255204433
05:36:50.675 --> 05:36:52.931
so we can start directing
investment towards

2963156947
05:36:52.932 --> 05:36:55.140
the industries that
will play a key role in

1032793602
05:36:55.141 --> 05:36:59.431
defending our nation in the coming years.

2790751514
05:36:59.432 --> 05:37:01.338
>> Sarah Bool thank you, Madam Chair.

3459347988
05:37:01.339 --> 05:37:03.798
And firstly, I'd just like
to start by saying it

1916025133
05:37:03.799 --> 05:37:06.157
was a pleasure to serve
on the Bill committee,

2641881950
05:37:06.158 --> 05:37:08.774
and I want to thank the clerks and all

4279505363
05:37:08.775 --> 05:37:10.682
of those who made it run so smoothly.

4266989275
05:37:10.683 --> 05:37:14.346
Now, today, I'm just going to focus
on one particular area, and I quote,

473894641
05:37:14.347 --> 05:37:18.522
I certainly think it is bizarre
that there is not an English

749279709
05:37:18.523 --> 05:37:22.722
commissioner that is 85%
of veteran population,

2670246316
05:37:22.724 --> 05:37:25.933
while the other 15% have three
commissioners to represent them.

1469985312
05:37:25.934 --> 05:37:27.538
I would certainly support that.

1525849711
05:37:27.539 --> 05:37:30.632
Now, those are not my words,
but those of Lieutenant

1595065856
05:37:30.632 --> 05:37:32.336
Commander retired Susan Hamilton,

1467140198
05:37:32.337 --> 05:37:34.478
the Veterans Commissioner for Scotland,

662595858
05:37:34.479 --> 05:37:36.887
in response to a question
from the armed Forces

4177211751
05:37:36.888 --> 05:37:39.029
Minister in the Bill Committee earlier

2535183922
05:37:39.030 --> 05:37:41.037
this year as to whether there should be

4028864873
05:37:41.121 --> 05:37:42.975
a Veterans Commissioner for England,

2118159756
05:37:42.976 --> 05:37:48.034
a view shared by all three of
the commissioners for Northern Ireland,

891249464
05:37:48.035 --> 05:37:51.824
Wales and Scotland together
is that the circa 1.4

2445446813
05:37:51.825 --> 05:37:54.855
million veterans who live
in the UK in England

197102022
05:37:54.856 --> 05:37:56.760
lack their own veterans commissioner,

3683177471
05:37:57.121 --> 05:38:01.432
but they believe it is
vital that we have parity

3129906738
05:38:01.433 --> 05:38:03.237
and consistency across the nations.

3741650681
05:38:03.238 --> 05:38:08.572
And an independent statutory
advocate for veterans in England.

2055613757
05:38:08.573 --> 05:38:11.633
So today I raised once more
the call for a National Veterans

1051573997
05:38:11.635 --> 05:38:14.024
Commissioner for England
via new clause three.

2269505000
05:38:14.025 --> 05:38:14.978
>> Which could be.

2408100658
05:38:14.979 --> 05:38:15.731
At this point.

1677145192
05:38:15.732 --> 05:38:17.288
>> Of course, I will give way.

3372314544
05:38:17.289 --> 05:38:19.275
>> I do thank you for giving way and

103007228
05:38:19.276 --> 05:38:21.279
I apologise for interrupting the flow.

2753224314
05:38:21.280 --> 05:38:21.530
The.

4151373429
05:38:21.531 --> 05:38:23.677
The point about consistency across all

3170234564
05:38:23.678 --> 05:38:25.483
the UK is really, really important,

2660595762
05:38:25.484 --> 05:38:28.945
and I do support the creation of
that veterans Minister for England,

3281018369
05:38:28.946 --> 05:38:32.456
of course, but in Scotland the role
is particularly important because

1616884826
05:38:32.457 --> 05:38:35.767
our veterans Minister in
the government is not a veteran himself.

2471004000
05:38:35.768 --> 05:38:37.122
He is a career politician.

2366680162
05:38:37.123 --> 05:38:40.787
I think he moved from being working
for the party to working for an MSP.

952527915
05:38:40.788 --> 05:38:42.695
So so that that is a really important

2226173172
05:38:42.696 --> 05:38:44.552
role in Scotland to bridge that gap.

2027691353
05:38:44.553 --> 05:38:47.814
But does she join me in encouraging
the SNP government to create

3219634453
05:38:47.815 --> 05:38:51.576
a veterans Minister who is
himself or herself a veteran?

3751759742
05:38:51.577 --> 05:38:53.132
>> Sarah Bool I thank the hon.

1905328489
05:38:53.133 --> 05:38:55.737
Member for his intervention and of course,

1541592721
05:38:55.738 --> 05:38:58.245
all experience of military
life is very valuable.

4219057627
05:38:58.246 --> 05:39:01.805
I would say without someone, with
someone without military experience,

3018166810
05:39:01.806 --> 05:39:04.465
I still think there is
something that can be brought

1181979103
05:39:04.466 --> 05:39:06.674
to the table for those
who don't have that,

1191806639
05:39:06.675 --> 05:39:09.337
but I do, I do, I do take
the point that he's noted.

1466323914
05:39:09.338 --> 05:39:11.445
I'm sure that they would have heard that,

2861842127
05:39:11.446 --> 05:39:13.303
and that could be put on the record.

3310360392
05:39:13.304 --> 05:39:16.915
Now, taking a step back, the Royal
British Legion launched the campaign

656484897
05:39:16.916 --> 05:39:20.377
to create the role of veterans
commissioner in England back in 2023,

2052504794
05:39:20.378 --> 05:39:23.837
the last conservative government
accepted that request, and in 2024,

3325080159
05:39:23.838 --> 05:39:27.197
the office for Veterans Affairs
began recruiting for the position.

365197331
05:39:27.198 --> 05:39:30.485
However, the 2024 general
election was called shortly

3642795777
05:39:30.486 --> 05:39:32.490
afterwards and all progress was ceased.

1522715029
05:39:32.492 --> 05:39:34.281
Now, in the Bill committee,

1848367558
05:39:34.282 --> 05:39:37.732
the response to this request
was to say, well, look,

2455171031
05:39:37.733 --> 05:39:40.383
we have an armed forces commissioner now,

4284382550
05:39:40.385 --> 05:39:44.482
and alongside this means
this role is not required.

3469316571
05:39:44.483 --> 05:39:47.329
But firstly, we do welcome Commodore Polly

317270434
05:39:47.331 --> 05:39:49.626
Perkins CBE to be the first holder of

389279147
05:39:49.627 --> 05:39:51.783
the role of the Armed Forces Commissioner,

3729289063
05:39:53.131 --> 05:39:54.989
and I do wish her well in this role.

1271412001
05:39:54.990 --> 05:39:58.186
However, this particular
role has been created to

519390768
05:39:58.188 --> 05:40:00.493
benefit serving personnel
and their families.

208392876
05:40:00.494 --> 05:40:03.945
It would investigate general welfare
matters in the armed Forces,

1294223775
05:40:03.946 --> 05:40:07.244
abolishing the office of
the Service Complaints Ombudsman,

1300510885
05:40:07.245 --> 05:40:09.750
and transferring its
functions and responsibility

2299150328
05:40:09.751 --> 05:40:13.780
to the newly established Commissioner

2216503711
05:40:13.781 --> 05:40:17.040
so veterans would only fall under
the Armed Forces Commissioner,

1072779659
05:40:17.041 --> 05:40:19.649
where a veterans complaint
relates to their time in

2645859826
05:40:19.650 --> 05:40:22.208
service and when they were
subject to service law.

1683307749
05:40:22.209 --> 05:40:24.565
There are, however, time
limits for submitting

2177987368
05:40:24.566 --> 05:40:26.571
a complaint and therefore only veterans

2547629192
05:40:26.572 --> 05:40:29.342
who have recently left
the armed forces will

3190745073
05:40:29.343 --> 05:40:31.347
generally fall within those provisions.

1559371331
05:40:31.347 --> 05:40:34.636
Now, in terms of valour, we
recognise the government's

375466654
05:40:34.637 --> 05:40:36.528
50 million funding for valour,

3046527937
05:40:36.529 --> 05:40:38.734
the national programme
designed to increase

2865490911
05:40:38.735 --> 05:40:42.126
veterans access to relevant charities,

1686055111
05:40:42.127 --> 05:40:43.932
services and support across the UK.

541402986
05:40:44.121 --> 05:40:47.982
However, if valour was
the answer to all veterans issues,

525105658
05:40:47.983 --> 05:40:50.090
then why is the position of the veterans?

1202919135
05:40:50.091 --> 05:40:53.347
Commissioners remained for Northern
Ireland, Scotland and Wales?

2462893178
05:40:53.349 --> 05:40:55.555
There is still fundamental
value in forming

1315308101
05:40:55.556 --> 05:40:57.109
this Commissioner for England.

66769017
05:40:57.110 --> 05:41:01.685
Two it shouldn't be a question
of either or, but both.

744418108
05:41:01.686 --> 05:41:03.942
Now what would
the Veterans Commissioner do?

2095437217
05:41:03.943 --> 05:41:06.350
Well, it would serve as
an independent advocate

1366468031
05:41:06.351 --> 05:41:08.757
and voice for veterans
and families in England.

1745175863
05:41:08.758 --> 05:41:12.579
It would signpost veterans
and their families to relevant

886594085
05:41:12.579 --> 05:41:16.038
charities and services based
on their individual needs.

3791182842
05:41:16.039 --> 05:41:19.985
It would produce regular policy
recommendations based on unmet need.

3489199912
05:41:19.986 --> 05:41:22.871
It would work closely
with government agencies

2917993869
05:41:22.872 --> 05:41:25.240
to develop and refine
policies and services,

3828094220
05:41:25.240 --> 05:41:27.696
and it would promote the community,

2486188043
05:41:27.697 --> 05:41:29.501
leveraging their skills and hiring,

471469967
05:41:30.090 --> 05:41:32.145
highlighting what they offer to society.

595355720
05:41:32.146 --> 05:41:34.604
In addition, this role
would actually be able to

462958494
05:41:34.605 --> 05:41:38.983
assist with the Armed
Forces Covenant Extension.

2816616870
05:41:38.984 --> 05:41:41.482
Now, in terms of
the Armed Forces Covenant,

1334201234
05:41:41.483 --> 05:41:43.740
one of the most critiqued
aspects of that is

1451852676
05:41:43.742 --> 05:41:45.747
that it is currently poorly signposted,

2825235250
05:41:45.748 --> 05:41:49.381
inconsistently enforced,
and compliance significantly

2520342284
05:41:49.382 --> 05:41:50.886
varies from region to region.

1135483951
05:41:50.887 --> 05:41:53.344
And speaking to service
personnel, the issue is,

3651344131
05:41:53.345 --> 05:41:56.638
is that many are really not
aware of what it offers,

2500472955
05:41:56.639 --> 05:41:59.880
and in reality, they don't feel
the genuine value from it.

2811208605
05:41:59.881 --> 05:42:03.190
The enforcement is therefore
an absolutely key issue, and indeed,

125379324
05:42:03.191 --> 05:42:05.600
that very point was made
last year in the House

28605294
05:42:05.601 --> 05:42:07.907
of Commons Defence
Committee in their report,

848888864
05:42:07.908 --> 05:42:10.367
which stated it wasn't
an issue about how it was

772622191
05:42:10.368 --> 05:42:12.724
legislated or the nature
of services provided,

3057515529
05:42:12.725 --> 05:42:15.184
but how it was enforced
and how it was provided.

2211010565
05:42:15.185 --> 05:42:19.582
Now, given that
the government does seem content

2544525000
05:42:19.583 --> 05:42:22.332
to expand the role
and extent of the covenant,

12055190
05:42:22.333 --> 05:42:25.341
we should welcome the role of
veterans Commissioner because

2554121656
05:42:25.342 --> 05:42:28.834
it would play a crucial
role in accountability,

590134315
05:42:28.835 --> 05:42:31.090
monitoring the implementation
and the impact

623041286
05:42:31.091 --> 05:42:33.879
of that extended covenant duty.

2950676344
05:42:33.880 --> 05:42:36.637
Equally, the commissioner
could also play an important

1528833141
05:42:36.638 --> 05:42:39.079
role in implementing
the veterans strategy,

2367148602
05:42:39.079 --> 05:42:43.878
with its three core aims to
celebrate, contribute and support.

873551468
05:42:43.879 --> 05:42:46.388
And it could also play
a really important role in

1880060038
05:42:46.389 --> 05:42:48.882
coordinating responses
of the Veterans Advisory

3689113278
05:42:48.883 --> 05:42:51.933
and Pensions Committee
across England to provide

2580963135
05:42:51.934 --> 05:42:54.632
local outreach
and independent coordination.

2259799943
05:42:54.633 --> 05:42:56.889
The Veterans Advisory
and Pension Committees

1135031272
05:42:56.890 --> 05:42:58.628
are an underutilised resource,

3178862374
05:42:58.629 --> 05:43:01.686
and coordination of these by
the Veterans Commissioner could

2267673606
05:43:01.688 --> 05:43:04.194
really support efforts to
enhance their efficacy.

1562354487
05:43:04.195 --> 05:43:07.503
The Commissioner could use this
network through regular reporting

1049934796
05:43:07.504 --> 05:43:11.488
to identify trends and evidence
presenting these findings.

3042899263
05:43:11.489 --> 05:43:16.287
It is the Royal British Legion's
recommendation that the UK government

2283108309
05:43:16.288 --> 05:43:18.994
should introduce a Veterans
Commissioner for England,

3818397020
05:43:18.995 --> 05:43:21.100
ensuring that veterans and their families

3456016523
05:43:21.101 --> 05:43:23.579
know who to turn to for advocacy

3131976744
05:43:23.581 --> 05:43:27.381
and to campaign and champion their
needs at the heart of government.

1929827634
05:43:27.382 --> 05:43:31.390
I would strongly urge
the government to listen.

3503153509
05:43:31.391 --> 05:43:31.942
Thank you.

733051645
05:43:31.943 --> 05:43:36.185
>> Rachel Taylor thank you
very much, Madam Chair.

2623446159
05:43:36.186 --> 05:43:40.431
It was also an honour to serve
on the Armed Forces Bill,

376920678
05:43:40.432 --> 05:43:43.980
Select Committee and help
deliver on our General Election

2935444348
05:43:43.981 --> 05:43:47.030
promise to extend the Armed
Forces Covenant to every

27333930
05:43:47.031 --> 05:43:50.232
area of government to better
support Armed forces,

1659523576
05:43:50.233 --> 05:43:53.484
personnel and veterans, and
I was delighted to be joined

779608361
05:43:53.485 --> 05:43:57.882
by so many veterans with
experience on that committee,

1744321182
05:43:57.883 --> 05:43:59.287
particularly the right hon.

1098222698
05:43:59.288 --> 05:44:00.992
Member for Rayleigh and Wickford.

4022245280
05:44:02.130 --> 05:44:04.035
The Member for Halesowen North Devon,

3860763676
05:44:04.036 --> 05:44:09.587
Selly Oak and South Ribble
and also Solihull West and Shirley.

677980498
05:44:09.588 --> 05:44:15.688
If I'm correct, I don't want
to upset my, my the hon.

2424893510
05:44:16.129 --> 05:44:20.729
Member, who is almost
a neighbour, their their input

4174488902
05:44:20.730 --> 05:44:22.935
into that committee was
extremely valuable,

438664761
05:44:22.936 --> 05:44:28.929
and I feel that the work we
were able to do across party

1504254087
05:44:28.930 --> 05:44:33.089
with with good temper was
was extremely valuable.

3499952152
05:44:33.090 --> 05:44:37.188
And, and I really sort of think that
the time spent was, was worthwhile.

2371425101
05:44:37.189 --> 05:44:41.358
It was also extremely helpful
as the the right hon.

3714674606
05:44:42.128 --> 05:44:44.885
Member for Rayleigh
and Wickford has already mentioned

1556943919
05:44:48.129 --> 05:44:50.085
to visit the Veterans and Armed Forces

3188849782
05:44:50.086 --> 05:44:55.987
housing and also to meet
with the members of

345339627
05:44:55.988 --> 05:44:58.585
the the the Armed Forces Justice Scheme.

929044341
05:44:58.586 --> 05:45:00.190
And that was extremely helpful.

2830368686
05:45:00.191 --> 05:45:02.801
And we were able to ask
them a number of questions.

1578449097
05:45:02.802 --> 05:45:05.429
And whilst our recollections
of some of those

4012997457
05:45:05.430 --> 05:45:07.183
conversations may slightly differ,

715364928
05:45:07.184 --> 05:45:12.483
it was still extremely useful
to see how that system worked

1904691461
05:45:12.484 --> 05:45:15.834
in contrast to how our
non-military justice system works.

1174164818
05:45:15.835 --> 05:45:18.678
Now, I welcome this
government's commitment

1183137518
05:45:18.679 --> 05:45:20.836
to placing a legal duty on public services

3729472829
05:45:21.132 --> 05:45:23.087
to consider the circumstances of armed

3785112520
05:45:23.088 --> 05:45:25.635
forces personnel and their families.

979477189
05:45:25.636 --> 05:45:28.936
My constituents want to see
veterans supported and those

1872270911
05:45:28.936 --> 05:45:33.099
who serve able to do
so with dignity and respect.

1169403283
05:45:33.100 --> 05:45:35.887
We were elected to renew our armed forces,

2069068550
05:45:35.888 --> 05:45:38.432
and this bill delivers on that promise.

1821684041
05:45:38.433 --> 05:45:41.885
It was encouraging to hear
evidence from representatives

1431042721
05:45:41.886 --> 05:45:43.682
of armed forces charities,

3793834024
05:45:43.683 --> 05:45:45.336
the Service Families Federation,

1432810952
05:45:46.129 --> 05:45:49.186
officials from the Service Justice
System and personnel from

3024188890
05:45:49.188 --> 05:45:53.582
across the Armed Forces
and the Ministry of Defence.

2755220396
05:45:53.583 --> 05:45:58.633
They all recognise the importance of
the changes we are making to turn

2266838421
05:45:58.635 --> 05:46:02.237
the tide after years of underinvestment
by the party opposite.

4008650809
05:46:02.238 --> 05:46:06.388
Our armed forces are
a source of national pride,

3584355649
05:46:06.389 --> 05:46:08.736
and I want younger generations to see

1536832787
05:46:08.737 --> 05:46:11.235
the armed forces as
a future for themselves

319932779
05:46:11.236 --> 05:46:15.338
and an opportunity to do
more for their country,

2765861742
05:46:15.339 --> 05:46:20.490
contributing to the security of our
nation to make this a reality,

4084674054
05:46:20.490 --> 05:46:22.936
armed forces personnel and their families

3234462685
05:46:22.936 --> 05:46:26.136
need our full support and respect

2484463810
05:46:26.137 --> 05:46:30.743
as they make daily sacrifices in
their service to our country.

3043682785
05:46:30.744 --> 05:46:33.385
That's why I am pleased that after years

2856610647
05:46:33.386 --> 05:46:35.784
of military families forced to deal with

1048337556
05:46:35.785 --> 05:46:39.783
the lowest level of
satisfaction with service

2650114318
05:46:39.784 --> 05:46:41.387
family accommodation on record,

1567530271
05:46:41.388 --> 05:46:47.033
we have bought 36,000 family homes
back into public ownership,

2027741737
05:46:47.034 --> 05:46:51.836
with the savings being reinvested
into fixing and improving forces.

924399529
05:46:51.837 --> 05:46:53.834
>> Housing with the hon.

1728425638
05:46:53.835 --> 05:46:54.135
Lady.

2322167309
05:46:54.136 --> 05:46:55.490
>> Yes, I'll give Pam Cox.

2709659101
05:46:55.492 --> 05:46:59.390
>> Thank you for giving
way in my constituency.

725465245
05:46:59.391 --> 05:47:01.296
Colchester, we have a thousand homes,

181421690
05:47:01.297 --> 05:47:03.654
nearly a thousand homes
that have been brought

1508337236
05:47:03.655 --> 05:47:06.493
back into public ownership
with the creation

2753786006
05:47:06.494 --> 05:47:08.582
of the Defence Housing Service.

88685578
05:47:08.583 --> 05:47:12.335
Would she agree with
me that new clause 13,

2388783984
05:47:12.336 --> 05:47:16.882
which addresses the question of
single living accommodation,

3440292973
05:47:16.882 --> 05:47:19.289
threatens to undermine
that new Defence Housing

2053122541
05:47:19.290 --> 05:47:21.647
Service before it's really
got off the ground,

1334288357
05:47:21.648 --> 05:47:24.805
and that although single living
accommodation needs attention,

3967677894
05:47:24.806 --> 05:47:28.316
that that attention should be given
within the armed forces umbrella.

2234981050
05:47:28.317 --> 05:47:29.994
>> I thank the my hon.

1182367793
05:47:29.995 --> 05:47:33.986
Friend for her valuable intervention
and her experience with

693674759
05:47:33.987 --> 05:47:37.985
so many military families
living in her constituency.

4072961310
05:47:37.986 --> 05:47:42.537
I, I agree with with
her that new clause 13

185337030
05:47:42.538 --> 05:47:46.233
focuses on single living accommodation,

1429839614
05:47:46.234 --> 05:47:49.033
which is often of
a relatively temporary nature,

2889540184
05:47:49.034 --> 05:47:53.936
whereas our focus really needs to
be on the catastrophic situation

1174850277
05:47:53.938 --> 05:47:59.041
within our family homes
up and down the country,

1486464463
05:47:59.042 --> 05:48:03.239
which we both saw on the on
the visit down, down south.

4093272342
05:48:03.240 --> 05:48:05.544
Service families deserve
high quality housing

249574118
05:48:05.546 --> 05:48:08.135
that meets military
operational requirements

2569073113
05:48:08.136 --> 05:48:14.833
while providing them with the comfort
they need to support their family.

3166554229
05:48:14.834 --> 05:48:17.691
This bill's establishment of
the Defence Housing Service

3974639710
05:48:17.692 --> 05:48:20.784
will go a long way to meeting these needs.

2719680998
05:48:20.785 --> 05:48:22.690
A generational renewal of over 40,000

3963831423
05:48:23.132 --> 05:48:25.136
military homes modernised and upgraded,

818798116
05:48:25.137 --> 05:48:28.338
together with a historic
programme of house building

3100159227
05:48:28.339 --> 05:48:30.646
with the potential for over 100,000

3564793216
05:48:30.647 --> 05:48:35.989
new homes on surplus defence land
for civilian and military families,

1780555959
05:48:38.132 --> 05:48:40.288
with serving personnel and veterans first.

3004495944
05:48:40.289 --> 05:48:42.887
The most significant plan in 50 years.

209983264
05:48:42.888 --> 05:48:46.038
A stark contrast to the scandal of

778899169
05:48:46.039 --> 05:48:49.334
the botched Tory privatisation that cost

3634710367
05:48:49.335 --> 05:48:51.240
us billions and let military families

2887102999
05:48:51.240 --> 05:48:53.097
down and left the country worse off.

2419484221
05:48:53.097 --> 05:48:56.645
It was a real eye opener to see
first hand the standard of

75274893
05:48:56.646 --> 05:48:59.603
accommodation military families
have been putting up with,

1009783649
05:48:59.604 --> 05:49:03.682
and the work needed to
make those properties

2508525465
05:49:03.683 --> 05:49:05.639
fit for our heroes and their families.

3517198914
05:49:05.640 --> 05:49:08.645
I'm immensely proud that in
this bill we stand by our

1774429506
05:49:09.132 --> 05:49:11.640
pledge to halve violence
against women and girls.

1697943564
05:49:12.135 --> 05:49:14.541
The service justice system
is being modernised,

939639804
05:49:14.542 --> 05:49:16.990
so it can provide better victim support

3413793926
05:49:16.990 --> 05:49:19.995
and ensure that the victims
of the most serious

4134349016
05:49:19.996 --> 05:49:22.833
offences have access to protection orders.

242316081
05:49:22.834 --> 05:49:27.501
Criminal behaviour does not
belong in our armed forces.

877192270
05:49:27.502 --> 05:49:31.443
The UK has a strong record for
cultivating the highest values

1098647659
05:49:31.444 --> 05:49:35.936
and standards in some of
the toughest conditions.

355015249
05:49:35.938 --> 05:49:38.094
We are bringing change to service justice,

3988962905
05:49:38.095 --> 05:49:40.100
creating a victim centred approach that

515377454
05:49:40.101 --> 05:49:42.307
will support personnel
that are the victims

2527346690
05:49:42.308 --> 05:49:44.936
of unacceptable sexual assault,

1498603819
05:49:44.936 --> 05:49:48.838
domestic abuse, stalking and harassment in

1012977375
05:49:48.839 --> 05:49:51.785
a period of significant
global instability.

2514088477
05:49:51.786 --> 05:49:53.692
Our commitment to the security of our

3890992046
05:49:54.136 --> 05:49:55.992
country requires us to invest in our

1637768062
05:49:55.993 --> 05:50:00.845
armed forces so that we can combat
any challenges we as a country face.

1330262563
05:50:00.846 --> 05:50:05.137
Part of that has to be about
expanding our reserve forces.

3722068874
05:50:05.138 --> 05:50:08.288
Individuals, including
members of this House,

2511725223
05:50:08.289 --> 05:50:11.892
use their free time to make up
an integral part of our armed forces,

3838019571
05:50:11.893 --> 05:50:14.501
and I am incredibly proud
when constituents of mine

908714418
05:50:14.502 --> 05:50:18.960
tell me that they are
part of our reserves.

2728367832
05:50:18.961 --> 05:50:21.769
Bedworth, in my constituency,
hosts the largest and one

1658783599
05:50:21.770 --> 05:50:26.442
of the most famous Armistice
Day parades in Britain,

4215540589
05:50:26.443 --> 05:50:29.244
held always on the 11th
day of the 11th month.

2227798896
05:50:29.245 --> 05:50:33.949
We truly are a town that never forgets,

2500180440
05:50:33.950 --> 05:50:35.607
and I want to pay tribute to all

549117421
05:50:35.608 --> 05:50:37.664
the veterans and service personnel in my

4193382295
05:50:37.665 --> 05:50:42.139
constituency of North Warwickshire
and Bedworth and all of

2660512109
05:50:42.140 --> 05:50:45.340
those who work in the defence
industry supply chains.

2168320505
05:50:45.341 --> 05:50:50.292
My constituents are proud that this
Labour Government is backing our

47528687
05:50:50.293 --> 05:50:54.586
armed forces and improving
the lives of our country's bravest,

2717888594
05:50:54.587 --> 05:50:56.742
while putting our nation's security first.

1519977644
05:50:57.136 --> 05:50:59.796
I will continue to do what
I can to support military

3996893130
05:50:59.797 --> 05:51:02.002
families and veterans
from my constituency,

616064673
05:51:02.136 --> 05:51:04.143
and I recommend this bill to the House.

526904322
05:51:04.144 --> 05:51:08.146
But before I wind up,
I also want to put on

3489373003
05:51:08.147 --> 05:51:12.390
record at the start of Pride Month how

1304083338
05:51:12.391 --> 05:51:16.091
proud I am to have seen the LGBT financial

2386625906
05:51:16.092 --> 05:51:21.439
recognition scheme implemented here.

2388779413
05:51:21.440 --> 05:51:25.837
With a £75 million investment
and the the Memorial,

2467762544
05:51:25.838 --> 05:51:31.546
an open letter dedicated and unveiled
by the King in October 2025.

35388626
05:51:31.547 --> 05:51:34.289
I would recommend everyone in this House

3368061386
05:51:34.290 --> 05:51:37.789
and across the country to make a visit

4134746759
05:51:37.790 --> 05:51:41.335
to the National Memorial Arboretum to see

869117633
05:51:41.336 --> 05:51:43.142
that it is a very powerful reminder

3911688129
05:51:43.143 --> 05:51:45.790
of the absolute injustice that was done

3227237410
05:51:45.791 --> 05:51:49.037
to hard working service personnel

3135662826
05:51:49.038 --> 05:51:54.943
who were serving their country first
to the best of their ability.

3142634268
05:51:54.944 --> 05:51:55.445
Yes, yes.

202962012
05:51:57.138 --> 05:51:57.840
>> Ian Roome.

2401981637
05:51:57.841 --> 05:51:59.195
>> Thank you, Madam Chair.

1102614200
05:51:59.196 --> 05:52:02.936
It was a pleasure to be a member of
the Armed Forces Bill Committee,

3213710539
05:52:02.936 --> 05:52:05.586
and it is also an honour
to be able to speak

191036221
05:52:05.587 --> 05:52:08.787
on the Armed Forces
Bill for a second time.

506330768
05:52:08.788 --> 05:52:10.240
To this government's credit,

977628942
05:52:10.242 --> 05:52:15.392
this bill responds to
a number of key challenges.

3360100457
05:52:15.393 --> 05:52:18.742
Are our armed forces face in the 2020s.

2030504715
05:52:18.743 --> 05:52:23.243
However, today I want to argue
the case for new clause 13,

2203795837
05:52:23.244 --> 05:52:25.550
something the Liberal
Democrats pushed for in

2636832200
05:52:25.551 --> 05:52:28.943
committee and a cause
very close to my heart,

1660416537
05:52:28.944 --> 05:52:32.151
the need to give every member
of our armed forces a safe,

79206177
05:52:32.153 --> 05:52:35.289
decent home, whatever their
family circumstances.

190281816
05:52:35.290 --> 05:52:39.541
Some who serve live in single
accommodation for decades,

755705527
05:52:40.136 --> 05:52:41.841
you know, for their whole career.

1043790544
05:52:41.842 --> 05:52:45.793
Not everyone chooses to
be in a relationship,

2526025314
05:52:45.793 --> 05:52:48.088
and many also go and live in single

2315758159
05:52:48.089 --> 05:52:52.147
living accommodation away from their
wives and go home at the weekend.

1515900465
05:52:52.148 --> 05:52:55.291
So sometimes it's there
for the whole career,

2714933867
05:52:55.292 --> 05:52:58.945
not just to a stepping
stone until they find

543184297
05:52:58.946 --> 05:53:05.793
a partner and then move
on into into quarters.

3397991300
05:53:05.794 --> 05:53:09.091
The Secretary of State has
promised the biggest renewal

3425334110
05:53:09.092 --> 05:53:13.044
of armed forces housing
in more than 50 years.

2736436436
05:53:13.046 --> 05:53:15.895
To echo his words, the last British forces

803551664
05:53:15.896 --> 05:53:19.443
personnel deserve is a decent home.

3957476552
05:53:19.444 --> 05:53:23.897
Last year, the government rightly
agreed with our party that

2810849848
05:53:23.898 --> 05:53:26.956
armed forces housing should meet
the decent homes standards,

3109326649
05:53:26.957 --> 05:53:29.264
and it was encouraging
to see that commitment

962940663
05:53:29.265 --> 05:53:34.952
make its way into
the Renters Right Act 2025.

1493935178
05:53:34.953 --> 05:53:38.496
However, there are two types of
armed forces housing service,

3313155284
05:53:40.136 --> 05:53:45.893
family accommodation
and single living accommodation.

4130757535
05:53:45.894 --> 05:53:49.892
In 2021, the Public Accounts
Committee estimated that

2220661124
05:53:49.893 --> 05:53:52.539
the latter may support
as many as 8000 people.

992105131
05:53:52.540 --> 05:53:57.339
More than half of our armed
forces personnel at that time,

2066286484
05:53:57.340 --> 05:54:01.254
more than a third of the armed
forces personnel were to believed to

940127425
05:54:01.255 --> 05:54:03.744
be living in the poorest grade of service

444307143
05:54:03.745 --> 05:54:07.990
housing and 3% in accommodation

2968203002
05:54:07.990 --> 05:54:11.041
so poor that they were
exempt from paying rent.

140853395
05:54:11.042 --> 05:54:15.701
The Renters Rights Act misses out single

1906066126
05:54:15.702 --> 05:54:17.556
living accommodation in section 101.

1359372385
05:54:19.139 --> 05:54:22.891
Despite many new recruits being
young and too much of the defence

3530399540
05:54:22.892 --> 05:54:27.443
housing estate being in
a shocking state of repair,

645695855
05:54:27.444 --> 05:54:32.803
this amendment is our opportunity
to begin to fix that.

2294080460
05:54:32.804 --> 05:54:36.013
I speak from personal experience,
having lived in single living

2667249397
05:54:37.139 --> 05:54:39.797
accommodation myself as
I still wet behind the ears.

2726685105
05:54:40.141 --> 05:54:45.335
Young airman Porter to
Braunton block at then RAF

2786540623
05:54:45.336 --> 05:54:47.493
Chivenor in North Devon in the late 1980s.

3515732527
05:54:47.494 --> 05:54:49.845
Now RMB Chivenor a Royal Marine base.

355616932
05:54:49.846 --> 05:54:54.805
The way, the nicest way I can
describe it is to say it was basic,

1451927356
05:54:56.139 --> 05:54:59.953
but before family life happened,
it was home to me and my mates.

2719539092
05:54:59.954 --> 05:55:03.990
For at least two years I was at Chivenor.

1571235207
05:55:03.992 --> 05:55:07.849
My room on the base is still there
and whichever Royal Marine has it

1797500843
05:55:07.850 --> 05:55:13.443
today has every right to be housed
somewhere without mould or damp.

1666589822
05:55:13.444 --> 05:55:15.199
While they serve king and country.

3929150873
05:55:15.200 --> 05:55:21.143
By the time the next Armed Forces
Bill comes before this House in 2031,

3492666208
05:55:21.144 --> 05:55:24.644
we must ensure that
the shameful findings of the last

2194704897
05:55:24.645 --> 05:55:27.746
Service Accommodation report
are a thing of the past,

1508754168
05:55:27.747 --> 05:55:32.556
something I believe this government
is trying and attempting to fix.

3907123031
05:55:35.140 --> 05:55:38.539
As we saw saw on our service
on the committee visits.

2863640000
05:55:38.540 --> 05:55:42.539
As such, the Armed Forces
Bill should specify

2199378971
05:55:42.540 --> 05:55:44.194
that wherever the phrase service

4174390131
05:55:44.195 --> 05:55:48.940
family accommodation appears relating
to the standard of forces housing,

50524867
05:55:48.941 --> 05:55:53.842
this should be amended to also
cover single living accommodation

3995905622
05:55:53.843 --> 05:55:58.596
and any Ministry of Defence building
being used for that purpose.

1568270308
05:56:00.103 --> 05:56:02.260
Why should those who are single be treated

3776828598
05:56:02.261 --> 05:56:05.044
any different from those who are serving,

1953585155
05:56:05.046 --> 05:56:09.343
who choose to be with their families?

2866222846
05:56:09.344 --> 05:56:12.794
The Armed Forces Bill will have
united support from parties

3145925894
05:56:12.796 --> 05:56:16.904
across this House and
so should New Clause 13.

22326557
05:56:16.905 --> 05:56:20.951
I urge the government to be
bold, accept no half measures

2865787788
05:56:20.952 --> 05:56:27.539
and deliver decent housing for
every member of our armed forces.

1506131803
05:56:27.540 --> 05:56:28.091
Thank you.

4239307382
05:56:28.092 --> 05:56:29.647
>> I call Doctor Scott Arthur.

1066130234
05:56:29.648 --> 05:56:30.701
>> Thank you, chair.

185136772
05:56:30.702 --> 05:56:31.253
Thank you.

4147832940
05:56:31.254 --> 05:56:34.802
And you'll be pleased to hear I'm
going to be relatively short.

1991141621
05:56:34.803 --> 05:56:37.399
So I'm proud to welcome
this Armed Forces bill.

4109851811
05:56:38.139 --> 05:56:41.840
It represents a vital step towards
renewing our contract with

2631073195
05:56:41.841 --> 05:56:45.296
those who keep us safe as
an MP with Redford Barracks,

492304167
05:56:45.297 --> 05:56:48.698
Dreghorn Barracks and also RAF
Kirknewton in my constituency.

1887213950
05:56:48.699 --> 05:56:51.196
This bill is of immense pride to me,

1259412534
05:56:51.197 --> 05:56:55.040
but it is also one of urgent necessity.

2082424400
05:56:55.041 --> 05:56:57.942
So I focus on clauses, new
clauses three and five.

4160039521
05:56:57.943 --> 05:57:01.353
But I want to start by welcoming
the increased investment

3571445050
05:57:01.354 --> 05:57:04.936
which underpins the renewal, that renewal.

3779597295
05:57:04.938 --> 05:57:07.194
Our new £9 billion defence
housing strategy.

342929034
05:57:07.195 --> 05:57:10.153
This will be the biggest renewal
of military accommodation

1982248052
05:57:10.154 --> 05:57:12.110
in half a century and across Edinburgh

1606597506
05:57:12.111 --> 05:57:15.543
South West our forces
families will benefit

4268107488
05:57:15.544 --> 05:57:18.439
and I see this already
in Edinburgh South West.

427414514
05:57:18.440 --> 05:57:21.894
For too long, the state
of service accommodation,

2263601799
05:57:21.895 --> 05:57:23.199
as we have heard already,

2078206525
05:57:23.200 --> 05:57:25.197
has been a source of deep frustration.

3968593683
05:57:25.198 --> 05:57:29.350
But now in my constituency it
is slowly becoming a source

381477197
05:57:29.351 --> 05:57:32.156
of envy as people watch
these homes being upgraded.

3817482774
05:57:32.157 --> 05:57:36.543
I am happy that this landmark
strategy will significantly improve

3243158205
05:57:36.544 --> 05:57:39.793
the state of service housing
up and down the country,

1450842005
05:57:39.794 --> 05:57:42.103
and I have to thank
the Minister, the member,

3121250268
05:57:42.104 --> 05:57:44.008
for bringing Birmingham and Selly Oak

349036929
05:57:44.144 --> 05:57:45.949
for stepping in in my constituency,

3866994420
05:57:45.950 --> 05:57:50.903
because the MoD was about to sell
surplus homes on the private market,

693453419
05:57:51.144 --> 05:57:52.499
on the on the open market.

4070426082
05:57:52.500 --> 05:57:55.597
But instead he stepped
in to make sure that

825739252
05:57:55.599 --> 05:57:57.404
we were transferred to the council.

2248847431
05:57:57.405 --> 05:58:00.855
And those ex-army homes
are now council homes,

1274703679
05:58:00.856 --> 05:58:05.196
which I think is a fantastic
outcome here on New clause three.

3152023121
05:58:05.197 --> 05:58:08.196
On veteran support,
the Royal British Legion

3332099236
05:58:08.197 --> 05:58:10.744
has rightly highlighted the outstanding

4175353648
05:58:10.745 --> 05:58:14.203
vacancy for Veterans Commissioner
for England, which was advertised.

3327816669
05:58:14.204 --> 05:58:17.465
Let's face it, just a few days
before the last general election.

2231129901
05:58:17.466 --> 05:58:19.172
And that is something that we do.

1528959255
05:58:19.173 --> 05:58:21.251
We do have to question in Scotland.

3305746396
05:58:21.252 --> 05:58:24.297
We have long seen the clear
impact of our veterans

1361683179
05:58:24.298 --> 05:58:26.845
Commissioner and I spoke
about that earlier,

3317553994
05:58:26.846 --> 05:58:30.151
and it is only right that
England has one two.

2780332522
05:58:30.153 --> 05:58:33.547
So I do urge the government to
think about this seriously.

2369241287
05:58:33.548 --> 05:58:34.852
But there are two points.

3001707566
05:58:34.853 --> 05:58:37.210
There's two points that
have to be considered.

521303552
05:58:37.211 --> 05:58:39.469
We do have to look at
the existing veterans,

1994192004
05:58:39.470 --> 05:58:41.524
commissioners understand what is working

2572570449
05:58:41.525 --> 05:58:43.532
and what is not built on best practice.

1396653796
05:58:43.533 --> 05:58:47.195
And of course, Operation Valour is
getting rolled out at pace and scale.

3929530058
05:58:47.196 --> 05:58:49.654
So we have to get
the interaction between right,

3460502893
05:58:50.145 --> 05:58:52.249
between veterans commissioner and valour.

3800494558
05:58:52.250 --> 05:58:52.850
Absolutely.

3159544351
05:58:53.143 --> 05:58:53.493
Right.

3545636628
05:58:53.494 --> 05:58:57.449
So I think it is right that we
we want action in this area,

915101391
05:58:57.450 --> 05:59:00.256
but we also have to show
a little caution as well

1183998583
05:59:00.257 --> 05:59:04.046
to make sure we get it right first time.

4074226763
05:59:04.047 --> 05:59:05.301
And now new clause five.

960731951
05:59:05.302 --> 05:59:09.493
It really is an opportunity to
tear down some of the unfair

3226969378
05:59:09.494 --> 05:59:11.849
barriers facing non-UK
Armed forces personnel.

990214845
05:59:11.850 --> 05:59:14.057
I welcome the intent
behind the new clause,

1009202496
05:59:15.158 --> 05:59:19.047
which seeks to amend the Immigration
Act 2014 to waive the fee for

2715276718
05:59:19.048 --> 05:59:22.446
indefinite leave to remain
applications from spouses

2525631277
05:59:22.447 --> 05:59:27.445
and children of current
or former service personnel.

1254469071
05:59:27.446 --> 05:59:30.454
As a constituent, a constituent
recently raised the painful

2794453466
05:59:30.454 --> 05:59:33.258
administrative hurdles affecting
Commonwealth soldiers,

392366402
05:59:34.144 --> 05:59:36.751
veterans and their families
who now call Edinburgh,

2163906901
05:59:38.257 --> 05:59:40.164
Scotland and the wider UK their home.

1235111559
05:59:40.165 --> 05:59:42.757
I met I met the All Nations
Christian Fellowship

2420703984
05:59:42.757 --> 05:59:45.497
Church in in Oxgangs on Oxgangs Avenue.

2862543017
05:59:45.498 --> 05:59:46.802
They had an open evening.

701074741
05:59:47.167 --> 05:59:50.945
It was fantastic and it culminated
in some excellent food.

1402993699
05:59:50.946 --> 05:59:54.460
But he told me that while he told
me that Edinburgh was his home now,

1823019450
05:59:54.461 --> 05:59:58.602
and he told me about how proud
he was to serve in three rifles,

691022081
05:59:58.603 --> 06:00:01.313
and I have to say, I have
never met anybody who

836978959
06:00:01.314 --> 06:00:03.371
is prouder to serve in our armed forces,

2863798525
06:00:03.372 --> 06:00:06.003
despite the fact that he
was not born in the UK.

666398109
06:00:06.004 --> 06:00:09.704
And he also told me about how he lost

285628966
06:00:09.704 --> 06:00:11.793
some of his friends in Afghanistan.

23995776
06:00:11.794 --> 06:00:15.549
He was an amazing man, I have
to say, and all sorts of ways,

4098348245
06:00:15.550 --> 06:00:17.703
but I was ashamed to hear that.

4062060177
06:00:17.704 --> 06:00:21.749
He is expected to pay visa fees for
his family to settle in the UK.

514925304
06:00:21.750 --> 06:00:23.749
He has left the forces now.

1693282356
06:00:23.750 --> 06:00:28.196
He is a veteran, a proud veteran,
but he is on modest income.

3592936287
06:00:28.197 --> 06:00:31.357
The fees that he faces are
just incredible for him.

239507857
06:00:31.358 --> 06:00:33.514
And he wasn't just advocating for himself.

2690432323
06:00:33.515 --> 06:00:34.869
He's not a selfish person.

2336448678
06:00:34.870 --> 06:00:37.529
He was advocating for others
in his network as well.

3149154081
06:00:37.530 --> 06:00:40.740
So I think it's right that
the government takes this seriously.

4035374552
06:00:40.740 --> 06:00:43.752
If you are prepared to lay down
your life for this country,

2653248032
06:00:43.753 --> 06:00:46.813
your family should not face
financial penalty to live in it.

3430113367
06:00:46.814 --> 06:00:49.021
We must give these brave
individuals a fair

957797917
06:00:49.022 --> 06:00:51.296
and dignified pathway to settlement.

3341440226
06:00:51.297 --> 06:00:54.597
Now, I accept that this is
best led by the Home Office,

2628204857
06:00:54.599 --> 06:00:57.058
but I do think that
the amendment which has been

3882428328
06:00:57.059 --> 06:00:59.302
brought forward by the Member for Hunter.

3275552897
06:00:59.303 --> 06:01:02.664
What this debate is achieved is,
I think, right across this House,

3215988161
06:01:02.665 --> 06:01:04.872
certainly the people
that are in this room,

2013587756
06:01:04.873 --> 06:01:06.429
we want to see action on this,

3645591425
06:01:06.430 --> 06:01:08.738
and I do not think that
anybody opposes this.

2856418086
06:01:08.739 --> 06:01:10.797
And so I think we have to remember this.

969889261
06:01:10.798 --> 06:01:12.454
And we do have to demand action.

678332791
06:01:12.454 --> 06:01:12.655
So.

3513246850
06:01:12.656 --> 06:01:15.265
So I am hopeful that this
bill will finally deliver

2107767856
06:01:15.266 --> 06:01:17.421
the settlement that our military deserves.

2646695656
06:01:17.422 --> 06:01:19.649
The promise is there.

3874091490
06:01:19.650 --> 06:01:21.907
We must ensure that our
delivery on housing,

4281287303
06:01:21.908 --> 06:01:23.762
recruitment and fairness matches it.

517941044
06:01:23.763 --> 06:01:26.503
And I want to make three points.

2426843267
06:01:26.504 --> 06:01:29.414
The the journey of this bill
will not be completed today.

3969445756
06:01:29.415 --> 06:01:32.073
There's going to be other
opportunities to amend it.

2439562101
06:01:32.074 --> 06:01:35.740
So I do hope that if it is the right
thing on new clause three and five,

3994326636
06:01:35.740 --> 06:01:39.352
we will find time to make space
for the intent behind them.

3330800917
06:01:39.353 --> 06:01:43.303
And on devolution there is no bigger
supporter of devolution than me,

3989462101
06:01:43.304 --> 06:01:46.699
but there is nothing worse than
being than being on the wrong side

2944669055
06:01:46.700 --> 06:01:49.810
of the border when it comes to
access and services sometimes.

266714952
06:01:49.811 --> 06:01:53.603
And for our military families that
move between England and Scotland,

1299381389
06:01:53.604 --> 06:01:55.910
they really feel
the difference in childcare.

1624306638
06:01:55.911 --> 06:01:59.358
And depending on the age of your
child, that has different impacts,

1407925830
06:01:59.359 --> 06:02:01.557
or if your spouse happens to be a teacher,

503447058
06:02:01.558 --> 06:02:05.020
moving from Scotland to England
and vice versa can be a huge hurdle.

3839569226
06:02:05.021 --> 06:02:08.803
So as we think about amending
this bill to make lives

2785542531
06:02:08.804 --> 06:02:11.060
better for our armed
armed forces personnel,

2403500670
06:02:11.061 --> 06:02:14.160
I think please think carefully
about families who are moving

1893357646
06:02:14.161 --> 06:02:17.254
between the between England
and the devolved nations,

1821523525
06:02:17.255 --> 06:02:20.813
and make sure that we have
a safety net for them to make sure

4114322390
06:02:20.814 --> 06:02:24.199
that they are never disadvantaged
for serving our country.

111956833
06:02:24.200 --> 06:02:27.451
And lastly, chair, the last time
I mentioned RAF Kirknewton,

1223379204
06:02:27.452 --> 06:02:30.210
I did make the point that it's the home of

4129140235
06:02:30.211 --> 06:02:33.648
number 661 Volunteer Gliding Squadron,

3640387034
06:02:33.649 --> 06:02:35.506
the net zero fleet of the Air Force,

1416963128
06:02:35.507 --> 06:02:41.044
if you like, and they fly a fleet
of four Grob Viking T1 gliders

1905068144
06:02:41.046 --> 06:02:44.707
and they provide excellent experience
to the Royal Air Force Air Cadets.

3878650062
06:02:44.708 --> 06:02:47.454
But what I did not say is it is also

3800167572
06:02:47.454 --> 06:02:52.299
the home to a meticulously recreated

1092042914
06:02:52.300 --> 06:02:55.554
World War One Sopwith One Strutter
aircraft and this has been.

1799242513
06:02:55.555 --> 06:02:59.065
This has been built by the Aviation
Preservation Society of Scotland.

2580211317
06:02:59.066 --> 06:03:01.609
And why I mentioned this
is that the big military

425466061
06:03:01.610 --> 06:03:03.313
installations in my constituency,

19458778
06:03:03.314 --> 06:03:05.899
Redford and Dreghorn
Barracks and also the air

3252140206
06:03:05.900 --> 06:03:07.906
base there have got fences around them.

2660947586
06:03:07.907 --> 06:03:11.507
But that does not mean they're not
well connected with the community.

1993867784
06:03:11.507 --> 06:03:15.208
So when I'm out in Colinton,
I meet our armed forces

646720308
06:03:16.149 --> 06:03:18.406
serving armed forces
people at the bus stop.

1957304598
06:03:18.407 --> 06:03:20.564
I meet them at the school gates sometimes,

4111292409
06:03:20.565 --> 06:03:22.622
and I meet them in Colinton means Tesco.

444820286
06:03:22.623 --> 06:03:25.684
I do worry about the diet of
some of our younger servicemen,

1666291535
06:03:25.685 --> 06:03:28.092
but that's the debate,
perhaps for another day.

2939563089
06:03:28.093 --> 06:03:30.299
And at Colinton Primary
School, when, when,

7158068
06:03:30.300 --> 06:03:33.362
when when the school was closed
due to snow a few years ago,

418258781
06:03:33.363 --> 06:03:35.722
it was the army that came
down and cleared it.

3344499305
06:03:35.722 --> 06:03:38.833
Perhaps they were desperate to
get their kids back to school,

1408918911
06:03:38.834 --> 06:03:40.138
but we've all been there.

3994690483
06:03:40.139 --> 06:03:42.297
And when we need a barbecue at that school

4137632622
06:03:42.298 --> 06:03:43.854
a couple of years ago, it was.

3139720711
06:03:43.855 --> 06:03:46.815
The army provided it and they
brought with them the rarest

1306033119
06:03:46.816 --> 06:03:50.200
piece of military equipment
I've ever seen deployed chair.

732926665
06:03:50.201 --> 06:03:52.552
It was the army's bouncy castle.

1583029635
06:03:52.553 --> 06:03:54.156
They brought fully camouflaged.

2006455261
06:03:54.157 --> 06:03:57.712
I have no idea what the Army
does with the rest of the year.

4057522520
06:03:57.713 --> 06:03:58.163
Perhaps.

3453296450
06:03:58.164 --> 06:04:00.962
Perhaps there's a written
question that Sarah Bool.

2247279135
06:04:00.963 --> 06:04:01.464
But this.

4170136164
06:04:01.465 --> 06:04:04.300
This is incredibly important because our.

1431591648
06:04:04.301 --> 06:04:07.655
In my constituency,
particularly around Colinton,

1697766462
06:04:07.656 --> 06:04:10.053
the armed forces are fully integrated.

3458789363
06:04:10.054 --> 06:04:13.400
And this is something I cherish
in local people cherish.

2902808225
06:04:13.401 --> 06:04:17.653
And I really do hope that
this bill, the covenant,

2551589751
06:04:17.654 --> 06:04:21.264
are about creating and maintaining
and sustaining that kind of culture.

2838696788
06:04:21.265 --> 06:04:23.725
And all of us have a duty
to maintain that here.

4020635690
06:04:24.149 --> 06:04:24.700
Thank you.

1533508709
06:04:24.701 --> 06:04:25.051
Chair.

4031892790
06:04:25.052 --> 06:04:25.401
Chair.

1398356
06:04:25.403 --> 06:04:26.657
>> I call Kevin Bonavia.

1176066654
06:04:27.151 --> 06:04:28.506
>> Thank you, Madam Chair.

2226508994
06:04:28.507 --> 06:04:31.516
And first, can I thank
everybody involved in

425657588
06:04:31.517 --> 06:04:33.675
bringing to to the bill where it is today,

870839905
06:04:33.676 --> 06:04:37.458
Ministers and particularly members of
the Armed Forces Select Committee.

2034833983
06:04:37.459 --> 06:04:41.401
That's a serious amount of
work, because this is not just

4048707119
06:04:41.403 --> 06:04:45.702
a typical armed forces bill
where we are performing

1847099774
06:04:45.703 --> 06:04:49.355
our constitutional duty in this
House to renew our armed forces,

1345664416
06:04:49.356 --> 06:04:54.104
but it goes much, much further than that.

2851783862
06:04:54.105 --> 06:04:56.853
It it it pushes forward our armed forces.

1587387472
06:04:56.854 --> 06:04:59.560
Covenant makes it real across our country.

3318464673
06:04:59.561 --> 06:05:03.552
It gives our armed forces
a housing they finally

775988998
06:05:03.553 --> 06:05:05.709
deserve and the justice that they deserve.

409297028
06:05:08.153 --> 06:05:10.059
And it gives our reserves true, true,

1166908549
06:05:10.060 --> 06:05:14.059
a true role to play in
the defence of our nation.

3684056293
06:05:14.060 --> 06:05:18.860
And that is why we have to pass this bill.

3251069594
06:05:18.861 --> 06:05:21.267
And there are some really
important amendments.

4237000538
06:05:21.268 --> 06:05:22.872
And in particular, Madam Chair,

3353550456
06:05:22.873 --> 06:05:25.481
I want to cover a government
amendment number nine,

2084394417
06:05:25.482 --> 06:05:28.990
which relates the Armed Forces
Covenant and Government Amendments 48,

2537376018
06:05:28.992 --> 06:05:32.052
51 and 54, which relates to
the new Defence Housing Service.

1130241884
06:05:32.155 --> 06:05:35.555
So, first, with the Armed
Forces Covenant that goes to

1522164973
06:05:35.556 --> 06:05:39.209
the heart of this country's
commitment to our armed forces.

4204400298
06:05:39.210 --> 06:05:45.358
And we have talked about it
so is much for so many years.

3381009081
06:05:45.359 --> 06:05:48.906
But in reality, is it justly
applied across our country.

1683567596
06:05:48.907 --> 06:05:54.708
This bill goes to
the heart of that question,

2452204415
06:05:54.709 --> 06:05:58.957
and it it tries to put that
covenant into practice.

513604231
06:05:58.958 --> 06:06:02.565
When we talk about our armed forces,

432983981
06:06:02.566 --> 06:06:07.104
we are actually talking about a community,

2440222238
06:06:07.105 --> 06:06:11.154
including those who have
served of 4.5 million people.

3643042167
06:06:11.155 --> 06:06:14.706
That's including 2 million
veterans that are alive today.

3308076184
06:06:14.707 --> 06:06:17.761
And yet for many of them,
support has depended less

3881241650
06:06:17.762 --> 06:06:20.556
on the principle and more
on a postcode lottery.

539083899
06:06:20.557 --> 06:06:23.166
For too long, the covenant
has been the right idea,

2585341356
06:06:23.167 --> 06:06:25.756
but too often the wrong
experience on the ground.

112584138
06:06:25.757 --> 06:06:28.164
We've had the principle
of no disadvantage yet.

966587723
06:06:28.165 --> 06:06:30.563
Delivery has been uneven
and and inconsistent.

3388202897
06:06:30.564 --> 06:06:34.404
You take my own county of Hertfordshire.

1049364090
06:06:34.405 --> 06:06:35.458
We have 11 councils.

1424618054
06:06:35.459 --> 06:06:37.406
I have four in my constituency.

3592985922
06:06:37.407 --> 06:06:39.364
I can tell you from my own experience,

600739397
06:06:39.365 --> 06:06:42.207
the way they apply that
covenant varies tremendously.

668444769
06:06:42.208 --> 06:06:46.606
And that's why amendment
number nine is so important,

3941861059
06:06:46.607 --> 06:06:49.865
because it applies the covenant
to the new combined authorities,

1674240746
06:06:49.867 --> 06:06:53.607
which we will soon have in my county.

582115051
06:06:53.608 --> 06:06:56.016
So >> The bike spend
expanding that legal duty.

3713568188
06:06:56.017 --> 06:06:57.671
We are recognising simple truth,

1646296881
06:06:57.672 --> 06:07:00.279
the decisions that shape
people's lives in housing,

1941659478
06:07:00.280 --> 06:07:03.552
planning, local services are
not all taken in one place.

1271706974
06:07:03.553 --> 06:07:06.859
But if the covenant is going
to work, it has to exist

3953784052
06:07:06.860 --> 06:07:09.456
everywhere where those decisions are made.

2077168057
06:07:09.457 --> 06:07:10.611
I'm happy to give way.

1666248743
06:07:12.158 --> 06:07:14.918
>> Madam Speaker, first of
all, can I commend the hon.

112322808
06:07:14.918 --> 06:07:16.523
Gentleman, the covenant for us?

1736516683
06:07:16.524 --> 06:07:20.085
And I know the Minister knows this
because he's a practical experience

2414939292
06:07:20.086 --> 06:07:22.744
and knowledge of it in
relation to Northern Ireland.

911098073
06:07:22.745 --> 06:07:25.454
The covenant is something
we want to see in totality.

4124179256
06:07:25.454 --> 06:07:26.257
The only right.

3964058555
06:07:26.257 --> 06:07:29.662
We want to have it the same wherever
you are in London, Edinburgh,

2287787456
06:07:29.663 --> 06:07:32.852
Cardiff or Portadown
or Newtownards in my constituency.

2885851305
06:07:32.853 --> 06:07:35.906
There is anomalies in
Northern Ireland where,

1128343923
06:07:35.907 --> 06:07:38.214
for instance, if you're
a someone, a veteran,

823082957
06:07:38.215 --> 06:07:40.321
you've served in the forces, you've left,

2986786949
06:07:40.322 --> 06:07:42.879
the forces you should be
getting priority housing.

2019483437
06:07:42.880 --> 06:07:45.339
That should be one of
the things that should be.

1794411418
06:07:45.340 --> 06:07:48.700
It doesn't happen, but it should
happen because the conditions are

291224619
06:07:48.701 --> 06:07:51.961
different in Northern Ireland
and they are here in the mainland.

2651858265
06:07:51.962 --> 06:07:53.517
That's only one of the things.

1322467786
06:07:53.518 --> 06:07:55.974
There's other things that
where the shortcomings

603198996
06:07:55.975 --> 06:07:57.480
and the shortfall is as well.

2823327072
06:07:57.481 --> 06:08:00.242
I know that in my council
area of Ards and North Down,

1031548767
06:08:00.243 --> 06:08:02.649
the veterans Minister
or veterans councillor is

3753458048
06:08:02.650 --> 06:08:04.855
a fellow called Councillor
Trevor Cummings,

1319337575
06:08:04.856 --> 06:08:06.964
and he works very hard to make it happen.

2981254916
06:08:06.965 --> 06:08:09.023
But the point I'm trying to make is this

947978277
06:08:09.024 --> 06:08:10.979
there needs to be fairness everywhere.

3288442232
06:08:10.980 --> 06:08:11.431
The hon.

955560848
06:08:11.432 --> 06:08:13.990
Gentleman is right to say
that I support him 100%.

2671410911
06:08:13.992 --> 06:08:16.049
I know the Minister, when he comes back,

2713798597
06:08:16.050 --> 06:08:19.008
perhaps will give us some
reassurance in relation to that.

1049111733
06:08:19.010 --> 06:08:19.561
Thank you.

952998652
06:08:19.561 --> 06:08:19.912
Sorry.

3621538741
06:08:19.913 --> 06:08:21.267
>> Thank you, Madam Chair.

2470259002
06:08:21.268 --> 06:08:22.322
And I thank the hon.

1933674807
06:08:22.323 --> 06:08:23.775
Member for his intervention.

640948252
06:08:23.776 --> 06:08:25.783
As ever, speak up for his constituents.

1995886499
06:08:25.784 --> 06:08:29.144
But the welfare of the armed forces
community in Northern Ireland,

2053182523
06:08:29.145 --> 06:08:32.215
and I'm sure that this
government will treat

1098240455
06:08:32.216 --> 06:08:35.757
them with the respect
that they deserve to.

3208033346
06:08:35.757 --> 06:08:38.708
I can talk about my area in Stevenage.

2278283101
06:08:38.709 --> 06:08:42.270
We have the borough council that has
signed the Armed Forces Covenant.

434272177
06:08:42.271 --> 06:08:44.958
But it's not just a piece of paper.

2401118047
06:08:44.959 --> 06:08:48.208
It's working to turn that
commitment into something real,

463323989
06:08:48.209 --> 06:08:51.167
but working with the armed
forces community that including

3044019109
06:08:51.168 --> 06:08:53.209
an initiative such as the Muster Point,

3319561021
06:08:53.210 --> 06:08:57.059
which is a grass roots mutual
support veterans organisation,

1827743620
06:08:57.060 --> 06:08:59.865
that they talk to each other,

3376789172
06:08:59.867 --> 06:09:02.475
they bring cases to
the council and actually think,

4028835144
06:09:02.476 --> 06:09:04.808
let's work out a solution
here to make sure

2499312659
06:09:04.809 --> 06:09:06.665
that this person is not left behind.

1066468236
06:09:07.156 --> 06:09:09.412
That council staff
understand when a veteran

3863735429
06:09:12.159 --> 06:09:13.965
comes to them what their needs are.

3236309502
06:09:13.966 --> 06:09:16.517
And that work that we have in Stevenage,

2116615827
06:09:16.518 --> 06:09:19.076
which is led locally by our
armed forces champion,

3458235415
06:09:19.077 --> 06:09:21.906
Councillor Claire Paris,
she's working with veterans

254809381
06:09:21.907 --> 06:09:25.479
in Castle Point like Stu Mendelson,

1200232947
06:09:25.480 --> 06:09:28.339
Steve Black and many others
who have visited this place,

3648185962
06:09:28.340 --> 06:09:30.464
including earlier today,

2697133494
06:09:30.465 --> 06:09:33.124
that they are not left behind,
that places like this

70107566
06:09:33.125 --> 06:09:37.808
and across the country
are truly for them to.

2213414293
06:09:37.809 --> 06:09:40.218
But the reality is that
this kind of joined up,

2157240008
06:09:40.219 --> 06:09:42.374
practical delivery has not been consistent

3397608463
06:09:42.375 --> 06:09:44.281
across the country, and for too long,

2493500242
06:09:44.282 --> 06:09:46.789
service families have been
told that the covenant

256663453
06:09:46.790 --> 06:09:48.695
exists only to find their experience,

3835681702
06:09:48.696 --> 06:09:51.054
depend on that postcode
in which they live in.

2824103450
06:09:51.055 --> 06:09:54.216
So when we look at this bill
and this amendment in particular,

3911443884
06:09:54.217 --> 06:09:56.875
the question is not whether
we need more frameworks,

843064417
06:09:56.876 --> 06:09:58.831
new office holders or more statements.

808662072
06:09:58.832 --> 06:10:01.590
The question is whether we
finally ensure the covenant

2143718687
06:10:01.591 --> 06:10:03.697
works everywhere in this country of ours,

462542087
06:10:03.698 --> 06:10:07.712
not just in the places where there
is strong local leadership,

3208355268
06:10:08.156 --> 06:10:12.660
this duty in this bill embeds
a covenant across the system and ensures

3326421561
06:10:12.661 --> 06:10:15.571
that the kind of approach that
we see in my constituency,

1688014311
06:10:15.572 --> 06:10:19.161
Stevenage, is not
the exception, but the standard.

1385484689
06:10:19.162 --> 06:10:21.208
And after years with covenant,

1856391079
06:10:21.209 --> 06:10:23.665
was talked about but not
consistently delivered.

912964271
06:10:23.666 --> 06:10:28.344
This bill is what starts to
make that consistency real.

3728950116
06:10:28.345 --> 06:10:32.364
And secondly, Madam Chair,
I turn to amendments 48,

380921466
06:10:32.365 --> 06:10:33.870
51 and 54 on service housing.

3070783781
06:10:33.871 --> 06:10:37.258
As we already heard earlier
in this debate, for too long,

452654618
06:10:37.260 --> 06:10:40.118
service families were expected
to put up with conditions

1405226333
06:10:40.119 --> 06:10:43.559
that simply would not be
tolerated anywhere else.

791602807
06:10:43.560 --> 06:10:46.809
Two thirds of service family
accommodation needs major

1981587568
06:10:46.810 --> 06:10:52.257
work repair satisfaction has
collapsed as low as 16%,

2894495315
06:10:52.258 --> 06:10:55.418
and tens of thousands of complaints
being made year upon year.

3653231727
06:10:57.156 --> 06:10:59.314
And let's be honest about how we got here.

4026376892
06:10:59.315 --> 06:11:02.176
That is the legacy of
a failed housing model,

1592783434
06:11:02.177 --> 06:11:04.332
a botched privatisation that left families

679856460
06:11:04.333 --> 06:11:10.708
living in substandard homes while
taxpayers continued footing that bill.

3901635739
06:11:10.709 --> 06:11:16.506
And this government is
now putting that right.

739664009
06:11:16.507 --> 06:11:19.563
A £9 billion investment into our service

27825248
06:11:19.564 --> 06:11:21.369
housing tens of thousands of homes,

2492438827
06:11:21.370 --> 06:11:23.561
upgraded or rebuilt, and, crucially,

4060478765
06:11:23.563 --> 06:11:27.413
bringing homes back into public
ownership so we can finally

2029086264
06:11:27.414 --> 06:11:31.122
take back control of
standards and delivery.

455945786
06:11:31.123 --> 06:11:32.878
And this isn't just about comfort.

1564567805
06:11:32.879 --> 06:11:34.401
It is about capability, too.

2384173958
06:11:34.403 --> 06:11:38.358
When only 44 and ten personnel
are satisfied with service,

3988159720
06:11:38.359 --> 06:11:40.516
life and morale has fallen to record lows.

1032997353
06:11:40.517 --> 06:11:41.972
Housing is not a side issue.

2550923627
06:11:41.972 --> 06:11:43.377
It is central to retention,

385886498
06:11:43.378 --> 06:11:45.685
readiness and the future
of the armed forces.

3350425974
06:11:45.686 --> 06:11:47.541
Madam chair, I've had the privilege,

1545032470
06:11:47.542 --> 06:11:49.850
as many other members
of this House have had,

3444137128
06:11:49.851 --> 06:11:52.209
having not served in
the forces but being part

3990872923
06:11:52.210 --> 06:11:54.315
of the Armed Forces Parliamentary Scheme.

355256997
06:11:54.316 --> 06:11:57.478
And as part of that, we get to
visit bases around the country,

3691118047
06:11:59.112 --> 06:12:00.769
as I did with the RAF last year.

3418432791
06:12:00.770 --> 06:12:04.862
I tell you what, the person
that we met are proud,

1730010369
06:12:04.863 --> 06:12:07.815
but they're proud not
just of their service,

1580683800
06:12:07.816 --> 06:12:09.961
they're proud of their families,

993634856
06:12:09.962 --> 06:12:13.061
but they want homes for
their families as well.

2350934899
06:12:13.063 --> 06:12:15.320
And the homes that they
have vary massively.

270485727
06:12:15.321 --> 06:12:18.064
We've seen some great
examples of what can be done.

3290045944
06:12:18.065 --> 06:12:20.121
We've seen other examples of housing has

805300034
06:12:20.122 --> 06:12:21.977
not been dealt with for generations.

1472871042
06:12:21.978 --> 06:12:25.907
We owe it to them to see that
they have a future for themselves

1520476170
06:12:25.908 --> 06:12:28.063
and their families in those accommodation.

1739669678
06:12:28.064 --> 06:12:29.117
>> Here, here, here.

1277053098
06:12:29.118 --> 06:12:29.970
So the creation.

1526246178
06:12:29.971 --> 06:12:34.911
>> Of the Defence Housing Service
is a decisive break with the past.

2741500221
06:12:34.912 --> 06:12:40.066
It puts forces families first,
and it gives the government the tools

1268588345
06:12:40.067 --> 06:12:44.617
to act and start the job of
rebuilding the estate properly.

1265205347
06:12:45.160 --> 06:12:49.560
Members of this House,
and indeed the wider British public,

2763482672
06:12:49.561 --> 06:12:53.061
are rightly proud of our armed
forces and our veterans.

1305748857
06:12:53.063 --> 06:12:58.666
But we need to demonstrate that
pride into meaningful action.

2813170312
06:12:58.667 --> 06:13:04.070
And that is what this bill will do.

2014700513
06:13:04.071 --> 06:13:05.826
>> Alison Taylor thank you, madam.

2094345878
06:13:06.159 --> 06:13:08.065
Sorry, Madam Chair, and thank you for

2070030816
06:13:08.066 --> 06:13:12.265
the opportunity to
contribute to this debate.

4261566254
06:13:12.266 --> 06:13:16.766
I felt it was important as a as a MP that

3713973776
06:13:16.767 --> 06:13:19.365
represents the west coast of Scotland,

1184395425
06:13:19.365 --> 06:13:23.568
and a large part of my seat is within
the River Clyde to contribute to

474657492
06:13:26.160 --> 06:13:28.717
this important debate today
and in my constituency

187705856
06:13:28.718 --> 06:13:30.472
of Paisley and Renfrewshire North,

4125693516
06:13:30.472 --> 06:13:33.733
there are quite a number of serving
and retired service members.

614584110
06:13:33.734 --> 06:13:36.806
We have many families that
settled in the constituency

2578594433
06:13:36.807 --> 06:13:41.061
to work in the war effort
during the Second World War,

1353217798
06:13:41.061 --> 06:13:44.112
in a in a in its constituency
with strong connections

3857452186
06:13:44.113 --> 06:13:47.111
to the armed forces
and the veteran's charity.

1990490320
06:13:47.112 --> 06:13:53.206
Erskine was founded there
in the The measures

1186552994
06:13:53.207 --> 06:13:54.910
former Erskine Veterans Hospital.

3618006961
06:13:54.911 --> 06:13:58.171
The measures in this bill will be
welcomed across Great Britain.

3850698907
06:13:58.172 --> 06:14:03.070
I was fortunate enough to join
local service personnel to learn

3349671239
06:14:03.071 --> 06:14:06.029
about the Armed Forces Covenant
shortly after my election,

3948141022
06:14:06.030 --> 06:14:09.311
and I've been greatly
encouraged to learn of

1937785494
06:14:09.311 --> 06:14:12.061
local employers signing
it and embracing it.

1973937212
06:14:12.061 --> 06:14:16.267
It is well past time that the government
did the same, and I know, too,

1357818311
06:14:16.268 --> 06:14:18.574
that the provisions on
service family housing

2505288597
06:14:18.575 --> 06:14:21.014
will be broadly welcomed
across the country,

2544802427
06:14:21.015 --> 06:14:24.767
and I look forward to seeing
the benefits of concerted efforts

3923097316
06:14:26.160 --> 06:14:29.819
to improve housing for
families in my constituency.

804717965
06:14:29.820 --> 06:14:31.976
Housing in our communities is so important

189410611
06:14:31.977 --> 06:14:33.984
not just to providing a place to sleep,

3735334336
06:14:33.985 --> 06:14:36.192
but also for access to
the local community,

1493607910
06:14:36.193 --> 06:14:38.163
schools, health services and so on.

804581667
06:14:38.164 --> 06:14:40.861
Our communities are open and generous,

2838496166
06:14:40.862 --> 06:14:45.513
and they appreciate the sacrifices
made by service personnel.

2779865591
06:14:45.514 --> 06:14:45.664
I.

2820814172
06:14:45.665 --> 06:14:50.715
I look forward, Madam Chair, to
welcoming more retired and serving

4049777631
06:14:52.159 --> 06:14:54.966
service personnel to to Paisley
and Renfrewshire North.

3750716982
06:14:56.160 --> 06:14:56.711
Thank you.

1357802393
06:14:56.712 --> 06:14:57.564
>> Anna Gelderd.

1413927398
06:14:57.565 --> 06:15:01.629
>> Madam chair, it's a privilege
to speak in support of this bill

2686098323
06:15:01.630 --> 06:15:04.938
and the government amendments laid
today, which improves housing,

4072831385
06:15:04.939 --> 06:15:08.196
strengthens protection for serving
personnel and their families,

3284748954
06:15:08.197 --> 06:15:10.504
and ensures our Armed
forces are prepared for

1167112216
06:15:10.505 --> 06:15:13.061
the challenges of
an increasingly uncertain world.

3816718964
06:15:13.061 --> 06:15:15.168
While much of this debate rightly focuses

1696216729
06:15:15.168 --> 06:15:16.872
on structures, powers, processes,

519064673
06:15:16.873 --> 06:15:19.079
the strength of our
armed forces ultimately

2533698229
06:15:19.079 --> 06:15:20.987
comes down to the brave men and women

3219489869
06:15:20.988 --> 06:15:23.195
who choose to serve
their country and their

155375187
06:15:23.196 --> 06:15:25.002
families who support them to do so.

467700903
06:15:25.003 --> 06:15:28.214
In South East Cornwall, we see
that every day through the close

2463029670
06:15:28.215 --> 06:15:30.872
connection between our
community and the Royal Navy.

3444641703
06:15:30.873 --> 06:15:32.979
At HMS Raleigh, people arrive from across

3529890946
06:15:32.980 --> 06:15:34.936
the UK to begin their service careers,

580530876
06:15:34.936 --> 06:15:37.042
and many leave with lifelong friendships,

4104839682
06:15:37.043 --> 06:15:38.849
skills and a deep sense of purpose.

1184322608
06:15:38.850 --> 06:15:42.715
Just recently, the recruits
of Gould, 25 slash, 37,

1599391206
06:15:42.716 --> 06:15:45.464
successfully passed out
from their initial naval

1802382769
06:15:45.465 --> 06:15:47.923
training and they know
the whole House will join

856181749
06:15:47.924 --> 06:15:50.230
me in congratulating
them on this significant

3232375396
06:15:50.231 --> 06:15:51.684
achievement and wishing them

2128949559
06:15:51.685 --> 06:15:55.520
every success as they begin their
careers in service to our country.

616460366
06:15:55.521 --> 06:15:58.820
One recruit marked this occasion
in particular memorable

668594986
06:15:58.821 --> 06:16:00.827
fashion by proposing to his now fiance,

1966605832
06:16:00.828 --> 06:16:05.815
so I hope the Minister will join me
in congratulating Cameron and Lexie

4239621710
06:16:05.816 --> 06:16:09.377
on their engagement and wishing them
a long and happy future together.

3257698389
06:16:09.378 --> 06:16:11.033
>> Here, here, here, here, here.

1664133345
06:16:11.034 --> 06:16:11.936
It is a reminder.

96565805
06:16:11.938 --> 06:16:15.623
>> That places like HMS Raleigh are
not simply training establishments.

4187344491
06:16:15.624 --> 06:16:19.136
For many, they are where futures are
built and the values of service,

1623271308
06:16:19.137 --> 06:16:21.443
commitment and community
are lived every day.

1778610510
06:16:21.444 --> 06:16:24.905
As you consider this bill, we must
remember that behind every policy

1106745326
06:16:24.906 --> 06:16:28.317
and every provision are the people
who make our armed forces great.

2985064644
06:16:28.318 --> 06:16:32.029
That is why I particularly welcome
government amendment to clause three

1702659743
06:16:32.030 --> 06:16:35.140
on housing and the creation of
a new defence housing service.

3606260011
06:16:35.141 --> 06:16:37.097
As I think about that new young couple

38088658
06:16:37.164 --> 06:16:39.522
and the home that they
hope to build together,

2666420310
06:16:39.523 --> 06:16:41.628
we cannot hope to strengthen recruitment,

1427411737
06:16:41.629 --> 06:16:44.335
retention and national
readiness if service personnel

1196154327
06:16:44.336 --> 06:16:47.910
and their families are living
in unacceptable accommodation.

3674411290
06:16:47.911 --> 06:16:48.814
>> On that point.

2576825716
06:16:48.815 --> 06:16:49.367
>> I will.

217305935
06:16:49.368 --> 06:16:50.322
>> I thank my hon.

430367220
06:16:50.323 --> 06:16:51.476
Friend for giving way.

52798289
06:16:51.477 --> 06:16:53.524
My father knows well that, like her,

3380812347
06:16:53.525 --> 06:16:55.582
I've got many serving folks in my patch.

2301046814
06:16:55.583 --> 06:16:59.467
There's a particular issue we've got
in Plymouth where South West Water,

1115557612
06:16:59.468 --> 06:17:01.679
which I know she deals with as well.

2040709738
06:17:01.680 --> 06:17:05.472
When they have outages and you
are in service accommodation,

2091032442
06:17:05.472 --> 06:17:07.730
you don't get access
immediately to the same

230936524
06:17:08.160 --> 06:17:10.867
compensation pay that your
very neighbours get access

1559864527
06:17:10.868 --> 06:17:13.324
to because they're not in
service accommodation,

817830429
06:17:13.325 --> 06:17:15.329
they're paying direct South west water,

238195220
06:17:15.331 --> 06:17:17.335
whereas in service accommodation you're

2313299377
06:17:17.336 --> 06:17:20.696
going through a third party service,
you don't get it immediately.

2311668946
06:17:20.697 --> 06:17:23.255
And the Minister knows this
well because he helped

4083778226
06:17:23.256 --> 06:17:25.714
me out with some casework
around this last year.

2109114249
06:17:25.715 --> 06:17:26.568
But does my hon.

1862696572
06:17:26.569 --> 06:17:28.775
Friend agree that this
is something we need

68579176
06:17:28.776 --> 06:17:30.584
to look at within this bill to make

3531480086
06:17:30.585 --> 06:17:34.145
sure that people get compensation
just as quickly as their neighbours,

854505728
06:17:34.146 --> 06:17:36.603
and aren't disadvantaged
by being in the forces.

3061121
06:17:36.604 --> 06:17:37.558
>> I thank my hon.

2883612363
06:17:37.559 --> 06:17:40.970
Friend for his intervention, and
I agree that we must work together

1735387067
06:17:40.971 --> 06:17:43.729
on issues such as that which
are incredibly important,

3432620146
06:17:43.730 --> 06:17:46.237
and we cannot hope to
strengthen our recruitment,

767213078
06:17:46.238 --> 06:17:48.994
retention and national readiness
if this accommodation

798906186
06:17:48.995 --> 06:17:50.950
is unacceptable and the Bill delivers.

177564693
06:17:50.951 --> 06:17:53.106
Landmark programme of investment to build,

2493692335
06:17:53.107 --> 06:17:56.266
renew and repair military homes
and put forces families first.

2648911705
06:17:56.267 --> 06:17:59.675
The Tory privatisation of military
housing cost taxpayers billions,

1436820855
06:17:59.676 --> 06:18:02.483
while leaving many service
personnel and their families

2189714690
06:18:02.484 --> 06:18:04.990
in accommodation that
simply was not good enough.

801975832
06:18:04.992 --> 06:18:07.149
I also welcome amendments to clause two in

781006443
06:18:07.150 --> 06:18:09.356
the expansion of
the Armed Forces Covenant,

1308634703
06:18:09.357 --> 06:18:11.513
which will extend to recognise the service

718383479
06:18:11.514 --> 06:18:13.167
life prevents unique challenges,

1375276971
06:18:13.168 --> 06:18:15.071
whether through frequent relocations,

3884367675
06:18:15.174 --> 06:18:17.127
disruption to education, difficulties,

3331001514
06:18:17.128 --> 06:18:20.019
accessing healthcare
or impact on family life,

4171755024
06:18:20.020 --> 06:18:23.378
ensuring that public bodies properly
recognise those challenges as

3076378184
06:18:23.379 --> 06:18:27.038
an important step towards delivering
the support that serving personnel,

2957428645
06:18:27.039 --> 06:18:29.194
veterans and their families truly deserve.

536431368
06:18:29.195 --> 06:18:32.556
This matters to our armed forces,
and we know that military morale

3737187521
06:18:32.557 --> 06:18:35.815
fell too deeply concerning levels
under the previous government.

2286080995
06:18:35.816 --> 06:18:38.222
That should concern every
member of this House.

3410898371
06:18:38.224 --> 06:18:41.231
I represent a constituency with
proud military communities,

895218212
06:18:41.232 --> 06:18:44.492
and I know the challenges faced
by service families and children

1599757088
06:18:44.493 --> 06:18:46.967
with special educational
needs and disabilities.

231138258
06:18:46.968 --> 06:18:50.076
Frequent moves can disrupt
education and the support networks

1814183006
06:18:50.077 --> 06:18:53.016
at the very moment
the stability is most needed.

577625409
06:18:53.017 --> 06:18:55.724
So I welcome wholeheartedly
the work being undertaken

3467551541
06:18:55.725 --> 06:18:58.231
in partnership with
the Department for Education,

486925549
06:18:58.232 --> 06:18:59.986
to improve continuity and support.

509841494
06:18:59.987 --> 06:19:03.046
I am also particularly pleased
to welcome amendments to code

276488179
06:19:03.047 --> 06:19:06.003
seven that strengthen protections
against sexual violence,

1731909955
06:19:06.004 --> 06:19:08.058
domestic abuse, stalking and harassment.

1678633042
06:19:08.059 --> 06:19:10.416
Violence against women
and girls remain one of

1747745409
06:19:10.417 --> 06:19:13.171
the greatest challenges
facing our society.

3337029431
06:19:13.172 --> 06:19:16.323
No one should ever face abuse,
intimidation or violence,

1117572821
06:19:16.324 --> 06:19:19.414
and certainly not those who serve
our community in this way.

817915693
06:19:19.415 --> 06:19:19.865
>> Here.

3877166726
06:19:19.867 --> 06:19:22.528
>> In a few weeks time,
I will have the privilege of

1059020909
06:19:22.529 --> 06:19:25.186
attending another passing
out parade at HMS Raleigh.

2896092324
06:19:25.186 --> 06:19:27.293
I know the Minister has previously joined

1883124923
06:19:27.293 --> 06:19:28.949
me to meet veterans in Torpoint,

1515793609
06:19:29.124 --> 06:19:32.786
a town that is home to one of
the country's highest veteran populations.

4065774214
06:19:32.787 --> 06:19:35.396
So I hope you accept my
invitation to revisit South

3653205008
06:19:35.397 --> 06:19:37.502
East Cornwall at the earliest opportunity

4085371136
06:19:37.503 --> 06:19:39.257
to meet the recruits who represent

2173521594
06:19:39.258 --> 06:19:41.215
the bright future of our armed forces,

43927261
06:19:41.216 --> 06:19:43.975
and to discuss the vital role
that South East Cornwall

1787722293
06:19:43.976 --> 06:19:46.683
continues to play in supporting
our nation's defence.

3224607098
06:19:46.684 --> 06:19:50.244
This bill recognises that strong armed
forces depend on strong people,

3989951964
06:19:50.245 --> 06:19:52.751
strong families and strong
communities like mine,

1578753932
06:19:52.752 --> 06:19:54.257
and I am proud to support it.

2605789063
06:19:54.258 --> 06:19:57.017
I look forward to seeing
the difference these measures

1986857971
06:19:57.018 --> 06:20:00.432
and these amendments will make
for those who serve here.

624693435
06:20:00.433 --> 06:20:02.339
>> Alex Baker thank you, Madam Chair.

2003883239
06:20:02.340 --> 06:20:04.146
On the Second Reading of this bill,

1491441547
06:20:04.168 --> 06:20:07.718
I spoke about the Armed Forces
Covenant and the importance

801973866
06:20:07.719 --> 06:20:11.467
of translating our gratitude towards those

1096969638
06:20:11.468 --> 06:20:13.472
who serve into practical support today.

3578738581
06:20:13.474 --> 06:20:15.631
Madam chair, I'm proud to speak in support

2536140391
06:20:15.632 --> 06:20:17.669
of the government's housing measures

33811660
06:20:17.671 --> 06:20:21.474
in clause three of this bill and
the amendments associated with them.

1164552864
06:20:21.475 --> 06:20:27.916
They go to perhaps the most tangible
test of whether we are keeping

932698091
06:20:27.917 --> 06:20:31.324
our side of the bargain with
our armed forces community.

3949645228
06:20:31.325 --> 06:20:32.829
The homes in which they live.

1602631632
06:20:33.168 --> 06:20:39.869
As the Member for Aldershot,
the home of the British Army,

379496185
06:20:39.870 --> 06:20:43.865
I represent around one one
1800 service family homes,

707565716
06:20:43.865 --> 06:20:47.772
one of the largest concentrations
anywhere in the United Kingdom.

3782454128
06:20:47.773 --> 06:20:51.525
That means the success of these
reforms will be felt directly

3489228015
06:20:51.525 --> 06:20:55.868
by thousands of military
families in my constituency.

3113692576
06:20:55.869 --> 06:20:59.826
For those families, the quality
of their accommodation

72497716
06:20:59.827 --> 06:21:01.482
is not an abstract policy issue.

2249649948
06:21:01.483 --> 06:21:04.876
It affects family life,
children's wellbeing, retention,

2271389026
06:21:06.168 --> 06:21:08.072
morale and operational effectiveness.

2530505627
06:21:08.073 --> 06:21:11.728
For years, too many service
family have lived in homes

173019989
06:21:12.171 --> 06:21:14.528
that fall short of
the standards they deserve.

1012523527
06:21:14.529 --> 06:21:18.019
I hear from families facing persistent

4042862260
06:21:18.020 --> 06:21:20.371
maintenance problems from personnel

1363780593
06:21:20.372 --> 06:21:24.222
frustrated by repair systems
that feel difficult to navigate,

2652693244
06:21:24.224 --> 06:21:26.775
and from parents who simply want a safe,

2276429245
06:21:26.776 --> 06:21:29.423
decent home in which to
raise their children.

3831294468
06:21:29.424 --> 06:21:32.280
This is why I welcome
the action this government

2137428252
06:21:32.281 --> 06:21:34.620
is taking on defence housing.

897139992
06:21:34.621 --> 06:21:35.925
I welcome the £9 billion.

2390404659
06:21:35.926 --> 06:21:40.028
I welcome nine out of ten
houses being refurbished,

1768318061
06:21:40.029 --> 06:21:42.872
and I welcome the housing officers that

2177047635
06:21:42.873 --> 06:21:44.729
will be on the streets of Aldershot.

3072112541
06:21:44.730 --> 06:21:46.335
As a result of this government.

3138559609
06:21:46.336 --> 06:21:49.321
The creation of a new
Defence Housing Service,

1683381036
06:21:49.322 --> 06:21:51.974
alongside the wider
Defence Housing Strategy,

3778383571
06:21:51.975 --> 06:21:55.073
represents a serious
and necessary step forward.

3393932740
06:21:55.074 --> 06:21:58.419
The commitment to long term investment,

3921745121
06:21:58.421 --> 06:22:01.681
clearer accountability and better

2636615984
06:22:01.682 --> 06:22:04.789
standards will matter enormously
to constituencies like mine.

2665839568
06:22:04.790 --> 06:22:09.524
But welcoming these measures does
not mean lowering our ambitions.

1915423732
06:22:09.525 --> 06:22:12.086
It means the opposite if we are going to

150756802
06:22:12.087 --> 06:22:14.316
rebuild trust with service families.

2597190755
06:22:14.317 --> 06:22:18.346
These reforms must be
felt in everyday life,

1706516862
06:22:18.347 --> 06:22:19.850
in repairs completed quickly,

3666856347
06:22:21.165 --> 06:22:26.869
damp and mould dealt with properly,
and a system that listens,

337091536
06:22:26.870 --> 06:22:28.373
responds and follows through.

4247979094
06:22:28.374 --> 06:22:30.979
I gently urge Ministers to ensure that

3262455732
06:22:30.980 --> 06:22:33.921
the Defence Housing Service
has the authority,

2444288908
06:22:33.922 --> 06:22:36.328
funding and accountability
it needs to succeed,

2256954265
06:22:36.329 --> 06:22:40.026
with service families placed at
the heart of its design and delivery.

3484744906
06:22:41.172 --> 06:22:43.579
But defence housing is
not just about families.

1273867475
06:22:44.172 --> 06:22:46.226
Single living accommodation matters too.

3236524901
06:22:46.227 --> 06:22:49.923
For many serving personnel,
particularly younger personnel

3208956414
06:22:50.172 --> 06:22:52.278
or those living away from their families,

2522335336
06:22:53.168 --> 06:22:55.323
single living accommodation is their home.

1303501262
06:22:55.324 --> 06:22:58.177
It shapes their daily lives, their morale,

2695671174
06:22:58.178 --> 06:23:01.539
their wellbeing and sense of where
they are valued by the country,

1093223369
06:23:01.540 --> 06:23:04.097
whether they are valued by
the country they serve.

1811005914
06:23:04.099 --> 06:23:06.707
That is why I welcome
government's review of single

3581350414
06:23:06.708 --> 06:23:10.572
living accommodation
and the overseas estate.

170804796
06:23:10.573 --> 06:23:10.924
It is.

3560690407
06:23:10.925 --> 06:23:13.635
It is right that we look
carefully at the standard of

563856175
06:23:13.636 --> 06:23:16.092
accommodation being provided
to those who serve,

2594162929
06:23:16.093 --> 06:23:19.927
whether they live with their
family or in single accommodation.

372556626
06:23:19.928 --> 06:23:23.032
As the Strategic Defence
Review recognised,

357772229
06:23:23.033 --> 06:23:25.876
accommodation is not similarly
simply an estate issue.

1371759256
06:23:25.877 --> 06:23:33.480
It is a retention issue, a recruitment
issue and a readiness issue.

2799293313
06:23:33.481 --> 06:23:34.785
The test now is delivery.

1629597197
06:23:34.786 --> 06:23:38.179
Before I conclude, I want
to reflect on a letter

3866323327
06:23:38.180 --> 06:23:41.625
I recently received from a constituent,

2880662254
06:23:41.626 --> 06:23:45.769
the father of a serving RAF member.

3694458331
06:23:45.770 --> 06:23:50.374
He wrote to me about helping his
son move into accommodation

1674880052
06:23:50.375 --> 06:23:53.574
at the start of a new
posting, his first posting.

3018450276
06:23:53.575 --> 06:23:56.519
Like any parent, he was proud.

1871421772
06:23:56.520 --> 06:23:59.129
Proud that his son had
chosen to serve his country,

830916270
06:23:59.130 --> 06:24:03.282
proud to see him beginning
the next chapter of his career.

1854722579
06:24:03.283 --> 06:24:07.576
But when he saw the room,
his son had been allocated,

1511336872
06:24:07.577 --> 06:24:10.622
that pride turned to concern.

659933341
06:24:10.623 --> 06:24:13.976
The room was small, outdated
and in poor condition.

2606769271
06:24:13.977 --> 06:24:15.079
There was no heating.

1010138430
06:24:15.081 --> 06:24:17.572
Basic facilities were inadequate.

664025004
06:24:17.573 --> 06:24:21.382
His son had to leave many of his
possessions that made him feel at home,

829907300
06:24:23.172 --> 06:24:25.178
because there simply was not the space.

2005753222
06:24:25.179 --> 06:24:29.526
What struck me most was not
the description of the building itself.

4133312084
06:24:29.528 --> 06:24:34.974
It was the father's description
of leaving his son behind.

70463013
06:24:34.975 --> 06:24:40.677
As policy makers, it is easy
for us to talk about estates,

1430622325
06:24:40.678 --> 06:24:43.772
stock programmes and investment.

568016027
06:24:43.773 --> 06:24:44.825
Those things matter.

2286898845
06:24:44.826 --> 06:24:48.579
But perhaps the best
test is a simpler one.

3545514633
06:24:48.579 --> 06:24:51.875
When we make decisions
about military housing,

2181708107
06:24:51.876 --> 06:24:58.531
we should ask ourselves if this
was our son or our daughter,

3551672824
06:24:58.532 --> 06:25:01.736
would we be content to leave them there?

2960450662
06:25:01.737 --> 06:25:04.373
Would we feel reassured driving away?

925129498
06:25:04.374 --> 06:25:08.430
Would we believe that they
were being treated with

1697010708
06:25:08.431 --> 06:25:12.025
the dignity and the respect
that their service deserves?

262730412
06:25:12.026 --> 06:25:15.633
And would we feel that the nation
was keeping its promise to them?

2544890358
06:25:17.184 --> 06:25:19.443
If the answer is no,
then we must do better.

3761783735
06:25:19.444 --> 06:25:22.933
That is why I welcome the action
this government is taking.

3050063140
06:25:22.934 --> 06:25:26.023
It is why I welcome
the commitment to improve service,

3161411890
06:25:26.024 --> 06:25:29.628
family accommodation and review
single living accommodation.

2000656862
06:25:29.629 --> 06:25:33.333
And it is why I hope
Ministers will continue

2049049907
06:25:33.334 --> 06:25:35.872
to push forward with urgency and ambition,

2294882663
06:25:35.873 --> 06:25:39.916
because those who serve our
country deserve decent homes.

1628119184
06:25:39.917 --> 06:25:43.883
Their families deserve peace of mind.

1858404129
06:25:43.885 --> 06:25:48.573
Their service deserves our respect and our

3168924257
06:25:48.574 --> 06:25:50.429
gratitude must be matched by action.

688094232
06:25:50.430 --> 06:25:50.982
>> I call.

809397953
06:25:50.983 --> 06:25:52.686
>> Shadow Minister Mark Francois.

3615029580
06:25:52.688 --> 06:25:58.026
>> Thank you very much, Madam Chairman.

3268577144
06:25:58.028 --> 06:26:00.284
Having addressed our amendments earlier

2334014975
06:26:00.285 --> 06:26:03.773
on towards the opening of the debate,

3426834027
06:26:03.774 --> 06:26:08.026
I'd now like to speak
particularly to the new clauses,

3432918466
06:26:08.028 --> 06:26:10.132
beginning with new clause three regarding

3154025644
06:26:10.133 --> 06:26:11.988
a Veterans Commissioner for England.

9367602
06:26:11.989 --> 06:26:12.421
My hon.

4270624804
06:26:12.422 --> 06:26:16.398
Friend from South Northamptonshire
made a very good case for this

4291274699
06:26:16.399 --> 06:26:19.257
amendment during the Select
Committee phase on the bill,

3812550945
06:26:19.257 --> 06:26:23.785
and she did exactly the same again
in the House this afternoon,

182879680
06:26:23.786 --> 06:26:25.878
if I may say so.

2431705443
06:26:25.879 --> 06:26:28.626
She also received cross-party support,

1035454841
06:26:28.627 --> 06:26:30.532
certainly in principle, from the hon.

2858082718
06:26:31.133 --> 06:26:33.842
Member for Edinburgh South
West, who gave, I thought,

1710619898
06:26:34.172 --> 06:26:36.025
an extremely thoughtful contribution

1038332532
06:26:36.025 --> 06:26:38.383
and also gave some support to my hon.

2768209463
06:26:38.385 --> 06:26:41.476
Friend for Huntingdon with.

1106213642
06:26:41.477 --> 06:26:43.031
Regarding his new clause five,

1211673977
06:26:43.032 --> 06:26:46.531
which I will come on to
in in just a moment.

3318658079
06:26:46.532 --> 06:26:51.076
When I was debating another
piece of primary legislation,

270612223
06:26:51.077 --> 06:26:54.478
the Armed Forces Commissioner Bill,

1349739799
06:26:54.479 --> 06:26:57.038
now an act with the Minister
here some months ago,

2150088607
06:26:57.039 --> 06:27:00.034
he did make a commitment at that time that

2635007838
06:27:00.035 --> 06:27:02.578
the existing veterans
Commissioners for Scotland,

1585034269
06:27:02.579 --> 06:27:05.228
Wales and Northern Ireland
would be mirrored by

3774718995
06:27:05.229 --> 06:27:09.925
the appointment of a Veterans
Commissioner for England.

2998801212
06:27:09.926 --> 06:27:14.382
However, that appointment has
still not yet come to pass.

1196956477
06:27:14.383 --> 06:27:15.676
That being the case.

3280662210
06:27:15.677 --> 06:27:18.537
I wonder if the Minister could
explain to the House this

4131698722
06:27:18.538 --> 06:27:21.380
evening where the government
now sits on this issue.

4028244653
06:27:21.381 --> 06:27:24.173
When can we expect them
to honour their pledge

4015758594
06:27:24.174 --> 06:27:27.477
to create a Veterans
Commissioner for England?

3535567751
06:27:27.478 --> 06:27:31.082
And have they begun any interview process,

359914428
06:27:31.083 --> 06:27:35.031
at least to begin to identify
suitable candidates for such a role?

1073300594
06:27:35.032 --> 06:27:37.430
The government did give
their word on this,

2009362023
06:27:37.431 --> 06:27:39.990
so the whole House would
be grateful for an update

3266500034
06:27:39.990 --> 06:27:42.579
from the Minister on where
this matter now sits.

3398948722
06:27:42.579 --> 06:27:46.579
I'd now like to turn to New Clause
five, which was tabled by my hon.

3338534673
06:27:47.176 --> 06:27:48.880
Friend the Member for Huntingdon,

1174035015
06:27:48.881 --> 06:27:53.522
and which also has the support of
over 20 other members of the House.

3399962551
06:27:53.523 --> 06:27:57.425
The essence of this
amendment is that no fees

1167163150
06:27:57.426 --> 06:27:59.532
should be charged with respect to serving

3009931877
06:27:59.533 --> 06:28:01.689
or previously serving members of the armed

2841422057
06:28:01.690 --> 06:28:03.293
forces or their family members,

408914602
06:28:03.294 --> 06:28:07.081
applying for indefinite leave
to remain under the Immigration

3915688527
06:28:07.082 --> 06:28:12.780
Rules appendix for Her
Majesty's Armed Forces.

2480305238
06:28:12.781 --> 06:28:15.881
The effect of the new
clause in practical terms

2879585208
06:28:15.882 --> 06:28:18.530
would be to amend the Immigration Act,

3177059034
06:28:18.531 --> 06:28:22.382
2014 so that when members of
the Armed Forces applied for ILR

1440556990
06:28:22.383 --> 06:28:25.587
in return for their willingness
to have served the Crown,

1601923286
06:28:26.176 --> 06:28:29.386
the offender fees, the attendant
fees for this would be waived.

4133781005
06:28:29.387 --> 06:28:31.484
This is a particular issue for Gurkha

1192202050
06:28:31.485 --> 06:28:33.390
families and for foreign and foreign,

1199667614
06:28:34.176 --> 06:28:36.380
foreign and Commonwealth
personnel serving,

3121142449
06:28:36.381 --> 06:28:41.829
or who have served in the armed forces.

3727630133
06:28:41.831 --> 06:28:43.578
In addition, yes, I will.

1693811173
06:28:43.579 --> 06:28:44.583
>> I thank the hon.

3682976350
06:28:44.584 --> 06:28:46.430
Gentleman for giving way.

2417878269
06:28:46.431 --> 06:28:48.537
And he mentions the the Gurkha community,

3315133341
06:28:50.175 --> 06:28:52.233
and I want to pay tribute to the Queen's

2055653962
06:28:52.234 --> 06:28:54.540
Gurkha Regiment and
the 30th Signal Regiment,

1310019744
06:28:54.541 --> 06:28:57.427
based just outside my constituency.

2737688903
06:28:57.428 --> 06:28:57.879
But the.

808782381
06:28:57.880 --> 06:29:00.736
The Gurkhas who served.

3567321964
06:29:00.737 --> 06:29:04.432
There are an essential and integral
part of our community and really

2328010755
06:29:04.433 --> 06:29:08.081
do offer great value and
and integrate into the community.

2247974483
06:29:08.082 --> 06:29:10.441
So I'd like to to thank
him for for mentioning

290452212
06:29:10.442 --> 06:29:12.197
them and giving me the opportunity

586741088
06:29:12.198 --> 06:29:16.532
to pay tribute to those Gurkhas who
live in or around my constituency.

4219498927
06:29:16.533 --> 06:29:18.936
>> I thank you for that intervention,

2150336602
06:29:18.936 --> 06:29:22.049
which I think she may have been
here when we had a particular

2822486503
06:29:23.176 --> 06:29:25.333
debate about the history of the Gurkhas in

1817762739
06:29:25.334 --> 06:29:27.730
British service just a few months ago,

3106832380
06:29:27.731 --> 06:29:32.891
and I echo everything she says
about the bravest of the brave,

1903409686
06:29:32.892 --> 06:29:35.801
and I therefore look forward
to receiving her support for

3720253581
06:29:35.802 --> 06:29:40.626
this new clause in
the Division lobbies this evening.

1694096361
06:29:40.627 --> 06:29:45.131
This is something that the Royal
British Legion and Poppy Scotland have

435375842
06:29:45.132 --> 06:29:48.791
campaigned on for a number of years,
and so I want to commend my hon.

2662635090
06:29:48.792 --> 06:29:50.798
Friend for Huntingdon, for, as it were,

2747120171
06:29:52.176 --> 06:29:55.977
taking up the cudgels so effectively
on their behalf this afternoon,

2250642585
06:29:55.978 --> 06:30:00.182
as he's already argued powerfully,
governments of both colours

1402063539
06:30:00.183 --> 06:30:03.294
have indicated in the past that
they were minded to do this.

1739157995
06:30:05.180 --> 06:30:07.838
Indeed, it's worth reiterating
that this was in both

3326823341
06:30:10.182 --> 06:30:12.688
our and Labour's 2024
general election manifesto,

3630693674
06:30:15.176 --> 06:30:17.133
but it has still not yet come to pass.

2453316854
06:30:17.135 --> 06:30:20.536
Having re- examined this issue
again within Her Majesty's

2216374762
06:30:20.537 --> 06:30:23.780
opposition and consulted shadow
departmental colleagues,

2122463508
06:30:23.781 --> 06:30:26.584
I'm pleased to tell
the House that should my hon.

827203440
06:30:26.585 --> 06:30:28.440
Friend seek to press this amendment,

492064254
06:30:28.441 --> 06:30:31.536
and should you grant that
request, madam chairman,

4195663451
06:30:31.537 --> 06:30:34.056
we in the front bench will support it,

87945584
06:30:34.057 --> 06:30:38.431
and we would encourage all other
members of the House to do so, too.

3862954575
06:30:38.432 --> 06:30:43.525
We do this on the basis
that there would still,

2718894296
06:30:43.526 --> 06:30:45.484
in reality, be a cost for the process.

786369348
06:30:45.485 --> 06:30:49.880
But we believe that in return for
their service to this country,

4203334354
06:30:49.881 --> 06:30:54.282
the Ministry of Defence should absorb
that cost within its wider Budget,

906460164
06:30:54.283 --> 06:30:56.730
which would represent, on an annual basis,

4065483329
06:30:56.731 --> 06:30:58.988
a very modest outgoing
compared to the scale

1539452551
06:30:58.989 --> 06:31:02.091
of the defence Budget as a whole.

2225167238
06:31:02.092 --> 06:31:04.883
In other words, the Department
would bear the cost

1091228006
06:31:04.885 --> 06:31:08.932
and not those who have
served or their families

3240354502
06:31:08.933 --> 06:31:12.530
who should not be disadvantaged for having

273448831
06:31:12.531 --> 06:31:15.630
offered to serve this country in uniform.

3708783629
06:31:15.631 --> 06:31:16.032
My hon.

3805733112
06:31:16.033 --> 06:31:18.981
Friend for Huntingdon put
the case extremely well,

1028446302
06:31:18.982 --> 06:31:21.579
and therefore I won't try the House's

4143547309
06:31:21.581 --> 06:31:23.386
patience by repeating it all again.

1998453144
06:31:23.387 --> 06:31:28.238
But suffice to say, I do believe there's
a strong moral case to do this,

1679056511
06:31:28.239 --> 06:31:31.182
and I very much hope that
the government might be

3132309517
06:31:31.183 --> 06:31:33.932
prepared to accept this
amendment on that basis.

1266981982
06:31:33.933 --> 06:31:38.735
But if that's not the case, I hope
then he will press it tonight,

153200892
06:31:38.736 --> 06:31:41.785
in which case I hope that
the whole House might

2731283437
06:31:41.786 --> 06:31:45.284
find it in their hearts to support it.

1762367736
06:31:45.285 --> 06:31:47.391
Madam chairman, I now turn to opposition.

204513460
06:31:47.392 --> 06:31:49.900
New clause six and our
associated new clause one,

2594998034
06:31:49.900 --> 06:31:53.332
which relate to the operation
of the European Convention on

3583472885
06:31:53.333 --> 06:31:56.935
Human Rights and its effects
on Armed Forces personnel,

1211539713
06:31:56.936 --> 06:31:59.391
including potentially those
reservists who might

483420444
06:31:59.392 --> 06:32:02.793
be mobilised under
the auspices of this Bill.

175848238
06:32:02.793 --> 06:32:06.037
How did we get to the situation
in which we are today,

3329143000
06:32:06.038 --> 06:32:09.033
where the European
Convention on Human Rights,

780655549
06:32:09.034 --> 06:32:11.483
the ECA, has spread to the battlefield

2644714474
06:32:11.484 --> 06:32:14.882
not just within Europe but globally?

462647550
06:32:14.882 --> 06:32:16.537
The history is significant here,

1889606292
06:32:16.538 --> 06:32:21.827
and it lies behind why we have
tabled these two new clauses.

554841242
06:32:21.828 --> 06:32:26.883
It all came about because of
something called the Algida case,

1602391905
06:32:26.885 --> 06:32:29.240
which was heard before
the Appellate Committee

3384979044
06:32:29.242 --> 06:32:30.949
of the House of Lords a couple of

2968837667
06:32:30.950 --> 06:32:32.956
years or so before the United Kingdom's

1793844482
06:32:34.180 --> 06:32:36.186
Supreme Court was created back in 2009.

1770669867
06:32:36.186 --> 06:32:39.688
The Algida case was about
the treatment of a prisoner

3335706508
06:32:42.185 --> 06:32:44.240
detained in Iraq during Operation Telic,

779788700
06:32:44.240 --> 06:32:49.579
and was brought by a now disgraced
lawyer called Phil Shiner.

678258171
06:32:49.579 --> 06:32:51.436
His name will be known to anyone who

309516049
06:32:51.438 --> 06:32:53.835
has ever served in the British Army.

1172112098
06:32:53.836 --> 06:32:56.686
For the record, shiner was
subsequently convicted of

348994722
06:32:56.688 --> 06:33:03.044
fraud and was struck off
as a practising solicitor.

3818196275
06:33:03.046 --> 06:33:05.783
Phil Shiner instructed
legal counsel to put

578539008
06:33:05.784 --> 06:33:09.585
forward his case to the House of Lords,

3205450740
06:33:09.586 --> 06:33:11.481
the lead appellant in that case,

1258761497
06:33:11.482 --> 06:33:13.538
before he became a member of Parliament,

721951554
06:33:15.184 --> 06:33:17.792
was one Keir Starmer QC,
the Minister for veterans.

944003795
06:33:18.180 --> 06:33:21.579
And people got into some
trouble over this because

2716860247
06:33:21.581 --> 06:33:23.637
when we highlighted this in the Commons,

3933985554
06:33:25.180 --> 06:33:28.040
she was adamant that he had
not been working for shiner.

3222267929
06:33:29.179 --> 06:33:32.288
Unfortunately for the Minister,
we had the court records from

2454196290
06:33:32.289 --> 06:33:35.780
the House of Lords which show
very clearly that Keir Starmer,

234351999
06:33:35.781 --> 06:33:42.689
as he then was, was the lead
appellant, appointed and instructed.

257085776
06:33:43.180 --> 06:33:47.682
That word is used in
the records by Phil Shiner's,

1513443527
06:33:47.683 --> 06:33:49.387
law firm Public Interest Lawyers.

3922591167
06:33:49.388 --> 06:33:52.686
The Minister for veterans
subsequently had to come to

3366700379
06:33:52.688 --> 06:33:55.546
the Commons in February
and go through the embarrassment

1670464746
06:33:55.547 --> 06:33:58.507
of having to correct the record
and admit that our version

2220607316
06:33:58.507 --> 06:34:02.042
of events has explained
to the Commons was true.

1763017809
06:34:02.043 --> 06:34:04.982
Nevertheless, Phil Shiner
was a persistent man,

243720192
06:34:04.983 --> 06:34:06.888
particularly when money was at stake.

2304836707
06:34:07.180 --> 06:34:09.889
So, several years after
losing in the House of Lords,

3439304035
06:34:09.890 --> 06:34:13.583
he took the case to the European
Court of Human Rights in Strasbourg.

2449508956
06:34:13.584 --> 06:34:18.387
And to be clear, Keir Starmer
was not acting in that action.

4215101418
06:34:21.184 --> 06:34:21.785
Shiner won.

3708916024
06:34:21.786 --> 06:34:25.640
So the Strasbourg court ruled that
the ECHR would then apply to any

3035259972
06:34:25.641 --> 06:34:30.439
theatre in which British armed
forces personnel were serving.

147377742
06:34:32.184 --> 06:34:33.386
Through that judgement.

621463029
06:34:33.387 --> 06:34:36.881
They effectively created an industry that

1760629414
06:34:36.882 --> 06:34:38.535
shiner then massively exploited.

2793149660
06:34:38.536 --> 06:34:43.584
He brought literally hundreds
of cases against current

961670220
06:34:43.585 --> 06:34:45.640
and past British armed forces personnel.

1294051212
06:34:45.641 --> 06:34:51.132
Many of the cases were funded by
British taxpayers through legal aid,

1582972473
06:34:51.133 --> 06:34:57.286
and were completely
and utterly fabricated for money.

2610492186
06:34:57.287 --> 06:35:01.597
It was the use of the ECA
that allowed him to do that.

713588276
06:35:01.597 --> 06:35:04.858
In other debates in the chamber,
we have heard senior Ministers,

3770508513
06:35:05.184 --> 06:35:07.941
including the Secretary of
State for Northern Ireland,

3506794565
06:35:09.184 --> 06:35:14.334
say that there is no such thing
as a vexatious prosecution.

2123104782
06:35:14.335 --> 06:35:17.840
Self-evidently there must be,
because otherwise why was shiner

1968329121
06:35:17.841 --> 06:35:21.591
struck off a convicted of
fraud by a court of law?

3989158116
06:35:21.592 --> 06:35:22.293
There can be.

1341099321
06:35:22.294 --> 06:35:28.834
In fact, there were hundreds
of vexatious prosecutions

3164776698
06:35:28.835 --> 06:35:30.638
against British military personnel.

1794422265
06:35:30.639 --> 06:35:32.740
It was, for the record, Johnny Mercer,

3614411091
06:35:32.740 --> 06:35:35.488
a former member of this
House when he served

1275112134
06:35:35.489 --> 06:35:38.986
on the defence Committee some years ago,

2495729971
06:35:38.987 --> 06:35:42.178
who led a subcommittee
investigation into this issue.

1464381670
06:35:42.179 --> 06:35:43.181
It's very powerful.

66715624
06:35:43.182 --> 06:35:45.746
Report helped to bring shiner to book.

1778442807
06:35:45.747 --> 06:35:48.689
No doubt saving
the taxpayer a lot more money

4292109942
06:35:48.690 --> 06:35:53.988
and leading to Shiner's
career ending in disgrace.

3563673663
06:35:53.989 --> 06:35:57.037
But to come to the present day,

4025856798
06:35:57.038 --> 06:35:59.739
what if there were a ceasefire in Ukraine?

4099441296
06:35:59.740 --> 06:36:03.990
Let us posit a situation in which,
under the auspices of the coalition

936921781
06:36:03.990 --> 06:36:08.790
of the willing British service
personnel were deployed to Ukraine.

4240075064
06:36:08.791 --> 06:36:10.696
If, by some happenstance, they became

2185135517
06:36:10.697 --> 06:36:13.441
involved in a firefight with Russian

2313398726
06:36:13.442 --> 06:36:17.112
troops who perhaps had incurred
across the line of ceasefire,

606260963
06:36:17.113 --> 06:36:21.039
who is to say that years,
maybe decades later,

2133572847
06:36:21.040 --> 06:36:25.585
those personnel will not end up
in a court of law for obeying

1777914921
06:36:25.586 --> 06:36:28.588
what they believe to be
perfectly legitimate orders,

1406577022
06:36:28.589 --> 06:36:33.237
but was subsequently second
guessed by human rights lawyer.

873999197
06:36:33.238 --> 06:36:37.436
Literally decades on, perhaps
with Russian assistance.

3422797262
06:36:37.438 --> 06:36:43.492
In short, we cannot allow this
government's obsession with human rights

3184053817
06:36:43.493 --> 06:36:49.946
to put our armed forces at risk,
either now or in the future,

1139084517
06:36:49.947 --> 06:36:51.852
or indeed, historically, in a moment,

3392372973
06:36:52.184 --> 06:36:56.685
and potentially force them
to fight ruthless opponents

4127280965
06:36:56.686 --> 06:36:58.542
with one arm tied behind their back.

3406498344
06:36:58.543 --> 06:37:03.407
This issue is not going to go away,
and at some point the government,

2774257645
06:37:03.408 --> 06:37:06.035
be it through
the Northern Ireland Troubles

425719392
06:37:06.036 --> 06:37:07.540
Bill or some other mechanism,

3118052273
06:37:07.541 --> 06:37:09.292
will be forced to address it.

1791460986
06:37:09.293 --> 06:37:15.493
The purpose of these new clauses is
to force them to address it today.

3515204477
06:37:16.186 --> 06:37:18.596
Yes, I was going to give
that, but no sign yet.

1918417186
06:37:19.192 --> 06:37:20.648
>> I am grateful to the hon.

2644568656
06:37:20.649 --> 06:37:21.952
Gentleman for giving way.

3702987968
06:37:21.953 --> 06:37:24.889
If I if I might just quote
a few words from the hon.

1878969757
06:37:24.890 --> 06:37:26.794
Member for Huntingdon, who spoke just

1039022434
06:37:27.184 --> 06:37:29.191
a couple of months ago in this chamber.

2446856269
06:37:29.192 --> 06:37:33.639
He said at the time this month
marks 20 years since I returned

3837613914
06:37:33.640 --> 06:37:35.997
from serving in Operation
Telic seven in Iraq.

906559422
06:37:35.998 --> 06:37:40.190
While I was there, we patrolled
Basra and snatch Land Rovers,

3497849660
06:37:40.191 --> 06:37:42.799
and 34 British soldiers
died in Snatch Land Rovers.

4208857924
06:37:42.800 --> 06:37:47.246
They were called mobile coffins
and suicide wagons for a reason.

4136065233
06:37:47.247 --> 06:37:49.554
In 2006, it was highlighted
to the government

3838060131
06:37:49.555 --> 06:37:51.409
that those vehicles were unsuitable,

2548964182
06:37:51.410 --> 06:37:54.320
and it was not until years
later that they were replaced.

175487560
06:37:54.321 --> 06:37:58.893
It wasn't the ECHR that put British
soldiers lives at risk in Iraq,

2014080896
06:37:59.144 --> 06:38:02.685
but it was the ECHR that
provided the legal basis for

4290919837
06:38:02.686 --> 06:38:05.638
the families of those
victims to seek justice.

592113949
06:38:05.639 --> 06:38:07.695
I think the gentleman is looking through

2273749040
06:38:08.188 --> 06:38:10.396
the wrong end of
the telescope on this one,

4107710082
06:38:10.397 --> 06:38:13.690
and that by seeking by seeking
to remove the US from the ECHR,

2531111407
06:38:13.691 --> 06:38:16.398
he potentially puts British
service people at greater

307056640
06:38:16.399 --> 06:38:20.788
risk than he does offer them protection.

2943091896
06:38:20.789 --> 06:38:24.583
>> I think, if I may say so,
it's extremely sad that the hon.

3912741019
06:38:24.584 --> 06:38:28.293
Gentleman is seeking to conflate
two completely different issues.

124229434
06:38:28.294 --> 06:38:34.538
And I think anyone who's actually
served on Operation Telic,

3730589874
06:38:34.539 --> 06:38:36.243
I suspect, would understand that.

3119388002
06:38:36.244 --> 06:38:38.503
So having made the point,
let me now turn to

1451191966
06:38:38.504 --> 06:38:43.188
our opposition new
clause two, which would.

3819886801
06:38:43.189 --> 06:38:45.847
No, I'm just going to make
some progress which would

2143989154
06:38:45.849 --> 06:38:48.357
require the Secretary of
State for defence to lay

2083545203
06:38:48.358 --> 06:38:52.745
a defence investment plan or dip
for short before Parliament

1642024932
06:38:54.185 --> 06:38:56.343
within a month of the passage of this act.

1317551180
06:38:56.344 --> 06:38:59.390
If it still hadn't been
published by then, which,

473856243
06:38:59.391 --> 06:39:02.103
for reasons I will come on to in a minute,

1709815365
06:39:02.104 --> 06:39:07.693
is not as fantastical as it might seem.

2759636449
06:39:07.694 --> 06:39:12.847
For context, today, the 2nd of June
2026, is the one year anniversary of

3838237182
06:39:12.849 --> 06:39:14.904
the publication of the government's much

1990998967
06:39:17.188 --> 06:39:18.891
vaunted Strategic Defence Review.

2637539185
06:39:18.892 --> 06:39:19.794
There is the SDR.

2591364031
06:39:20.189 --> 06:39:24.738
There's a lot of good in
the document, but one of the criticisms

236910363
06:39:24.739 --> 06:39:27.838
at the time was that
much of the programmatic

2286667180
06:39:27.839 --> 06:39:32.392
detail setting out which new
equipment the government intended

1768968231
06:39:32.393 --> 06:39:34.700
to purchase for our armed
forces was omitted.

4038860239
06:39:34.701 --> 06:39:39.190
For instance, the government
talked about buying

2032613848
06:39:39.191 --> 06:39:43.790
up to 12 new nuclear attack submarines.

156277840
06:39:43.791 --> 06:39:45.145
Well, that could mean two.

2891506319
06:39:45.146 --> 06:39:49.043
But all of this detail
was going to be provided

2257610587
06:39:49.044 --> 06:39:54.440
in the Defence Investment Plan.

2242676100
06:39:54.441 --> 06:39:59.843
But one year on from today, it
has still not been published.

184056743
06:39:59.844 --> 06:40:02.550
This has drawn very serious criticism from

3286602539
06:40:02.551 --> 06:40:05.088
right across the defence industry,

4169362509
06:40:05.089 --> 06:40:09.789
and also from the authors
of the SDR itself.

969919330
06:40:09.790 --> 06:40:14.737
Indeed, the lead author, Lord Robertson,

2771878682
06:40:14.738 --> 06:40:16.793
a lifelong Labour man to his fingertips,

1716808193
06:40:16.794 --> 06:40:20.194
has accused the Prime
Minister of, I quote,

1269160777
06:40:20.195 --> 06:40:22.944
corrosive complacency
because of the ongoing

369241763
06:40:22.945 --> 06:40:25.392
delay in saying how the government will

68095784
06:40:25.393 --> 06:40:28.939
fund the Strategic Defence Review

299798522
06:40:28.940 --> 06:40:31.043
and its attendant equipment requirements.

298477103
06:40:32.189 --> 06:40:33.593
When we were in government,

1085981134
06:40:33.594 --> 06:40:37.145
we used to publish a ten
year plan for the future

2385434643
06:40:37.146 --> 06:40:45.995
purchase of military equipment
universally known as the equipment plan.

4199841511
06:40:45.996 --> 06:40:47.301
In a moment, in a moment.

270707451
06:40:47.302 --> 06:40:52.549
This allowed industry to make rational
decisions about where to invest.

2601854383
06:40:52.550 --> 06:40:55.007
It helped improve
the morale of our armed forces

155025490
06:40:55.008 --> 06:40:57.316
by letting them know
about the new equipment,

1027870972
06:40:57.317 --> 06:40:59.624
which they could expect
to come into service,

1712111138
06:41:00.150 --> 06:41:02.107
and it also had an important deterrent

572407941
06:41:02.108 --> 06:41:05.693
effect on our potential adversaries.

3132922003
06:41:05.694 --> 06:41:09.046
By laying out exactly what we intended

1006275075
06:41:09.047 --> 06:41:10.904
to buy for the defence of the realm.

3680031922
06:41:11.189 --> 06:41:13.346
All of these things I'm giving away their.

3259313338
06:41:15.190 --> 06:41:19.043
All of these things have now been
put at risk by the government's

3813052272
06:41:19.043 --> 06:41:23.790
endless prevarication
and inaction for a year.

1313415735
06:41:23.791 --> 06:41:24.393
I give way.

1409188366
06:41:24.394 --> 06:41:24.794
>> Hon.

2188091491
06:41:24.796 --> 06:41:25.196
Member.

1589647439
06:41:25.197 --> 06:41:26.994
>> For giving way.

3060773463
06:41:26.995 --> 06:41:31.301
>> Will he just confirm that
on arrival in government,

2436363616
06:41:31.302 --> 06:41:36.144
the now recognised that the previous
government and the right hon.

2621729430
06:41:36.145 --> 06:41:44.449
Member sat to his left,
left an equipment plan with

559040603
06:41:44.450 --> 06:41:47.146
7 to £28 billion gap,
as stated by the Nao.

2847756173
06:41:47.147 --> 06:41:50.541
Is that correct or otherwise?

2963512362
06:41:50.542 --> 06:41:57.551
>> As a matter of fact, that is not
how I interpret what the Nao said.

2281703099
06:41:58.189 --> 06:41:58.791
Not at all.

2415450117
06:41:58.792 --> 06:42:00.597
But the house may remember we were.

2471087676
06:42:00.599 --> 06:42:02.002
No, he's had his go.

1562183896
06:42:02.003 --> 06:42:02.755
The house may.

3251555171
06:42:02.756 --> 06:42:04.109
Remember we were promised.

1311339566
06:42:04.110 --> 06:42:06.167
The dip will be published in the autumn.

3470464874
06:42:06.189 --> 06:42:08.742
Then we were faithfully
promised it by Christmas,

508364940
06:42:08.743 --> 06:42:10.197
and then we were absolutely,

1068760176
06:42:10.198 --> 06:42:12.846
definitely going to get
it in the New Year.

2725649627
06:42:12.847 --> 06:42:15.900
But here we are in June
and incredibly still no dip.

4244138410
06:42:15.901 --> 06:42:19.995
The reason for this is simple.

4108753313
06:42:19.996 --> 06:42:20.246
Yes.

1268178168
06:42:20.247 --> 06:42:26.401
>> But has he had a chance to look
at the report published by tech UK,

1432029129
06:42:27.188 --> 06:42:29.646
which represents a lot of
small and medium sized

1401056006
06:42:31.193 --> 06:42:33.097
companies in the defence tech sector,

4119980001
06:42:33.099 --> 06:42:35.557
and seen what they have
to say objectively about

2413396843
06:42:35.558 --> 06:42:38.268
the number of jobs that are
being lost in the sector,

4053996803
06:42:38.269 --> 06:42:40.175
the lack of investment in the sector,

1680521303
06:42:40.176 --> 06:42:42.704
the pressure that their
members are coming under

4199369928
06:42:42.704 --> 06:42:47.050
and the lack of viability
for the sector given this,

3824554159
06:42:47.051 --> 06:42:49.093
continued unbearable delay.

2092010185
06:42:49.094 --> 06:42:50.146
They need certainty.

3687395028
06:42:50.147 --> 06:42:51.653
When are we going to have it?

2754603926
06:42:51.654 --> 06:42:53.561
>> Well, I totally agree with my hon.

26122546
06:42:53.561 --> 06:42:53.962
Friend.

1962215612
06:42:53.963 --> 06:42:57.275
And of course, we'd all like to
know when we're going to have it,

2966580924
06:42:57.276 --> 06:42:59.502
but the reason we haven't
got it is simple.

1516595090
06:42:59.503 --> 06:43:00.004
It's not.

201312647
06:43:00.005 --> 06:43:01.910
The staff work hasn't been completed.

3749721979
06:43:01.911 --> 06:43:02.311
It has.

2251212280
06:43:02.313 --> 06:43:02.814
It's not.

1052832288
06:43:02.815 --> 06:43:04.796
The programmes haven't been costed.

530796952
06:43:04.797 --> 06:43:05.347
They have.

3803875901
06:43:05.349 --> 06:43:08.458
The fundamental problem is that
while Ministers are flat out,

4014729986
06:43:08.459 --> 06:43:10.414
they're knocking themselves out on it.

3800618063
06:43:10.415 --> 06:43:14.499
They're reduced to euphemisms
about how hard they're working.

1658034772
06:43:16.194 --> 06:43:17.849
It was actually done months ago.

346930841
06:43:17.850 --> 06:43:20.257
The problem, Madam Chairman,
is that the chance

2528463989
06:43:20.257 --> 06:43:22.696
of the Exchequer adamantly
refuses to sign it,

4004690662
06:43:22.697 --> 06:43:24.745
because then if she signed it,

575560787
06:43:24.746 --> 06:43:28.946
she'd have to say how she's
going to pay for it.

111217328
06:43:28.947 --> 06:43:32.293
That's why MoD Ministers
are completely hidebound,

4036032391
06:43:32.294 --> 06:43:35.395
because the Prime Minister
won't force the Chancellor to

4092693175
06:43:35.396 --> 06:43:39.400
sign the equipment plan for
the Armed Forces of the United Kingdom,

1375616671
06:43:39.400 --> 06:43:42.748
and the delay is now becoming a farce.

1052733036
06:43:42.749 --> 06:43:48.694
Indeed, we're now being widely criticised
by our international partners,

2729365401
06:43:48.695 --> 06:43:52.792
including just the other
day, the chairman of

3864454100
06:43:52.793 --> 06:43:56.743
the NATO military committee
at Defence Questions.

3573088537
06:43:56.744 --> 06:43:59.650
The Secretary of State was
adamant that the Prime

599571229
06:43:59.651 --> 06:44:02.588
Minister wanted it published
by the NATO summit,

482192196
06:44:02.589 --> 06:44:07.542
which raises two questions
which NATO summit

1773357019
06:44:07.543 --> 06:44:09.148
is it and which Prime Minister?

1472384458
06:44:09.149 --> 06:44:14.844
Assuming he means the summit in
Ankara on the 7th to 8th of July,

1430861808
06:44:14.845 --> 06:44:18.745
that means this vital document will
be delayed for yet another month.

2552234206
06:44:18.746 --> 06:44:21.897
And it's worse, because
last year there were £2.6

3509196582
06:44:21.898 --> 06:44:26.492
billion of in-year operational cuts,

3530055621
06:44:26.493 --> 06:44:30.555
and this year it's 3.5 billion of
in year cuts to the defence Budget.

1021710217
06:44:30.556 --> 06:44:32.900
So we will press this amendment this

37875839
06:44:32.901 --> 06:44:36.200
evening to force a vote in the House

1397776979
06:44:36.201 --> 06:44:41.699
on a backstop plan to produce the dip
to remind His Majesty's Treasury.

3209643187
06:44:42.192 --> 06:44:44.148
The first duty of government above all

3030324400
06:44:44.149 --> 06:44:45.954
others is the defence of the realm,

584571535
06:44:45.956 --> 06:44:48.615
and you can't defend
the realm with a lot of bluster

3694467850
06:44:48.617 --> 06:44:52.311
and an equipment plan
which does not exist.

2655582405
06:44:52.311 --> 06:44:53.516
>> Yeah yeah yeah yeah.

1794017321
06:44:56.195 --> 06:44:56.846
>> Minister.

2217810106
06:44:56.847 --> 06:45:00.308
>> I thank all members who have
spoken today for their contributions

516419264
06:45:00.309 --> 06:45:03.959
and for upholding the cross-party
support for our armed forces.

3762090354
06:45:03.960 --> 06:45:06.216
This bill makes significant
steps to improve

1339985484
06:45:06.217 --> 06:45:07.771
the conditions of service life

3651794229
06:45:07.772 --> 06:45:11.233
and renews the contract between our
nation and with those who serve.

356122248
06:45:11.234 --> 06:45:14.844
It delivers on a manifesto promise
to extend the Armed Forces

2503199523
06:45:14.845 --> 06:45:18.199
Covenant to every area of
government, 3 to 12 policy areas.

2162776312
06:45:18.200 --> 06:45:19.203
We will go further.

3390198542
06:45:19.204 --> 06:45:22.012
Backed by £9 billion Defence
Housing Strategy to build,

1720454159
06:45:22.191 --> 06:45:24.548
renew and repair tens of
thousands of military

407422074
06:45:24.549 --> 06:45:26.453
homes where modernising and improving

2682916907
06:45:26.454 --> 06:45:28.459
victim support and ensuring the service

3981593206
06:45:28.460 --> 06:45:30.703
justice system is able to protect

1498302206
06:45:30.704 --> 06:45:33.713
the victims of the most serious
offences from further harm.

762795981
06:45:33.714 --> 06:45:36.700
We will expand the reserve
Poole by changing the maximum

50908339
06:45:36.701 --> 06:45:39.796
age limit to which some
personnel can be recalled,

3376353350
06:45:39.797 --> 06:45:42.207
as we would, if needed,
be able to call on some

3338509127
06:45:42.208 --> 06:45:44.898
of the most experienced
volunteer reservists.

1936464732
06:45:44.899 --> 06:45:47.556
These are significant
but necessary changes to boost

3522716258
06:45:47.557 --> 06:45:50.064
preparedness in an era of
ever increasing threat.

2589100347
06:45:50.065 --> 06:45:54.553
I'll now address some of the major
issues highlighted in the debate.

2422438949
06:45:54.554 --> 06:45:56.761
I will begin by addressing
new clause five.

907257750
06:45:56.762 --> 06:46:01.157
I have served all over
the world with Gurkhas,

1016965495
06:46:01.158 --> 06:46:03.212
Fijians and broader Commonwealth troops.

2941494334
06:46:03.213 --> 06:46:06.373
They serve our country and they
serve with honour and courage.

2731082412
06:46:06.374 --> 06:46:10.050
In the very least we can do is
help them and their dependents

476831931
06:46:10.051 --> 06:46:12.308
scrap visa fees after
four years of service.

862050650
06:46:12.309 --> 06:46:13.713
This is not about politics.

4067047338
06:46:13.714 --> 06:46:15.620
It is not about a difference opinion.

576265270
06:46:15.621 --> 06:46:18.078
It is about language
and bounding the commitment

1797097215
06:46:18.079 --> 06:46:20.048
in the legislation in the correct way.

162652604
06:46:20.049 --> 06:46:22.557
There is already a settlement
fee waiver in place

3863407974
06:46:22.558 --> 06:46:24.663
for serving personnel introduced in 2022,

1814454619
06:46:24.664 --> 06:46:28.175
to recognise the burden of settlement
fees at the point of discharge.

3980122287
06:46:28.176 --> 06:46:30.758
For those who have served
for six or more years or

3929562802
06:46:30.760 --> 06:46:33.849
been medically discharged
due to their service.

3882588585
06:46:33.850 --> 06:46:36.303
However, that fee waiver did not extend

2918144851
06:46:36.304 --> 06:46:39.097
to dependants or recognise service

1330556989
06:46:39.099 --> 06:46:41.354
personnel who became
eligible for settlement

195161403
06:46:41.355 --> 06:46:42.809
after four years of service.

3150192325
06:46:42.810 --> 06:46:45.017
That is why this
government is committed to

2032309144
06:46:45.018 --> 06:46:47.074
scrap the visa fees for non-UK veterans,

3851550836
06:46:47.075 --> 06:46:49.082
who have served for four years or more,

314208397
06:46:49.083 --> 06:46:51.740
and their dependents
and Home Office and Ministry of

23738660
06:46:51.742 --> 06:46:54.198
Defence are working closely
together to deliver.

2983184114
06:46:54.199 --> 06:46:55.052
In my right hon.

2217279049
06:46:55.053 --> 06:46:57.861
Friend met with the Home
Office Minister just recently.

2762517725
06:46:57.862 --> 06:47:00.118
We remain firmly committed
to this manifesto

3865110681
06:47:00.119 --> 06:47:02.126
pledge and we will fully deliver on it.

2326507666
06:47:02.127 --> 06:47:04.533
I understand the intention
behind the amendment

2686983027
06:47:04.534 --> 06:47:06.590
and the desire to make progress quickly.

1461355319
06:47:06.591 --> 06:47:08.696
However, as drafted drafted the language,

2999440585
06:47:08.697 --> 06:47:10.702
this amendment does not clearly achieve

1363546580
06:47:10.703 --> 06:47:13.611
the intent set out by
the member's explanatory statement,

697944996
06:47:13.612 --> 06:47:15.115
which appears to be narrower.

1427323374
06:47:15.117 --> 06:47:18.325
While the explanatory statement
refers to spouses and children,

2745216207
06:47:18.326 --> 06:47:21.485
the clause itself appears to waive
fees for serving personnel.

2754123228
06:47:21.486 --> 06:47:23.841
Previously, service
personnel and their family

1187173953
06:47:23.842 --> 06:47:26.147
members using broad
and undefined categories,

834032434
06:47:26.148 --> 06:47:28.504
creating significant
uncertainty and a lack of

2454979693
06:47:28.505 --> 06:47:31.519
clarity about who precisely
is within scope.

1981957155
06:47:31.520 --> 06:47:34.648
It also contains no clear
link to length of service,

3317564231
06:47:34.649 --> 06:47:36.253
a time limited after discharge.

2858265674
06:47:36.254 --> 06:47:40.757
Taken together, this risk
creating a broader and unclear

3387506999
06:47:40.757 --> 06:47:43.311
statutory entitlement with
unintended consequences

784911246
06:47:43.313 --> 06:47:45.820
rather than a targeted
and coherent measure which

824999480
06:47:45.821 --> 06:47:48.176
families and dependents
can easily understand.

1394010282
06:47:48.177 --> 06:47:49.783
I will give way in two seconds.

1323533500
06:47:49.784 --> 06:47:52.893
In addition, section 68 of
the Immigration Act 2014 provides.

497528069
06:47:53.197 --> 06:47:56.797
The fee exemption should be set
out in secondary legislation

3271377651
06:47:56.798 --> 06:48:00.007
by introducing a fee exemption
into 2014 act itself.

3495116305
06:48:00.007 --> 06:48:02.648
This amendment would cut across existing

237259006
06:48:02.649 --> 06:48:04.603
statutory framework and reduce clarity

1402980167
06:48:04.604 --> 06:48:06.860
in the fee structure by
creating alternative

3210357188
06:48:06.861 --> 06:48:08.464
mechanism for controlling fees.

1674466266
06:48:08.465 --> 06:48:10.570
The government is committed to delivering

3649153832
06:48:10.571 --> 06:48:12.275
the manifesto commitment in full,

519683639
06:48:12.275 --> 06:48:14.382
and it is important that Ministers retain

1943623687
06:48:14.382 --> 06:48:16.789
the ability to determine
the appropriate scope,

1993775080
06:48:16.790 --> 06:48:21.202
the eligibility and delivery
approach so it's implemented fairly.

800266383
06:48:21.203 --> 06:48:22.056
I will give way.

811283853
06:48:22.057 --> 06:48:24.064
>> I thank the Minister for giving way,

358946192
06:48:24.065 --> 06:48:26.851
and I recognise that he
wants to deliver this

4204862536
06:48:26.852 --> 06:48:28.757
manifesto commitment as much as I do.

1555469739
06:48:28.758 --> 06:48:30.916
I would ask him, however, given that after

508981593
06:48:31.158 --> 06:48:33.063
two years we've made little progress,

2690900002
06:48:33.064 --> 06:48:37.597
mostly due to the machinery of
government within the Home Office.

333922286
06:48:37.599 --> 06:48:41.349
This was obviously tabled some time
ago and the government has had

3709897720
06:48:41.350 --> 06:48:44.359
ample opportunity to refine
the detail of this amendment in

1814856551
06:48:44.360 --> 06:48:47.706
order to make it acceptable
and delivered in such a way that it

1710239451
06:48:48.196 --> 06:48:51.256
could be voted on this evening
and passed by the government.

2502740344
06:48:51.257 --> 06:48:52.261
So could he ask me?

3025446258
06:48:52.262 --> 06:48:55.122
Could he answer me why
the government has taken no steps

1123535594
06:48:55.123 --> 06:48:57.834
to work with me in order to
get this across the line,

1557250165
06:48:57.835 --> 06:49:00.654
given that it is a manifesto
pledge of the government?

2081958135
06:49:01.156 --> 06:49:03.463
And also, can he give
some expectation around

4265358368
06:49:03.464 --> 06:49:05.871
the timeline about when
this will be delivered?

3101010049
06:49:05.872 --> 06:49:10.047
If the government chooses wrongfully
to vote against it this evening?

2536269507
06:49:10.048 --> 06:49:13.309
>> We need to move this legislation
forward in the right manner.

4221444928
06:49:13.310 --> 06:49:17.112
We will do so, and we're going to move
this forward as fast as possible.

961706966
06:49:17.113 --> 06:49:20.154
What I would recommend is
continue to push on this case.

3119732924
06:49:20.155 --> 06:49:21.108
Myself and my hon.

2965613543
06:49:21.109 --> 06:49:23.065
Friend, have heard you loud and clear.

659098676
06:49:23.066 --> 06:49:25.925
We have heard the Armed Forces
community loud and clear,

434002412
06:49:25.926 --> 06:49:29.136
and we're committed to delivering
this in line with the intent.

2021125541
06:49:29.137 --> 06:49:30.490
Turning to new clause two.

2947513872
06:49:30.492 --> 06:49:31.495
I'll make some way.

1345690985
06:49:31.496 --> 06:49:31.946
Turning.

1737139939
06:49:31.947 --> 06:49:32.950
I'll make some way.

2355191880
06:49:32.951 --> 06:49:34.305
Turning to New Clause two.

889387688
06:49:34.306 --> 06:49:37.266
This would require the Secretary
of State to lay a defence

2165650396
06:49:37.267 --> 06:49:39.722
investment plan before
the Houses of Parliament.

252213342
06:49:39.724 --> 06:49:41.680
The Prime Minister has been very clear

2471087569
06:49:41.681 --> 06:49:43.586
that the Defence Investment Plan will

1808534756
06:49:43.587 --> 06:49:45.442
be published before the NATO summit,

1097434300
06:49:45.443 --> 06:49:47.399
which we are working hard to finalise.

3281154197
06:49:47.400 --> 06:49:50.160
What I would recommend is
that he reads the Nao office

1625757747
06:49:50.161 --> 06:49:52.267
report that when we came into government,

2849453425
06:49:52.268 --> 06:49:57.748
it left a huge deficit
and that 47 out of 49,

1267752491
06:49:57.749 --> 06:50:03.163
47 out of 49 major programmes,
not on Budget nor on time.

3081321992
06:50:03.164 --> 06:50:06.002
I now turn to new clause
one and new clause six.

3782850556
06:50:06.003 --> 06:50:09.453
I will give way to
the Minister for giving way.

2316740055
06:50:09.454 --> 06:50:11.852
>> Has he and the Veterans Minister now

255631116
06:50:11.853 --> 06:50:13.557
seen the Defence Investment Plan?

2138319356
06:50:13.558 --> 06:50:17.859
>> So I'd like to commend
what is a fantastic question.

516471466
06:50:17.860 --> 06:50:22.051
Yes, I have seen the Defence
Investment Plan and importantly,

1328067660
06:50:22.052 --> 06:50:24.797
primarily focussed on learning the lessons

543882499
06:50:24.798 --> 06:50:26.503
from Ukraine and acting upon them

2292851381
06:50:27.201 --> 06:50:31.158
something that the last government
failed to do at the right scale.

1509221508
06:50:31.159 --> 06:50:33.700
Hence the reason I left the military.

3351856323
06:50:33.701 --> 06:50:36.161
I now turn to new clause
one and new clause six,

4099876097
06:50:36.162 --> 06:50:38.600
which seek to exempt
members of the reserve

3287240264
06:50:38.601 --> 06:50:40.104
forces deployed in operations

4228631065
06:50:40.105 --> 06:50:43.708
from the ECHR and require any
future Secretary of State to

4251040266
06:50:43.709 --> 06:50:46.806
consider whether to make
a derogation under article 15.

191332599
06:50:46.807 --> 06:50:47.810
The UK was binding.

681765205
06:50:47.811 --> 06:50:50.604
Has binding international
obligations under the ECHR,

666449766
06:50:50.605 --> 06:50:54.453
including in limited
extraterritorial circumstances where

371787742
06:50:54.454 --> 06:50:57.403
we exercise control over
individuals or areas.

1919873124
06:50:57.404 --> 06:51:00.362
Those obligations have implications
for the way UK forces,

339298970
06:51:00.363 --> 06:51:02.818
including reserve forces,
conduct UK operations.

3126295345
06:51:03.199 --> 06:51:05.760
I will not shy away from
the fact that we hold our

3182525900
06:51:05.761 --> 06:51:08.842
armed forces to the very
highest legal standards,

473346315
06:51:08.843 --> 06:51:10.749
and time and time again they deliver.

1783047641
06:51:10.750 --> 06:51:13.007
New clause one seeks to
change domestic law,

3454472596
06:51:13.007 --> 06:51:15.765
but it would not remove our
international obligations.

2663374124
06:51:16.201 --> 06:51:18.863
The UK cannot opt out on
a case by case basis and in

2869221508
06:51:18.864 --> 06:51:22.802
doing so would simply
shift case to Strasbourg.

1012857822
06:51:22.803 --> 06:51:25.863
New clause six is also unnecessary
as the Secretary of State

3656778316
06:51:25.864 --> 06:51:29.407
can already derogate under
article 15 of the ECHR.

4123614287
06:51:29.408 --> 06:51:30.511
I'll read that again.

2960581464
06:51:30.512 --> 06:51:33.271
New clause six is also
unnecessary as the sector state

385105905
06:51:34.195 --> 06:51:36.552
can already derogate under
article 15 of ECHR,

1920673294
06:51:37.200 --> 06:51:40.760
meaning the amendment does not provide
him with any additional powers.

2544323832
06:51:40.761 --> 06:51:45.006
And I do not want to be in
the same club as Belarus or Russia.

468993672
06:51:45.007 --> 06:51:46.900
Turning to new clause three,

2525638367
06:51:46.901 --> 06:51:50.353
this amendment seeks to seeks
to place a requirement on

2158149174
06:51:50.354 --> 06:51:53.151
the Secretary of State
to appoint a National

1437934486
06:51:53.153 --> 06:51:54.906
Veterans Commissioner for England.

2488765726
06:51:54.907 --> 06:51:57.013
The amendments also set out the functions

1560088028
06:51:57.014 --> 06:51:59.607
for the proposed office holder.

1063481510
06:51:59.608 --> 06:52:01.660
I acknowledge I will give way.

943428862
06:52:01.661 --> 06:52:02.613
I'm very grateful.

3761060014
06:52:02.614 --> 06:52:04.952
>> Ukraine has derogated from the ECHR.

1310860924
06:52:04.953 --> 06:52:07.964
Does that put it in the same
bracket as Belarus and Russia?

1414317837
06:52:07.965 --> 06:52:08.416
>> Yeah.

1464008108
06:52:08.417 --> 06:52:09.503
>> Very good.

495262265
06:52:09.504 --> 06:52:11.763
>> May I remind the other
side of the House,

2691193246
06:52:11.764 --> 06:52:13.820
clause 12 of the Overseas Operation Bill

349259828
06:52:13.821 --> 06:52:15.575
introduced by the last government,

619935848
06:52:15.576 --> 06:52:17.631
would have required any future Secretary

540248467
06:52:17.632 --> 06:52:19.488
of State to consider whether to make

256843924
06:52:19.489 --> 06:52:21.595
a derogation under article 15 in relation

2043489300
06:52:21.596 --> 06:52:23.399
to significant overseas operations.

1604343416
06:52:23.400 --> 06:52:26.255
The last government removed
elements of clause 12

1616030496
06:52:26.256 --> 06:52:28.561
during the bill's final
stages in Parliament,

2536887599
06:52:28.563 --> 06:52:30.468
because the concerns were raised that

985049735
06:52:30.469 --> 06:52:32.424
the provision risked damaging the UK's

2429444787
06:52:32.425 --> 06:52:36.086
reputation for upholding the rule of
law and commitment to human rights.

4233819419
06:52:36.087 --> 06:52:39.196
The last government, clause 12,
was also seen as unnecessary,

1168006231
06:52:39.197 --> 06:52:42.757
and that government can already
derogate under article 15 of the ECHR,

3612395844
06:52:42.758 --> 06:52:46.057
meaning the provision did not add
any additional legal powers.

3435636425
06:52:46.058 --> 06:52:47.663
So turning to new clause three,

325879865
06:52:47.664 --> 06:52:50.354
this amendment seeks to
place a requirement on

2637668208
06:52:50.355 --> 06:52:52.612
the Secretary of State
to appoint a National

1142683141
06:52:52.613 --> 06:52:54.365
Veterans Commissioner for England.

856517555
06:52:54.367 --> 06:52:56.472
The amendment also sets out the functions

1699576082
06:52:56.474 --> 06:52:58.078
for the proposed office holder.

1438047459
06:52:58.079 --> 06:53:00.635
I acknowledge the sentiment
behind this amendment,

2096386667
06:53:00.636 --> 06:53:02.944
which is to ensure that
those who have served

3187084904
06:53:02.945 --> 06:53:05.250
receive the recognition
support they deserve.

1492568360
06:53:05.251 --> 06:53:07.556
Now, the Veterans
Commissioners for Scotland,

734526726
06:53:07.557 --> 06:53:10.314
Northern Ireland and Wales
are not statutory officers.

1846808286
06:53:10.315 --> 06:53:13.524
Therefore, such a role would not
in itself require legislation.

2534534040
06:53:13.525 --> 06:53:17.036
We are putting in place the valour
programme, which looks at digital.

3123604081
06:53:17.037 --> 06:53:19.695
It looks like a valour lead,
a digital headquarters.

3344155409
06:53:19.696 --> 06:53:22.354
It then looks at valour
officers and valour centres.

1202046210
06:53:22.355 --> 06:53:25.115
Once that is in place, we
then need to look at whether

2983426088
06:53:25.117 --> 06:53:27.373
we need a Veterans
Commissioner for England,

125972724
06:53:27.374 --> 06:53:30.435
how it docks into the valour
programme and how it docks into

311030466
06:53:30.436 --> 06:53:33.844
the Veterans Commissioners in
Northern Ireland, Wales and Scotland.

3518204164
06:53:33.845 --> 06:53:38.203
We will update the House in due
course when that is in place, based.

3209091749
06:53:38.204 --> 06:53:39.358
>> On new clause five.

3976156425
06:53:39.359 --> 06:53:43.365
We don't yet have
the date for the second day

1502190073
06:53:43.367 --> 06:53:47.207
on this bill for report and Third Reading,

3429944855
06:53:47.208 --> 06:53:49.365
but it seems likely that it will be before

2680975313
06:53:49.367 --> 06:53:51.609
the summer recess on the 16th of July.

2744935011
06:53:51.610 --> 06:53:54.701
Taking the Minister at his word.

3907616004
06:53:54.702 --> 06:53:57.261
And I think, knowing where
his heart lies on this,

2462362569
06:53:57.262 --> 06:54:00.867
can he give the House an assurance
that when we get that second day,

1811595521
06:54:00.868 --> 06:54:05.600
whenever it is, by that time, when
we get back to this on report,

1055068566
06:54:05.601 --> 06:54:07.356
we will table a similar amendment.

383818327
06:54:07.357 --> 06:54:10.017
He'll be able to come back
to us with some progress,

204406315
06:54:12.204 --> 06:54:13.808
including with the Home Office.

685680751
06:54:13.809 --> 06:54:16.619
>> We will update on progress
once we've spoken to Home

1773616810
06:54:16.620 --> 06:54:19.129
Office and when the bill
comes back to the House.

2628107699
06:54:19.130 --> 06:54:23.601
What I can say from a going back to
some of the questions made by hon.

890300244
06:54:23.602 --> 06:54:25.708
Friends across the house, my friend, hon.

3588677364
06:54:26.204 --> 06:54:29.814
Friend from Slough and his fantastic
