the non-working payment

1781547279
08:10:47.697 --> 08:10:49.500
getting National Insurance credits.

457908383
08:10:49.501 --> 08:10:53.391
So, Madam Deputy Speaker, you can
imagine how frustrating it is

1108902348
08:10:53.392 --> 08:10:56.453
when DWP case handlers give
advice, as they have done to us,

594373940
08:10:56.454 --> 08:10:59.764
that the issue with deductions
would be resolved by asking Social

3602050240
08:10:59.765 --> 08:11:02.934
Security Scotland to remove
the underlying entitlement,

3303856223
08:11:02.935 --> 08:11:07.339
it fails to demonstrate any understanding
of how many benefits work,

3794149806
08:11:07.340 --> 08:11:09.646
and frankly demonstrates
a willingness to let

1507847194
08:11:09.647 --> 08:11:11.955
people be worse off
because they own the DWP?

582863762
08:11:11.956 --> 08:11:14.386
S own rules are complicated to apply.

3095194443
08:11:14.387 --> 08:11:16.191
Secondly, Madam Deputy Speaker D.W.

1354094656
08:11:16.192 --> 08:11:19.151
systems need to be set up
correctly to process information

86729559
08:11:19.152 --> 08:11:21.759
being provided to them by
Social Security Scotland.

1435272393
08:11:21.760 --> 08:11:24.269
Now, I am not going to
claim that Social Security

1992035720
08:11:24.270 --> 08:11:26.075
Scotland is perfect by any stretch,

3687114941
08:11:26.076 --> 08:11:28.285
and it is not in
the purview of this place,

242237515
08:11:28.286 --> 08:11:31.448
but I would like to see more
joined up working from all sides.

1933359112
08:11:31.449 --> 08:11:34.110
However, I have been assured
as much as I am able to

3907671916
08:11:34.111 --> 08:11:36.668
be by Social Security
Scotland that their computer

3986664526
08:11:36.669 --> 08:11:38.975
system is communicating
properly with the DWP

3959409573
08:11:38.976 --> 08:11:43.020
and I have no reason to believe otherwise.

1186580083
08:11:43.021 --> 08:11:44.778
But from the DWP side I have been.

1642394010
08:11:44.779 --> 08:11:47.988
Varyingly told the following that
their system shows a claimant

2744602045
08:11:47.989 --> 08:11:50.497
in receipt of a payment
of Carer Support payment,

2704685362
08:11:50.498 --> 08:11:52.453
despite them never having received it.

4051006113
08:11:52.454 --> 08:11:54.561
Secondly, that it is DWP policy to deduct

3682634223
08:11:54.562 --> 08:11:56.687
Carer Support Payment as standard

2492471083
08:11:56.688 --> 08:12:00.238
unless explicitly told otherwise
by Social Security Scotland.

4124151802
08:12:00.239 --> 08:12:04.300
And worryingly, the Minister for
Social Security and Disability,

2442861148
08:12:04.301 --> 08:12:06.356
whilst acknowledging the issue in March,

3959167292
08:12:06.357 --> 08:12:09.089
told us in writing that
wrongful deductions

779592935
08:12:09.090 --> 08:12:10.744
may cause confusion to customers

1378906296
08:12:10.745 --> 08:12:13.855
and that they are exploring ways
to make the process clearer.

643937653
08:12:13.856 --> 08:12:17.838
Now my view is is yes, DWP
mistakes can be confusing,

948026883
08:12:17.839 --> 08:12:21.247
especially given the communications
issues I have already outlined.

1488175243
08:12:21.248 --> 08:12:24.007
But for me, this statement
misses the point by stating

785175182
08:12:24.008 --> 08:12:26.985
that the problem is
claimants understanding

2821290143
08:12:26.986 --> 08:12:29.195
what we need is a system
that does not make

4142979512
08:12:29.196 --> 08:12:31.402
these systematic errors
in the first place.

1362648783
08:12:31.403 --> 08:12:33.861
That is very squarely for
the Department to sort

494580835
08:12:33.862 --> 08:12:35.919
out and not the claimant, I would argue.

1891770882
08:12:35.920 --> 08:12:38.327
Now, just finally last
week, the specialist DWP

1134657167
08:12:38.328 --> 08:12:40.434
complaints team have either worked out or

4120940558
08:12:40.435 --> 08:12:42.844
come clean with us
and owned up to the systemic

1882814701
08:12:42.845 --> 08:12:44.749
error impacting many Scottish carers.

3543827235
08:12:44.750 --> 08:12:47.739
They want to find a fix,
but they do not have a timescale

487866506
08:12:47.740 --> 08:12:50.450
in which this will be achieved
and until then it will

3441623332
08:12:50.451 --> 08:12:53.245
be up to a claimant to
realise there is a problem

3900141783
08:12:53.246 --> 08:12:56.240
and each month asks the DWP
to correct the deduction.

190515767
08:12:56.241 --> 08:12:59.046
I will repeat that they want the claimant

2630010166
08:12:59.047 --> 08:13:01.395
to ask the DWP to correct the deduction.

2910303924
08:13:01.396 --> 08:13:04.506
Madam Deputy Speaker, we all
know that unpaid carers are some

1811075221
08:13:04.507 --> 08:13:07.640
of the most overstretched groups
of people in our society,

3234472666
08:13:07.641 --> 08:13:10.151
and the DWP is telling
them to take on the burden

2984272660
08:13:10.152 --> 08:13:12.608
of correcting their failures
every single month.

1247680816
08:13:12.609 --> 08:13:13.913
Carers week is next week.

34221372
08:13:13.914 --> 08:13:16.112
I do not think that is a message that we

3289013289
08:13:16.113 --> 08:13:17.919
want to be sending from this place,

2550733432
08:13:18.289 --> 08:13:19.493
or indeed from the DWP.

2880683965
08:13:19.494 --> 08:13:22.955
Madam Deputy Speaker, this does all
sound a bit dry and complicated.

2482473423
08:13:23.289 --> 08:13:30.446
Benefit applications, overlapping
payments and underlying entitlements

806436002
08:13:30.447 --> 08:13:33.994
and are have a real human impact
on the lives of our constituents.

1586386372
08:13:33.995 --> 08:13:36.853
Having your Universal Credit
payment reduced to nil when

739375686
08:13:36.854 --> 08:13:39.948
you have food to buy and bills
to pay is very difficult.

1886962564
08:13:39.949 --> 08:13:44.693
There is no buffer to help you out
while you battle DWP to find out why.

1234063685
08:13:44.694 --> 08:13:47.904
And I have seen constituents
relying on credit cards for basics

3599614904
08:13:47.905 --> 08:13:50.714
and going without to
the detriment of their own health.

2508534993
08:13:50.715 --> 08:13:53.022
The stress and distress
it causes is immense.

2916376549
08:13:53.288 --> 08:13:57.841
The DWP computer error is the reason
my constituent has been suicidal.

57628581
08:13:57.842 --> 08:14:00.344
It is causing extreme
anxiety to the other.

4281334645
08:14:00.345 --> 08:14:05.244
They are not alone and fundamentally
this is not their fault.

4106974281
08:14:05.245 --> 08:14:08.054
Madam Deputy Speaker, I want
to make one final addition

4026170569
08:14:08.055 --> 08:14:10.313
to my remarks before
I come to a conclusion.

472767861
08:14:10.314 --> 08:14:12.220
I am mainly prepared for this debate.

600113640
08:14:12.221 --> 08:14:15.382
When we received an update this
morning on one of these cases,

1901365069
08:14:15.383 --> 08:14:18.242
my constituent received
a letter saying that he would be

230642869
08:14:18.243 --> 08:14:20.902
receiving a back payment of
the best part of £3,000.

2331364984
08:14:20.903 --> 08:14:21.789
He was confused.

3883805297
08:14:21.790 --> 08:14:22.692
We were confused.

1690881618
08:14:22.693 --> 08:14:24.700
My office had spelled out as clearly as

2737618957
08:14:24.701 --> 08:14:26.889
they could to DWP that he just needed

1639828745
08:14:26.890 --> 08:14:28.645
his Universal Credit paid back for

64792137
08:14:28.646 --> 08:14:32.202
the period December 2025 to February 2026,

1725649675
08:14:32.203 --> 08:14:36.788
in which Carer's Support payment
had been incorrectly deducted.

1940236239
08:14:36.789 --> 08:14:39.588
Being given a confusing
payment of too much money

1432818121
08:14:39.589 --> 08:14:42.688
can frankly just be as
distressing as too little.

3317346658
08:14:42.689 --> 08:14:46.136
I cannot stress enough the fear
of relying on the DWP spending

2659965703
08:14:46.137 --> 08:14:49.643
the money and then being told
that you have to repay it.

3435627124
08:14:49.644 --> 08:14:53.042
I am sure we all recognise
that as constituency PS.

1700782262
08:14:53.043 --> 08:14:55.442
As it turns out,
the DWP got it wrong again

57386647
08:14:55.443 --> 08:14:57.398
despite everything they had been told.

3181656
08:14:57.399 --> 08:14:59.755
Despite the months of
investigating the claim,

3818377948
08:14:59.756 --> 08:15:03.498
they thought he had never
received Carer's Support payment,

1290232880
08:15:03.499 --> 08:15:06.491
which he did until December and had repaid

2795691069
08:15:06.492 --> 08:15:08.649
him for the whole period of the deduction.

2774835441
08:15:08.650 --> 08:15:11.359
So now a further investigation
has to be carried out,

2093672797
08:15:11.360 --> 08:15:14.140
and then my constituent
will have to pay back over

3059917607
08:15:14.141 --> 08:15:16.249
two thirds of what he has just been paid,

3163866493
08:15:16.250 --> 08:15:18.458
and he needs to keep
that money until then.

1628000349
08:15:18.459 --> 08:15:22.988
I am really sorry, but
I just find that unacceptable.

813938908
08:15:22.989 --> 08:15:24.344
What on earth is going on?

2232090696
08:15:24.345 --> 08:15:25.698
And, Madam Deputy Speaker,

3558710957
08:15:25.699 --> 08:15:28.457
my constituent spotted
the problem, came to my office,

2106696743
08:15:28.458 --> 08:15:31.418
and after months of back
and forth, we have understood it.

1766837775
08:15:31.419 --> 08:15:32.723
But there are over 30,000

2136155174
08:15:32.724 --> 08:15:35.130
carers across Scotland
who have this underlying

1344548650
08:15:35.131 --> 08:15:38.751
entitlement and could be missing out
on Universal Credit as a result.

2163624559
08:15:38.752 --> 08:15:41.648
It has been a battle to get
to where we are today,

4044848306
08:15:41.649 --> 08:15:44.509
and I would not be surprised
if many carers in Scotland,

2447440343
08:15:44.510 --> 08:15:47.402
if told by the DWP that
the best thing to do would be to

1401704986
08:15:47.403 --> 08:15:50.110
give up their underlying
entitlement to this payment,

2479830254
08:15:50.289 --> 08:15:51.695
would do so and give it up.

1103393616
08:15:51.696 --> 08:15:53.952
And there are consequences
to that decision.

4190521109
08:15:53.953 --> 08:15:56.261
So I therefore hope that
the Minister can use

4023936775
08:15:56.262 --> 08:15:58.269
his time to set out what the Department

2825647923
08:15:58.270 --> 08:16:01.498
is doing to ensure its staff properly know

106245750
08:16:01.499 --> 08:16:03.503
about and understand Scottish benefits,

2325085457
08:16:03.504 --> 08:16:06.093
what engagement his department is having

1803348987
08:16:06.094 --> 08:16:08.443
with the Scottish Government in relation

2617145574
08:16:08.444 --> 08:16:10.952
to ensuring how we can get
that working together,

495396901
08:16:10.953 --> 08:16:12.208
and to refer to the hon.

1147169356
08:16:12.209 --> 08:16:15.841
Member for Strangford making sure
that that happens on a UK basis

2913460459
08:16:15.842 --> 08:16:19.401
and what their current understanding
of the underlying error is,

3120296927
08:16:19.402 --> 08:16:21.259
what steps are being taken to fix it

1881323594
08:16:21.260 --> 08:16:23.317
and what the timescale for this will be,

2492701105
08:16:23.318 --> 08:16:26.190
and crucially, what steps
are being taken to identify

2509402159
08:16:26.191 --> 08:16:28.688
carers being underpaid or wrongly advised

3220480755
08:16:28.689 --> 08:16:31.595
to drop their entitlement
and to offer proper

3912915641
08:16:31.596 --> 08:16:33.701
support while those errors are rectified.

4199165660
08:16:33.702 --> 08:16:37.641
Thank you, Madam Deputy Speaker.

701315383
08:16:37.642 --> 08:16:43.144
>> Minister thank you, Madam
Deputy Speaker and I will

2792458271
08:16:43.145 --> 08:16:45.705
begin at the outset by
saying that I hope the hon.

3220811268
08:16:45.706 --> 08:16:48.946
Lady saw me taking extensive notes there.

1077216104
08:16:48.947 --> 08:16:52.298
The speech that I was planning
to give was not as bespoke

1417328050
08:16:52.299 --> 08:16:56.802
to the issues that she raises
as perhaps she would like.

1419636820
08:16:57.293 --> 08:17:00.851
So I think at the outset,
I want to make clear to her that

3981482728
08:17:00.852 --> 08:17:03.963
if there are specific cases that
she wants to escalate to me,

3817500665
08:17:03.964 --> 08:17:07.795
clearly she has been
escalating them through usual

163492828
08:17:07.796 --> 08:17:11.096
channels to departmental
complaints teams, etc.

2458794332
08:17:11.097 --> 08:17:14.543
I am very, very happy to
have a look at those.

23090076
08:17:14.544 --> 08:17:15.094
Certainly.

3300094734
08:17:15.095 --> 08:17:16.607
>> Thank you.

3292544243
08:17:16.608 --> 08:17:17.310
>> Very much.

1658451362
08:17:17.311 --> 08:17:17.963
I just want.

1413211784
08:17:17.964 --> 08:17:21.608
Madam Deputy Speaker, I just
want to put on the record that

2404552180
08:17:21.609 --> 08:17:24.467
the Minister for Social Security
and Disability has been

3058916565
08:17:24.468 --> 08:17:27.830
very keen to work with me to
understand the problems that we have,

2487102318
08:17:27.831 --> 08:17:29.938
and we are very grateful for the support.

559835068
08:17:29.939 --> 08:17:33.050
What we are looking at is, is
the issues are still happening,

2650164152
08:17:33.051 --> 08:17:35.660
and I am grateful that
the Minister has taken them.

3450775733
08:17:35.661 --> 08:17:37.116
>> And I do understand that.

2408806002
08:17:37.117 --> 08:17:39.123
Madam Deputy Speaker, I would add that,

3657318850
08:17:39.124 --> 08:17:41.129
as the Minister with responsibility for

1751672104
08:17:41.130 --> 08:17:43.234
the relationship with Scottish Government

1806329519
08:17:43.235 --> 08:17:45.239
and therefore Social Security Scotland,

1570938890
08:17:45.240 --> 08:17:48.504
if she would be kind enough to let
me know too, I would be very,

3398056959
08:17:48.505 --> 08:17:51.266
very happy to see what we can
do to seek a resolution.

2686623460
08:17:51.267 --> 08:17:54.627
I do think it would be helpful,
Madam Deputy Speaker, nonetheless,

1245594409
08:17:54.628 --> 08:17:56.987
to just set out a little
bit of the background

1782542545
08:17:57.251 --> 08:17:59.207
and context to this before saying what

1962387872
08:17:59.208 --> 08:18:01.755
I am able to today about the particular

3315189967
08:18:01.756 --> 08:18:03.710
peculiarities that she highlights with

3952285359
08:18:03.711 --> 08:18:09.399
the system and the impact that that
has had on some of her constituents.

3220994968
08:18:09.400 --> 08:18:14.738
But we should, of course, all
expect, Madam Deputy Speaker,

3887540447
08:18:14.739 --> 08:18:18.092
our welfare system to deliver
for people as a safety net

65191164
08:18:18.093 --> 08:18:21.102
in difficult times and give
people the opportunity to build

1579689545
08:18:21.103 --> 08:18:24.849
better lives wherever in
the UK they happen to live.

3549612157
08:18:24.850 --> 08:18:27.862
So it is only right that we do
pay attention to this issue.

2502825664
08:18:27.863 --> 08:18:31.503
She is a powerful advocate for her
constituents in North East Fife,

2377817779
08:18:31.504 --> 08:18:34.295
but wherever colleagues
are around the country,

4086167828
08:18:34.296 --> 08:18:36.453
they should be able to expect an effective

2090224998
08:18:36.454 --> 08:18:38.609
and efficient service from the department,

3572747891
08:18:38.610 --> 08:18:40.113
as should their constituents.

1955291451
08:18:40.114 --> 08:18:43.322
In terms of background, following
the devolution of significant

242125728
08:18:43.323 --> 08:18:46.030
social security powers through
the Scotland Act 2016,

2412001652
08:18:46.031 --> 08:18:49.241
the delivery of welfare support
to people in Scotland is shared

1640440169
08:18:49.242 --> 08:18:51.999
between the UK government
and the Scottish Government.

1950336561
08:18:52.000 --> 08:18:54.708
This means many people in
Scotland now receive Social

298243139
08:18:54.709 --> 08:18:56.965
security support from
both the UK government

3192397513
08:18:56.966 --> 08:18:59.423
provided by the DWP
and the Scottish Government,

2448306326
08:18:59.424 --> 08:19:02.203
delivered by Social Security Scotland.

2302943468
08:19:02.204 --> 08:19:02.755
Of course.

3952827587
08:19:02.756 --> 08:19:06.050
>> We congratulate the Member
for North East Fife on raising

4142468058
08:19:06.051 --> 08:19:08.909
a very important issue that
our constituents are facing.

1738719598
08:19:08.910 --> 08:19:11.418
I wonder, though, if
the Minister will agree with

1994121936
08:19:11.419 --> 08:19:13.776
me that the prolonged
confusion and delay over

3944319625
08:19:13.777 --> 08:19:16.583
Social Security Scotland
taking over the administration

3085261012
08:19:16.584 --> 08:19:18.339
of devolved benefits from the DWP,

2059128462
08:19:18.340 --> 08:19:21.299
has contributed to a sense of
confusion among people about

696462868
08:19:21.300 --> 08:19:24.839
who is responsible for
the support that they're receiving.

4152553845
08:19:24.840 --> 08:19:25.794
>> I think my hon.

618085497
08:19:25.795 --> 08:19:27.449
Friend makes an important point.

3796093285
08:19:27.450 --> 08:19:29.904
I don't want to get
into a tit for tat with

2922701944
08:19:29.905 --> 08:19:33.042
in terms of determining responsibility

3828371726
08:19:33.043 --> 08:19:36.250
between the Westminster government
and the Scottish Government,

1692050633
08:19:36.251 --> 08:19:39.211
but it is certainly fair to say
that the agency agreements

577127030
08:19:39.212 --> 08:19:41.547
that we've entered into
have been extended,

1922028027
08:19:41.548 --> 08:19:43.993
in some cases on more than one occasion,

361488697
08:19:43.994 --> 08:19:48.193
and that can lead to a protracted amount

746127532
08:19:48.194 --> 08:19:50.102
of time for us to be able to deliver,

184617997
08:19:50.103 --> 08:19:53.993
as we would hope, and in the most
indeed aligned way possible.

4225730200
08:19:53.994 --> 08:19:54.544
Certainly.

2216708810
08:19:54.545 --> 08:19:55.497
>> I congratulate.

892602133
08:19:55.498 --> 08:19:55.899
>> The.

777135442
08:19:55.900 --> 08:19:57.204
>> Member for North East.

2764285482
08:19:57.205 --> 08:19:57.857
>> Fife for.

1687117973
08:19:57.858 --> 08:19:58.610
>> The debate.

2536569486
08:19:58.611 --> 08:20:01.821
>> She's had tonight, and also
congratulate the Member for Ayr,

105829683
08:20:01.822 --> 08:20:04.781
Carrick and Cumnock on her new
position in the Department.

654614426
08:20:04.782 --> 08:20:07.090
Might the Minister agree
with me that at £600

1593796568
08:20:07.091 --> 08:20:08.997
million the cost of 5000 motor homes,

355469469
08:20:08.998 --> 08:20:12.108
the set up of Social Security
Scotland is a national scandal?

1959219564
08:20:12.109 --> 08:20:15.544
>> Thank I you.

1615363997
08:20:15.545 --> 08:20:16.247
>> Again, he.

2382768774
08:20:16.248 --> 08:20:16.950
He tempts me.

1221357221
08:20:16.951 --> 08:20:20.205
I would agree that it is.

1524330019
08:20:20.206 --> 08:20:23.499
It is not alone in being
a national scandal up in Scotland,

4079287497
08:20:23.500 --> 08:20:25.649
if indeed that is what it is.

4215217074
08:20:25.650 --> 08:20:29.260
But for the purposes of seeking to
maintain a constructive relationship

3273430701
08:20:29.261 --> 08:20:31.869
with my counterparts in
Scotland, I may swerve the.

943546407
08:20:31.870 --> 08:20:38.448
The broader steer of that of
that particular question.

76236121
08:20:38.449 --> 08:20:40.499
But the focus should always be.

665179515
08:20:40.500 --> 08:20:43.559
Madam Deputy Speaker, on ensuring
that both systems work for

1759011595
08:20:43.560 --> 08:20:46.418
those who actually use it,
that people experience clear,

2309874144
08:20:46.419 --> 08:20:51.696
reliable and efficient service,
even if they receive support

2545775105
08:20:51.697 --> 08:20:54.104
from both the DWP
and Social Security Scotland.

1505831106
08:20:54.296 --> 08:20:55.198
>> Certainly for.

3011183052
08:20:55.199 --> 08:20:56.503
Can I thank the Minister?

2356659434
08:20:56.504 --> 08:20:58.759
He's always constructive
and always helpful,

4124589365
08:20:58.760 --> 08:21:00.667
and we look forward to to his answers

2281649823
08:21:00.668 --> 08:21:02.775
and and his contribution to help the hon.

3692889430
08:21:02.776 --> 08:21:04.632
Lady for North East Fife and others.

456104369
08:21:04.633 --> 08:21:06.640
But I know the debate is with Scotland.

242540868
08:21:06.641 --> 08:21:07.593
I mentioned North.

1235351216
08:21:07.594 --> 08:21:09.348
Now we're having similar problems.

4040547218
08:21:09.349 --> 08:21:13.102
So I just ask very kindly, would
the Minister engage in agree if we have

2949157726
08:21:13.103 --> 08:21:16.715
similar problems and we can highlight
them, would he take ours as well?

1588339908
08:21:16.716 --> 08:21:17.669
Thank you so much.

1325769080
08:21:17.670 --> 08:21:18.723
>> I certainly will.

1889668360
08:21:18.724 --> 08:21:21.984
As I said earlier, I am the Minister
responsible for devolution.

3071483394
08:21:21.985 --> 08:21:24.341
I have regular conversations
with Gordon Lyons

2335252223
08:21:24.342 --> 08:21:27.797
as the Minister for
communities, and I'm very,

4267041950
08:21:27.798 --> 08:21:30.854
very happy to pick up any
specifics where there

1706211473
08:21:30.855 --> 08:21:32.762
are kinks that need to be ironed out.

54936043
08:21:33.296 --> 08:21:35.705
I'm very, very happy to
do that for any member.

2568589038
08:21:35.706 --> 08:21:38.013
But Madam Deputy Speaker,
by March this year,

408721947
08:21:38.014 --> 08:21:40.322
DWP had completed its
role in the transfer of

4179859088
08:21:40.323 --> 08:21:42.980
customers in receipt of four
major devolved benefits

2959845364
08:21:42.981 --> 08:21:44.835
across the Social Security Scotland.

789021329
08:21:44.836 --> 08:21:47.800
This involved around
730 000 benefit awards

303479025
08:21:47.801 --> 08:21:49.554
for Personal Independence Payment,

3595954497
08:21:49.555 --> 08:21:52.198
Disability Living Allowance,
Carer's Allowance

733124131
08:21:52.199 --> 08:21:54.002
and Attendance Allowance customers.

2661640422
08:21:54.297 --> 08:21:56.352
This was a hugely important undertaking,

643886145
08:21:56.353 --> 08:21:58.911
not only because of
the number of people affected,

1921649198
08:21:58.912 --> 08:22:03.696
but because of how vital this
support so often is to people.

3550351842
08:22:03.697 --> 08:22:07.348
It required close operational
coordination, robust data sharing,

2123714823
08:22:07.349 --> 08:22:09.855
careful communication with
customers and a shared

691403734
08:22:09.856 --> 08:22:12.449
commitment to ensuring
continuity of support.

3548870849
08:22:12.450 --> 08:22:13.856
And I do hear what the hon.

189342717
08:22:13.857 --> 08:22:17.707
Lady says about her constituents
experience of that,

1061927507
08:22:17.708 --> 08:22:20.117
and it is a point that
is incredibly well made.

2157530104
08:22:20.296 --> 08:22:24.501
But crucially, in broad terms, it
did deliver for people in Scotland.

3997874432
08:22:24.502 --> 08:22:28.252
Payments continued without
interruption at the point of transfer,

2676183803
08:22:28.253 --> 08:22:31.060
and people were supported
and kept informed throughout.

3587394847
08:22:31.061 --> 08:22:33.968
That was a significant achievement
by both organisations.

2295405837
08:22:34.296 --> 08:22:37.555
Madam Deputy Speaker and a clear
demonstration of what effective

2457360463
08:22:37.556 --> 08:22:42.350
cooperative working can deliver
throughout this complex process.

2748316666
08:22:42.351 --> 08:22:45.611
It was very important that Scottish
customers should know how to

1232250281
08:22:45.612 --> 08:22:50.548
access information and who to
contact about devolved benefits.

2439264501
08:22:50.549 --> 08:22:53.254
DWP operational staff
also needed to know how

1079733851
08:22:53.255 --> 08:22:55.510
to signpost and support
customers correctly,

1428411243
08:22:55.511 --> 08:22:57.919
and I will take away
the particular point about

1328784020
08:22:57.920 --> 08:22:59.774
strengthening training that the hon.

2365672934
08:22:59.775 --> 08:23:03.598
Lady raised because if that has not
been delivered to full effect,

533808814
08:23:03.599 --> 08:23:06.811
then we need to make sure that
that is the case moving forward.

1631079085
08:23:06.812 --> 08:23:10.652
But to achieve this, DWP
and Social Security Scotland

4216088425
08:23:10.653 --> 08:23:12.707
work together on customer communications

2436222112
08:23:12.708 --> 08:23:16.655
and ensuring the messaging was clear
and consistent wherever possible,

1878192899
08:23:16.656 --> 08:23:19.814
with detailed information on
the changes to devolved benefits.

1671208751
08:23:19.815 --> 08:23:23.006
Published on gov.uk and Gov dot scot.

3582097443
08:23:23.007 --> 08:23:26.950
DWP operational guidance has been
updated to ensure DWP colleagues

2791907593
08:23:26.951 --> 08:23:30.211
are aware of the changes and where
procedures have been updated,

2386522677
08:23:31.255 --> 08:23:34.412
and colleagues received specific
guidance on handling customer

2659341331
08:23:34.413 --> 08:23:37.470
queries on Social Security
Scotland's benefits and payments,

2684358062
08:23:37.471 --> 08:23:39.927
with both organisations
agreeing that each would

2038103989
08:23:39.928 --> 08:23:41.983
signpost to the other where appropriate,

4049277777
08:23:41.984 --> 08:23:45.594
but should avoid providing guidance
or advice on each other's benefits.

2924092673
08:23:45.595 --> 08:23:47.802
There is the particular
point that the hon.

1533604521
08:23:47.803 --> 08:23:50.310
Lady made about the level
within the organisation

252308544
08:23:50.311 --> 08:23:52.367
that that training had been cascaded to,

756809514
08:23:52.368 --> 08:23:54.878
and I will check and confirm
that for her to make

4088109078
08:23:54.879 --> 08:23:58.854
sure that it has rippled
through to all levels.

3850519296
08:23:58.855 --> 08:24:01.312
But while both DWP and
the Scottish Government's

2999012640
08:24:01.313 --> 08:24:03.769
devolution programmes
closed in March this year,

440533098
08:24:03.770 --> 08:24:06.379
nobody should take this as
an indication that we do

1454747148
08:24:06.380 --> 08:24:08.836
not continue to work
together extremely closely.

3174353742
08:24:08.837 --> 08:24:11.153
As I have already said, it is vital that

3508872216
08:24:11.154 --> 08:24:12.806
co-operative relations continue.

606961248
08:24:13.300 --> 08:24:18.904
That is why DWP has created the Social
Security Scotland Liaison Unit,

1623173614
08:24:18.905 --> 08:24:21.552
a new function to support
the ongoing relationship

4272020081
08:24:21.553 --> 08:24:23.800
with Social Security Scotland.

3952111240
08:24:23.801 --> 08:24:26.158
The Liaison Unit will
ensure future changes to

454475220
08:24:26.159 --> 08:24:29.856
devolved and reserved
benefits are coordinated

895904774
08:24:29.857 --> 08:24:32.114
and also support DWP
business areas with any

1858724335
08:24:32.299 --> 08:24:34.353
Social Security Scotland facing matters.

3939215631
08:24:35.300 --> 08:24:38.359
Alongside the work of the unit,
DWP, the Scottish Government

4096919961
08:24:38.360 --> 08:24:41.620
and Social Security Scotland
continue to join up at many levels.

185743467
08:24:41.621 --> 08:24:44.078
Senior leaders agreed to
establish a joint forum

1564521363
08:24:44.079 --> 08:24:46.485
for Social Security
Scotland and DWP operations

277239224
08:24:46.486 --> 08:24:49.251
to exchange feedback to support continuous

982949465
08:24:49.252 --> 08:24:51.256
improvement and jointly resolve issues.

242502776
08:24:51.296 --> 08:24:55.051
The Joint Operational Working
Group provides an opportunity

2352735707
08:24:55.052 --> 08:24:57.007
to discuss the customer experience and

2050875613
08:24:57.008 --> 08:24:59.966
the journey our shared customers
are navigating to receive

4265160147
08:24:59.967 --> 08:25:03.456
the financial support
they are entitled to.

399030261
08:25:03.457 --> 08:25:04.961
There is, of course, certain.

2496470774
08:25:04.962 --> 08:25:05.513
>> Giving.

144354319
08:25:06.300 --> 08:25:06.500
We.

2408658514
08:25:06.501 --> 08:25:09.902
Again, I would be very interested
to understand if he would

2897123986
08:25:09.903 --> 08:25:13.553
agree with me that the problem
that we have identified,

738707797
08:25:13.554 --> 08:25:15.660
and potentially the scale of the problem.

2452918007
08:25:15.661 --> 08:25:17.867
Given the number of
unpaid carers receiving

2178720579
08:25:17.868 --> 08:25:19.572
an entitlement to this allowance,

3286512434
08:25:19.573 --> 08:25:22.105
should be looked at by this working group.

3664284196
08:25:22.106 --> 08:25:25.304
>> If it is OK with the hon.

276533969
08:25:25.305 --> 08:25:27.363
Lady, I will come to the broad thrust of

3510689036
08:25:27.364 --> 08:25:29.219
the problem that she has identified,

1486459038
08:25:29.257 --> 08:25:31.214
because I think it is quite complex in

760650263
08:25:31.215 --> 08:25:33.352
that there are also some challenges

4268048478
08:25:33.353 --> 08:25:36.915
in England and Wales in this space
that were identified by the review.

216099305
08:25:38.300 --> 08:25:40.961
But I will say a little more
in a moment about that.

3774970439
08:25:40.962 --> 08:25:42.967
But there is also continued ministerial

296632300
08:25:42.968 --> 08:25:44.923
engagement between the UK and Scottish

2998278847
08:25:44.924 --> 08:25:48.332
governments through the Joint
Ministerial Working Group on welfare,

431076237
08:25:48.333 --> 08:25:50.589
as a long standing forum
providing oversight

2184236370
08:25:50.590 --> 08:25:52.846
of the devolution of
social security powers.

1187846936
08:25:52.847 --> 08:25:55.805
In addition, of course, to
bilateral meetings as required,

505583391
08:25:55.806 --> 08:26:02.008
and I am the government's
representative on that working group.

3435934686
08:26:02.009 --> 08:26:05.256
But if I may turn to
the the thrust of the hon.

2221785150
08:26:05.257 --> 08:26:08.214
Member's contribution about
the plight of her constituents

3939342361
08:26:08.215 --> 08:26:10.200
in receipt of carers support payments,

2026983076
08:26:10.201 --> 08:26:12.950
she is correct that
the number of complaint

3583372027
08:26:12.951 --> 08:26:14.855
handlers has been increased recently.

1107303418
08:26:16.301 --> 08:26:20.101
It's also worth mentioning, for
the benefit of all colleagues,

4007874962
08:26:20.102 --> 08:26:23.861
that I have personally now
moved into a series of regular

4045505071
08:26:23.862 --> 08:26:26.804
meetings on complaints
and indeed MP correspondence,

865537061
08:26:26.805 --> 08:26:30.015
because I think it's fair to say
that the Department recognises

3402674744
08:26:30.016 --> 08:26:32.576
more must be done urgently
to take a grip of that.

4197776557
08:26:33.300 --> 08:26:36.362
In the last two weeks I've had
2 or 3 such meetings already,

2182464025
08:26:36.363 --> 08:26:40.753
and they will continue until we
reach an acceptable level in

3251509115
08:26:40.754 --> 08:26:45.153
terms of complaint handling
and timeliness of response.

1848188126
08:26:45.154 --> 08:26:47.605
In that vein, if she would like to send me

2216514346
08:26:47.606 --> 08:26:49.952
the case that she referred to in March,

2203249417
08:26:49.953 --> 08:26:53.617
where she's been told that that is yet
to be assigned to a case handler,

1563392838
08:26:53.618 --> 08:26:59.507
I would be very, very happy
to look into that for her.

3968358932
08:27:00.256 --> 08:27:02.362
But this has clearly been distressing for

4178589973
08:27:02.363 --> 08:27:04.704
a number of constituents of the hon.

2165170635
08:27:04.705 --> 08:27:07.201
Members, and I acknowledge that.

2667096931
08:27:07.202 --> 08:27:09.458
I also acknowledge that
there will sometimes

2365591833
08:27:09.459 --> 08:27:11.064
be cases where someone is given

926332535
08:27:11.065 --> 08:27:13.405
the wrong information
by either my department

1536644055
08:27:13.406 --> 08:27:15.602
or by Social Security Scotland,

2636255882
08:27:15.603 --> 08:27:18.932
or where our IT systems could
join up more effectively.

3245645779
08:27:18.933 --> 08:27:22.509
Where that happens, we need to
work together to put that right.

122849201
08:27:22.510 --> 08:27:26.006
Where I slightly disagree with the hon.

3126325854
08:27:26.007 --> 08:27:28.063
Lady is the suggestion that this exists.

288395507
08:27:28.064 --> 08:27:29.805
As I said, only in Scotland.

3990852061
08:27:29.806 --> 08:27:32.113
I think it's a rather
more nuanced situation.

2421035121
08:27:32.114 --> 08:27:34.271
There are clearly, from what she has said,

1459242310
08:27:35.300 --> 08:27:37.810
some issues that I need
to take away and look at.

301591855
08:27:38.304 --> 08:27:40.161
But some of the issues that the hon.

4237814806
08:27:40.162 --> 08:27:43.356
Member has identified, we
have seen in England too,

3338698860
08:27:43.357 --> 08:27:46.607
and I probably do myself
no favours by saying that,

1581075364
08:27:46.608 --> 08:27:50.271
in that I think that we've got a broader
DWP issue rather than something

1282967996
08:27:50.272 --> 08:27:54.606
that I would pin directly on
Social Security Scotland,

2325961884
08:27:54.607 --> 08:27:57.617
for example, as I just referenced,
the issue in how Carer's

2165682701
08:27:57.618 --> 08:28:00.625
Allowance and Universal Credit
work together was identified

2610792520
08:28:00.626 --> 08:28:03.183
in the review of Carer's
Allowance overpayments in

3423292048
08:28:03.184 --> 08:28:05.741
England and Wales in respect
of Carer's Allowance.

104755911
08:28:05.742 --> 08:28:08.300
We are committed to delivering
this change in line

1157681284
08:28:08.301 --> 08:28:10.407
with our plans to modernise DWP services.

3248047159
08:28:10.408 --> 08:28:13.463
It will be for me as Minister
to ensure that there

664622305
08:28:13.464 --> 08:28:16.158
is a transition of those new arrangements

528098927
08:28:16.159 --> 08:28:21.208
that supports the Scottish mechanisms also

1389257594
08:28:21.209 --> 08:28:23.163
work to automatically offset benefits,

858557142
08:28:23.164 --> 08:28:26.527
which is where we want to get to,
will begin in the next financial

1876541397
08:28:26.528 --> 08:28:29.536
year and is intended for
completion within this Parliament.

3614844496
08:28:29.537 --> 08:28:31.846
But hearing as I am for
the first time today,

4027776174
08:28:32.304 --> 08:28:33.859
the specifics of what the hon.

227643136
08:28:33.860 --> 08:28:36.110
Lady has said, I will take that away.

31654987
08:28:36.111 --> 08:28:40.461
I am not able to make a commitment
that that will be quickened up,

2426293582
08:28:40.462 --> 08:28:42.572
but I want to have a look at that and see

2659381114
08:28:42.573 --> 08:28:44.430
if there is anything that we can do,

1076998061
08:28:44.431 --> 08:28:47.841
but we will work specifically on
CSP with Social Security Scotland,

1148609517
08:28:47.842 --> 08:28:50.651
to look at any issues around
data sharing and processes

2309381043
08:28:50.652 --> 08:28:55.311
necessary to align that
are specific to Scotland.

1047214146
08:28:55.312 --> 08:28:59.861
What I would also just briefly
say, Madam Deputy Speaker,

1533167319
08:28:59.862 --> 08:29:03.256
is that the implementation of
the Social Security powers in

3648871149
08:29:03.257 --> 08:29:06.467
the Scotland Act 2016 has been
a significant programme of work,

1800185591
08:29:06.468 --> 08:29:09.656
underpinned by strong cooperation between

2793115794
08:29:09.657 --> 08:29:12.801
DWP and Social Security Scotland.

371390589
08:29:12.802 --> 08:29:15.962
At every level, of course, there
will be ongoing work required

3440105087
08:29:15.963 --> 08:29:18.670
to keep the two systems
working effectively together,

573553280
08:29:18.671 --> 08:29:20.978
but my department is
committed to doing that.

881733878
08:29:20.979 --> 08:29:22.684
In the spirit of this productive,

2584557925
08:29:22.685 --> 08:29:25.140
customer focussed relationship
with the Scottish

3407129714
08:29:25.141 --> 08:29:27.195
Government and Social Security Scotland.

4215653692
08:29:27.196 --> 08:29:28.651
As issues arise and the hon.

2737222265
08:29:28.652 --> 08:29:31.413
Lady has outlined many today
and as I said to the hon.

3733495485
08:29:31.414 --> 08:29:34.673
Gentleman from Strangford where
he has them in Northern Ireland,

2050536856
08:29:34.674 --> 08:29:36.710
I am happy to look at those two.

840812940
08:29:36.711 --> 08:29:39.921
We will work together as Social
Security Scotland in this case,

2990183295
08:29:39.922 --> 08:29:44.357
and the Department for Work and Pensions
to draw on lessons learned from

3379068279
08:29:44.358 --> 08:29:46.362
navigating the complexities of creating

1165092024
08:29:46.363 --> 08:29:48.167
a shared social security landscape,

3869829606
08:29:48.168 --> 08:29:51.811
to find solutions that are
respectful of devolution,

2666144219
08:29:51.812 --> 08:29:54.768
maintain our commitment to
working together constructively

3239777929
08:29:54.769 --> 08:29:57.427
and always keeping in mind
what really matters here,

1082456562
08:29:57.428 --> 08:30:00.538
which is the people that
the Department for Work and Pensions

3803156071
08:30:00.539 --> 08:30:02.896
and Social Security
Scotland are here to help,

707610685
08:30:02.897 --> 08:30:07.654
and the experience that
they have of our services.

2722512253
08:30:07.655 --> 08:30:12.658
>> The question is that
this House do now adjourn,

349630301
08:30:12.659 --> 08:30:19.407
as many as are of that opinion say aye.

4222026639
08:30:19.408 --> 08:30:20.311
the ayes have it.

2156968368
08:30:20.312 --> 08:30:21.013
Order, order!

